title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shells and bake for 30 minutes at 350 degrees and then reduce heat to 325 degrees and bake an additional 30 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: sweet and sour red cabbage
directions: Place
cabbage in casserole dish in layers of apple and onion. Season
each
layer
with salt, pepper and sugar.	Put herbs
in middle.
Pour Port and vinegar over finished layers. Cover and cook
at
300° for 2 hours.
If desired, sour cream may be stirred in just before serving.
Serves 4.

title: corn pone pie
directions: Brown meat and onions in skillet.
Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Place in baking dish and cover with cornbread batter and bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable-stuffed chicken
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover tightly with heavy-duty plastic wrap.
Fold back a small edge of wrap to allow steam to escape.
Microwave at High 5 to 6 minutes, or until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring every 2 minutes.
Drain vegetables.
Spoon vegetables into cavity of chicken.
Truss chicken; place, breast side down, on a microwave roasting rack.
Combine browning-and-seasoning sauce and butter; brush or rub half of mixture into skin.
Combine basil and lemon rind; sprinkle half over chicken.
Microwave at High 10 minutes. Turn chicken, breast side up.

Brush or rub remaining browning mixture into skin; sprinkle with remaining basil mixture. Microwave at High 18 to 22 minutes, or until temperature of stuffing is 145° and meat at thigh registers 185°.
Drumsticks will be easy to move.
Yields 4 servings.

title: new french onion soup
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter ovenproof soup bowls.
Melt 1/2 cup butter in skillet over medium heat. Cook onions until tender and transfer to soup bowls.
Mix soup, milk, salt and pepper to taste and pour over onions.
Top with French bread slice and grated cheese.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: finger lick'n chicken
directions: Mix eggs, milk, seasoned salt and pepper together in separate bowl.
Add chicken and let set in the ingredients for 5 minutes. In separate container add flour to chicken.
Fry as usual.

title: grasshopper angel
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk, cool, add liqueurs and salt.
Fold in whipped cream.
Put 1/3 mixture on each layer of angel cake and top, letting it run down the sides.
Store in refrigerator.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Add evaporated milk into which white vinegar has been added, this will sour the milk.
Roll out for pies.

title: mexican casserole no. 2
directions: Brown beef in skillet, mashing constantly to eliminate lumps. Drain.
Add all ingredients except Doritos.
Mix well and let heat in a large Dutch oven (pot).
When ready to serve, add Doritos and reheat.

title: wild rice and mushrooms
directions: Soak rice in warm water about 2 to 4 hours.
Wash rice several times and drain.
Boil 3 quarts of water and add rice.
Bring to second boil; remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 10 minutes. Drain.
Cook bacon until crisp and drain.
Melt butter in separate pan with chopped vegetables.
Saute until half done.
Mix rice, bacon and vegetables together.
Place in greased baking dish; cover and bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.

title: castillian skillet dinner
directions: Melt margarine in a large skillet and brown beef in it. Remove beef and drain on paper towel.
Saute onion in remaining margarine. Mix meat, onions and remaining vegetables and spices in skillet.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Serve on tortillas you have preheated.

title: chicken breast scallopini
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken and Parmesan cheese, in a bowl and refrigerate.
Sauce should be made at least 3 hours in advance.

title: watergate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Wash cranberries. Chop in blender. Stir 2 cups boiling water in jello until dissolved, about 2 minutes. Add sugar and chopped cranberries. Add apples and nuts. Refrigerate 4 hours.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix ingredients.
Mix 3 teaspoons to 1 cup of hot water.

title: cocoa kiss cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy. Combine flour and cocoa.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Add nuts, beat on low until blended.
Chill dough for 1 hour or until firm enough to handle.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops, floured, in fat.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook in electric skillet for 1 1/2 hours at 150° or bake in oven for 1 1/2 hours at 375°.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cut bacon in pieces.
Fry until brown.	Keep 1/2 cup of bacon drippings and fry the onions in it.
Drain.
Mix vinegar, sugar and water; bring to a boil.
Add cornstarch, onions and bacon. Pour mix over potatoes and heat thoroughly.

title: spiced prune drops
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix brown sugar, margarine, milk and egg. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until almost no indentation remains when touched, 8 to 9 minutes.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Chop cranberries in food processor. Mix with 1 cup sugar. Let stand in the refrigerator several hours or overnight. Dissolve jello with hot water and add to cranberries and sugar. Add orange juice, orange rind, undrained pineapple, celery, pecans and apple. Mix well and pour into mold. Chill.

title: pie dough
directions: Beat egg.
Add vinegar to 5 tablespoons water and mix.
Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Add egg mixture.
Line pie pan and bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 crusts.

title: cauliflower slaw
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Mix tuna, crumbs, onion and egg together.
Form into 4 patties. Preheat oil in skillet.
Add patties and brown on both sides. Serve on rolls.
Garnish with lettuce, tomatoes, onion slices, ketchup, relish, etc., as desired.

title: my grandmother's molasses cookies
directions: Cream together the sugar and shortening.
Break in the egg and beat vigorously. Add molasses, salt, cinnamon and ginger.
Beat well.
Add milk, then soda dissolved in the vinegar.
Add flour, using enough only to roll out well.
Cut into large cookies and bake in a moderate oven on a greased sheet about 12 minutes. These are rather soft and very good.
These proportions make
a rather large family batch.

title: zucchini-carrot cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Set aside. Combine carrots and next 3 ingredients to dry mixture.
Beat at high speed on electric mixer 4 minutes.
Pour into 9-inch greased square pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Check with toothpick. Cool.

title: miniature beef and onion cheesecakes
directions: Place the butter, flour, salt and pepper in the bowl of a food processor.
Pulse until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Pulse in the egg yolks, one at a time.
Add the yogurt, 2 tablespoons at a time, and pulse until mixture just comes together.
Carefully remove from the bowl and form into a flattened round disk.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for about an hour.

title: green chili casserole
directions: In a lightly greased baking dish or pan, spread half of the chilies on the bottom of dish (be sure to split chilies in half). Grate cheese and sprinkle half of cheese over chilies.
Cover cheese with the rest of the chilies, then cover with the rest of the cheese.
Mix together the milk, salt, mustard, pepper and eggs. Pour evenly over top of cheese.
Bake in oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until lightly brown on top at 350°.
Remove from oven and cut into squares.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Place beans in large saucepan and cover with water.
Heat and boil for 2 minutes, then remove the beans from heat and let soak for 1 hour.
Then add water, if necessary, to cover beans and simmer, uncovered, for about 50 minutes until tender.
Don't overcook them.
Reserve liquid.

title: creamy baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Put a slice of Swiss cheese on each.
Mix wine and cream of chicken soup together; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle Stove Top stuffing over top of chicken and pour butter on top of stuffing.
Cover dish and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
If you would like stuffing crispier, bake uncovered for a couple of minutes.

title: simple salad
directions: Place peach or pear half or one of each on lettuce leaf.
Add a small scoop of cottage cheese and top with cherry half or sprinkle with paprika.
If dressing is required, use a French dressing.

title: provencal marinade
directions: Pour over chicken and marinate at room temperature for 2 hours or in refrigerator 4 hours. Return chicken to room temperature before grilling.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; add peas and meat.
Mix cheese, milk, soup, onion and salt.
Simmer until cheese is melted.
Add to first 3 ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Serves 14 to 16.

title: baked beans
directions: Place beans in large casserole dish.
In frying pan, brown bacon and remove from drippings.
Brown onion.
To beans, add drippings, onion, sugar and syrup; mix well.
Spread bacon pieces over top of beans and bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and place in well-greased casserole dish.
Spread additional seasoned crumbs on top of mixture.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 35 to 40 minutes or until bubbly in center.

title: applesauce magic
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch dish with whole graham crackers.
Mix dry Jell-O and applesauce.
Spread layers of mixture over graham crackers.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Add more layers of ingredients. Top with Cool Whip and chopped nuts.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender and refrigerate overnight.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; beat well.
Add sugar gradually. Beat until light.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour 20 minutes in cold oven.
Do not preheat oven.
I use two large loaf pans, greased and floured.

title: jordan's cartwheel pinwheels
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ham slices, until well combined. Spread the cream cheese mixture on each ham slice and roll up. Slice each ham roll-up to 1/4 to 1/2-inch thickness.
Arrange on platter and serve.

title: scalloped potatoes parmesan
directions: Blend soup, milk, Parmesan and shredded cheese, Mrs. dash or other seasoning and Tabasco sauce.
In buttered 13 x 9-inch pan layer potatoes, onion and sauce.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake until brown and tender (approximately 20 minutes).

title: creamy icing
directions: Combine flour and milk over heat, stirring constantly, to make a paste.
Cool.
Beat together sugar and butter until smooth.
(In Hawaii, I put my mixing bowl into a bowl of ice to keep everything cool.)
Add the paste to the sugar and butter.
Add vanilla.
Beat until creamy like whipped cream.
This will frost one cake.

title: cobbs creek oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt margarine; add sugar and beaten egg and molasses.
Stir together dry ingredients and add to the rest.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet and press flat with back of spoon.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes, or until golden brown.
Yields 7 dozen cookies.

title: cool cracker dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on your favorite crackers.

title: my dad, corky's beef jerky
directions: Mix together.
Add meat; cut 1 x 1/4-inch.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 150° for 12 hours.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together.
Drain off any fat. Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce to simmer. Cook one hour or until chili is thick.
Makes 4 pints.

title: onion baked chicken strips
directions: Slice each chicken into 3 or 4 strips.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Roll each strip into dry ingredients to coat.
Drizzle a little Squeeze Parkay in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Lay strips in pan.
Sprinkle any remaining mix over chicken.
Drizzle squeeze Parkay lightly over chicken.
Bake uncovered for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Grind wafers into fine crumbs.
Mix in other ingredients.
Roll into logs.
Wrap in foil and store in refrigerator at least 48 hours before serving.
Slice to serve.
Makes a pretty tray for holidays.

title: cocoa muffins
directions: Mix all together, as for any muffin, and bake in a greased muffin tin that has been filled about 3/4 full of the batter. Bake at 400°
for 20 minutes.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Butter 8 x 12-inch baking pan.
Line bottom of pan with well drained sauerkraut.
Top with tomato slices, then dab with Thousand Island dressing and dot with margarine.
Place corned beef on top of the margarine and next, sprinkle Swiss cheese over meat and caraway seed.
Heat in 425° oven 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: carrot applesauce cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Set aside.
Beat eggs.
Stir in oil, sugar and vanilla. Add applesauce and carrots.
Mix well.
Add to flour mixture, stirring just enough to moisten.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° in a 13 x 9 greased pan for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Blend in soup and cheese. Put broccoli in colander and run hot water over to break apart. Add this and other ingredients to soup and cheese mixture.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until brown on top.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in bottom of pan.
Mix flour, sugar, and milk together; pour on top of melted butter.
Do not stir.
Butter will cover fruit.
Bake at 350 degree for 45 minutes to an hour or until crust is brown.

title: save-a-bundle trail mix(makes 6 cups)
directions: Mix all ingredients and store the mixture in an airtight container.
Make individual snack packs in plastic bags and store in airtight container.
Will keep 2 to 4 months on pantry shelf.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Mix all together, except crackers and margarine.
Sprinkle crackers on top.
Pour melted margarine over mixture.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Thaw and roll thin, one sheet of puff pastry.
Bake as directed, piercing with a fork.
Drizzle with heated, seedless raspberry jam.
Drizzle with melted chocolate using a cake decorator.
Arrange sliced fruit in a single layer.
May sprinkle with grated white chocolate (optional).
Cut into serving pieces.

title: quick ostkaka
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Turn into buttered casserole and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy fettucini
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart serving dish.
Pour butter over noodles; add Parmesan and toss gently.
Stir together sour cream and whipping cream; fold into noodles.
Garnish with parsley.
Serve immediately.

title: juicy meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly and pack firmly into a loaf pan. Bake in a moderate oven (350°) 1 hour. Let stand 5 minutes before slicing. Makes 8 servings.

title: norma's macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, add cottage cheese, sour cream, egg, salt, pepper and cheese; set aside.
Cook macaroni according to package.
Drain well and mix with ingredients in bowl.
Turn into a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hummus dip
directions: Blend together 15 seconds.
Scrape sides; add oil to smooth. Serve with veggies or pita bread.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: pistachio chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour half the mixture into greased Bundt pan.
With remaining mixture, add 3/4 cup chocolate syrup and pour over plain mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Mix sour cream and mayonnaise with taco seasoning mix.
Spread bean dip on large, flat plate or bowl.
Spread taco-flavored mix over bean dip.
Sprinkle on tomatoes, green onions and grated cheese.
Serve with chips.
Chill when not in use.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix biscuit mix, salt and corn meal. Add to melted butter and corn. Beat well and drop by spoonfuls in deep fat. When brown, serve with syrup and butter.

title: pasta and ceci (chickpeas)
directions: In medium size pot, pour in oil. Add onion and cook on medium heat until onion is transparent. Add ceci (rinse can with a little water and add to ceci) and cook on low gas for 30 minutes with lid on. Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain macaroni.
Reserve some liquid.
Put macaroni in bowl and add ceci.
Mix well. Add some of the macaroni liquid.
Serve. Garnish with macaroni, Parmesan cheese and/or crushed red pepper, if desired.

title: rhubarb pudding
directions: In a large bowl, cream together butter and sugar until the mixture is light and beat in egg.
Into a bowl, sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add the flour mixture to the butter mixture alternately with milk, beating well after each addition, to make a smooth batter.
Pour the batter into a buttered baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inch and spread it evenly with a metal spatula.
Scatter rhubarb over the batter and sprinkle with white or brown sugar and chopped walnuts or pecans over the mixture.
Bake the pudding in a 350° oven for 40 minutes or until it is browned.
Serve with warm Nutmeg Sauce.

title: carrot and raisin salad(easy)
directions: Mix carrots or raisins; sprinkle on ginger.
Mix mayo and orange or lemon marmalade.
Mix everything together.

title: zucchini bread with pineapple
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini; mix well.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Add nuts and pineapple. Bake in 2 large loaf pans, greased and floured, for 1 hour in a 325° oven.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil and sugar together.
Blend remaining ingredients into mixture.
Mix well.
Pour evenly into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes (ovens vary) at 325°.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix vinegar and sugar and bring to a boil; pour over kraut, onions, celery and green pepper.
Let stand in refrigerator for several hours.
Keeps a long time.

title: cold water chocolate cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Mix rest of ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 9 x 14-inch pan.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Defrost shrimp soup and add to softened cream cheese and add rest of ingredients.
Use hand mixer.
When serving, sprinkle paprika on top.
Shrimp can be cut up finer.

title: streusel coffee cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in butter.
Beat egg and milk.
Stir into above mixture.
Place half of cake batter into greased and floured 8X8 pan.
Sprinkle with half of topping mixture and then remaining batter and topping. Bake at 375 degrees for 25-30 minutes.
When doubling recipe, bake in 9X13 pan for 35-45 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix together thoroughly sugar, shortening and eggs.
Stir in sour milk and mashed bananas.
Sift together and stir in flour, baking powder and soda.
Blend in chopped nuts.
Pour into a well greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes before baking.
Bake until it tests done, usually 50 to 60 minutes in 350° oven.

title: tassies
directions: Blend or sift together softened cream cheese and margarine with flour. Shape into 1 inch balls; place in tiny muffin tins. Press dough against bottom and sides.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Bring to a boil and cook for almost 1 minute.
Then remove from heat, quickly adding the oats, butter and vanilla.
Drop on wax paper quickly by teaspoon.

title: curried shrimp in rice mold
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in 1/4 cup hot water.
Moisten curry powder with bouillon water.
Melt butter in a saucepan and stir in flour.
Mix well.
Stir in the milk with the curry mixture.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture reaches cream sauce consistency.
Pack the hot cooked rice into a greased ring mold and place mold in a pan of water to prevent sticking.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Add the raw, peeled and deveined shrimp to the hot cream sauce and cook until shrimp are pink and done.
Unmold rice ring on heated platter.
Pour curried shrimp into center of ring.
Decorate with parsley.
Serve hot.

title: icebox cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream the butter and brown sugar.
Add egg and vanilla. Beat well. Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Stir in nuts, if desired.
On a lightly floured surface, shape the dough into three 10 x 1-inch rolls. Tightly wrap each roll in wax paper.
Freeze for at least 12 hours. Cut into 3/8-inch slices and place on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Remove to wire rack and cool. Makes about 7 dozen.

title: biscuit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan; set aside.
Mix sugars and put in separate bowl.
Dip biscuits in melted butter, then in sugar mixture, then in nuts.
Arrange around Bundt pan until full.
When complete, bake for 10 to 15 minutes until biscuits look done.
Remove from oven.
Let stand for approximately 10 minutes before turning over onto plate.
Use remaining butter and pecans as topping.

title: fruit medley punch
directions: Prepare ice ring in advance, if desired.
In blender container, puree strawberries.
In large punch bowl, combine pureed strawberries and remaining ingredients, except ginger ale. Stir until sugar dissolves.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and ice ring.
Makes 3 1/2 quarts.

title: betty's chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and cook in heavy saucepan, stirring constantly.
Place in baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: pickle sandwiches
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Trim crusts from bread slices.
Spread mix over bread and roll around pickle slices. Chill 2 hours or more.
Cut into bite size pieces.

title: freezer raspberry sauce
directions: Combine the mashed berries, sugar and corn syrup; stir until well mixed.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
In small bowl, combine liquid pectin and lemon juice.
Stir into fruit mixture; mix for 3 minutes.
Add remaining whole berries, stirring carefully to distribute fruit, but leave berries whole.
Ladle into 1 pint or smaller freezer containers; seal and let stand at room temperature for 24 hours.
Store in refrigerator up to 3 weeks or in the freezer for up to 1 year.
Thaw and stir before using.
Can serve over ice cream, sponge cake, shortcake or waffles.
Makes 4 pints.

title: butterless fudge
directions: Cook to soft ball stage, stirring occasionally.
Cool to lukewarm; add vanilla, few grains salt (optional nuts or peanut butter).
Beat well until thick and creamy.
Spread into buttered pan.
Cool.
Cut in squares.

title: cornstarch clay
directions: Put the salt and 2/3 cup of water into a pot and bring to a boil.
Mix the cornstarch with the remaining water.
Stir well. Blend these two mixtures together and knead into clay.
Mold into shapes and let dry several hours.
They can be painted when dry. Store the clay in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: easy ambrosia salad
directions: Drain fruit well.
Mix with coconut, marshmallows and sour cream.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chili con carne
directions: In skillet, cook meat, onion and green pepper until meat is lightly browned and vegetables are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: french-toasted chicken-and-cheese sandwiches
directions: Salt and pepper the beef to taste and form into a ball.
Put on a platter.
Surround the ball with sliced onions and serve with rye bread.
Have salt and pepper shakers handy.

title: henry's clam dip(double for a crowd)
directions: Mix all together in blender.

title: veal scallopine
directions: Mix flour, paprika and salt and pepper together.
Coat meat with mixture.
Brown floured meat and onion in oil.
Add undrained mushrooms and tomatoes.
Add seasonings, garlic, carrots and peppers.
Cook until done (20 to 30 minutes).
Serve over buttered noodles.

title: fried rice
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic until meat is tender; add rice and simmer.
Add soy sauce; stir and add scrambled eggs.
Add vegetables; cook until desired crispness.
Keep stirring to keep from sticking.
Add a little if needed.

title: mini ham puffs
directions: Roll each rectangle out, closing the perforations on the triangles.
Cut each rectangle into 6 squares.
Put each square in a muffin pan.
Repeat with rest of dough.
Mix filling together and place on top of each square.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: kool orange delight
directions: Mix cottage cheese with dry orange jello.
Add drained mandarin oranges and Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: decorator frosting
directions: With electric mixer at medium speed, cream together Crisco and confectioners sugar.
Add water or milk and vanilla.
Scrape bowl and beaters during mixing.
Continue beating until completely blended.
Add coloring, if desired.
Yields 3 1/4 cups.

title: chocolate covered cherry cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together. Add egg and vanilla; mix well. Combine flour, cocoa, salt, baking powder and baking soda; add to above mixture and mix well. Shape cookie dough into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Press down in center of each cookie with your thumb. Drain cherries, reserving cherry juice. Place a cherry in the thumb indention of each cookie. Melt chocolate chips and sweetened condensed milk over low heat. When chocolate chips are melted add 4 tsp. of cherry juice and stir well. Frost each uncooked cookie with approximately 1 tablespoon of frosting. Bake at 350 degrees for about 10 minutes.

title: chicken party ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well by hand.
Shape into ball.
Roll in pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Place chicken into broth.
Cook 20 minutes.
Once broth is hot.
Celery and onion chunks are cut into broth while cooking. After chicken is done, add cream of mushroom soup.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place vegetables in 2-quart casserole. Combine dry ingredients, mixing well. Spoon over vegetables.
Mix soup and water.
Pour over vegetables and dry mixture.
Bake at 325° if in glass dish or 350° in metal pan for 40 minutes.
Stir gently twice. Top with cracker crumbs the last 20 minutes of cooking time.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in buttered 10 x 6 x 2-inch pan.
Add water, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
Mix together sugar, flour and butter until crumbly.
Spread mixture over apples.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes 6 servings.

title: yule cake
directions: Sift sugar, flour, baking powder and salt over fruit and nuts; coat well.
Beat eggs until light.
Add vanilla.
Blend into fruit and nuts.
Batter will be stiff.
Spoon into paper lined pans. Bake at 300° for approximately 1 3/4 hours.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Turn out.

title: traveling cupcakes
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine in saucepan.
Add nuts and stir. Combine sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla.
Do not beat.
Put in muffin or cupcake foils.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen small cupcakes.

title: tasty chicken soup
directions: Cook leg quarters in 4 quarts water until tender; remove meat from bones and chop.
Add water to make 3 quarts.
Heat butter and add 1 cup flour.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir onions, carrots and celery into the roux and cook 10 minutes.
Add chicken broth, chicken pieces and 1 cup long grain rice (uncooked), salt and pepper and bring to boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Add half and half and heat.
Yield:
4 1/2 quarts.
This freezes well before adding half and half.

title: fruit ball
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, powdered sugar and lemon juice. Add other ingredients.
Mix well and shape into a ball.
Chill overnight and roll in chopped pecans.
Serve with crisp crackers.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Season to your taste.
Shape in ball. Roll in chopped nuts.

title: chocolate pies
directions: Beat cream cheese, chocolate syrup and Eagle Brand milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crumb crusts.
Freeze until firm.

title: cracker barrel fried apples
directions: Combine apple juice and apples in a medium skillet.
Simmer gently and turn apples often with spatula until fork-tender but not mushy.
Remove with slotted spoon to oven dish.
In blender, put 1/2 cup apple juice, cornstarch, spice and sugar.
Blend a few seconds until smooth.
Stir into hot juice in skillet and cook, stirring constantly, on medium-high until it bubbles and becomes thickened and smooth.
Turn heat off. Pour over apples.
Serve warm as side dish or dessert.

title: fried bananas
directions: Combine salt, cream and egg.
Peel and cut bananas in fourths. Roll them in egg mixture and then corn flakes.
Fry in deep fat until golden brown.
Serves four.

title: scottish oat cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix and set aside water and soda to cool; mix all dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Finally add soda mixture.
Divide dough into thirds.
Pat out on thinly-floured surface into a rectangular shape.
Roll to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into 2 x 3-inch rectangles, trimming edges.
With spatula, set on cookie sheet.
They spread.
Barely brown the edges, no more than 8 minutes.
They will still be light in color.
Remove from pan immediately.
They crisp up as they cool.
Cookie sheet must be washed and cooled between batches or use 3 cookie sheets.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: peanut-rice crispy
directions: Combine everything except cereal.
Make balls.
Roll in toasted coconut, if desired, or stuff into dates and top with walnuts.

title: instant spice tea
directions: Mix and heat and drink!

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and press in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: snowballs
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine chocolate and evaporated milk. Stir over low heat until chocolate melts.
Remove from heat.
Stir in confectioners sugar and nuts.
Chill a few hours.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in coconut.
Makes 30 balls.

title: delicious no-sugar apple pie
directions: Place apple juice in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Combine oleo, cornstarch and spices in a small bowl.
Add small amount of apple juice; stir until well blended.
Stir cornstarch mixture into apple juice.
Pour over apples.
Bake at 425° for about 30 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° for 30 minutes longer.
This is a pie diabetics can eat.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into a ball.
Chill in refrigerator overnight for best flavor.

title: tossed orange salad
directions: Place orange rind, juice, corn oil, vinegar and salt in small jar with tight-fitting lid.
Cover and shake well.
Refrigerate dressing several hours.
Toss together romaine, zucchini, oranges and onion in large bowl.
Just before serving, pour dressing over salad and toss to coat evenly.

title: vegetable stuffing(diabetic)
directions: Saute onions, mushrooms and celery in oil.
Steam carrots and cauliflower until tender.
Mash all vegetables or puree in blender.
Add poultry seasoning.
Stuff in bird and cook immediately, or cook in casserole at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. (For a 10 to 12 pound turkey, double the recipe.)
Yields 6 servings.
Calories per serving:

title: six layer dinner
directions: Salt and pepper each layer to taste.
Bake in slow oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Keep cover on.

title: traditional white bread
directions: Mix water, salt, sugar, softened margarine and flour, then dry milk.
Add active yeast.
Heat oven to 350°.

title: carrot dip for broccoli
directions: Combine cottage cheese and mayonnaise in blender container. Process at high speed until smooth.
Mix with remaining ingredients in bowl. Chill. Serve with broccoli flowerets for dipping.
Yields 48 tablespoons.

title: cranberry salad
directions: In food processor, grind cranberries.
Add sugar and set aside.
In large bowl, dissolve jello with hot water.
Add pineapple, pecans and celery.
Grind orange (peel and all) and add to mixture. Add cranberries.
Mix and chill overnight.
Great for the holidays.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients using 1/4 cup of the bacon drippings. Heat remaining 1/4 cup bacon drippings in square 9-inch baking pan. Add batter. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes. May take longer if altitude is high.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour with fork.
Add egg and melted butter; blend together.
Add nuts, chips and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: glass candy
directions: Bring ingredients to boil; boil to hard ball stage (when drop of syrup dropped in cold water turns to brittle).
Remove from heat and add desired food coloring and 1 small jar of flavor oil.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Place uncooked rice in bottom of pan. Pour French onion soup and 1 can water over rice.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper. Place chicken on rice.
Spread cream of celery soup over chicken. Bake, uncovered, in preheated 300° to 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add water as necessary.

title: boiled shrimp
directions: In large pot, mix water, onion, garlic, celery, bay leaf and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Add shrimp and simmer for 15 minutes. Add lemon.
Let boil for a few minutes longer.
Let them cool in the water that they were cooked in.
Drain and chill them.
Serve them cold.

title: oh so good sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, white sugar, powdered sugar and eggs in a large bowl.
Add vanilla and cream again for three minutes.

title: light and luscious strawberry pie
directions: Layer strawberries in a pie plate.
Mix jello with 1 cup hot water.
Allow to set for 30 minutes.
Mix pudding with 1 cup cold water.
Add to jello mixture.
Pour over strawberries.
Chill to set.

title: apple spice cake
directions: Grease and lightly flour a 9-inch tube pan.
Stir together the dry ingredients, except sugar.
Peel, core and finely chop the apples.
In a large mixer bowl, stir together the eggs and vanilla.
Beat on high speed with mixer for 2 minutes.
Gradually add oil, beating for 2 minutes.
Gradually beat in the sugar. Add dry ingredients, apples and walnuts alternately, beating well after each addition.
Beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool thoroughly.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Form a ball and roll in paprika.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and flavoring and beat well. Add potato chips.
Sift flour and soda.
Stir in creamed mix. Drop on cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: vegetarian pizza
directions: Spread sauce on crust, pile high with veggies.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.
275 calories; fat, 4 gms.
13% fat.
This is good for dieters.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vinegar, and cook until thick. Add vinegar and cook 5 minutes longer.
Pour into warm jars.
Put into hot water bath for 15 minutes.

title: crazy cake
directions: Combine all ingredients (except coconut and nuts).
Cook in saucepan until forms soft ball in water.
Remove from heat; add coconut and ice cake.

title: bread pudding
directions: Cover the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan with bread cubes, possibly two layers.
Pour over this the remaining ingredients; sprinkle a dash of cinnamon on top.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350° or until set.

title: turkey mini meatballs
directions: Mix together all ingredients and form into small, bite size balls.
Place meatballs on top of broiler pan so any fat will drip away.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes or until brown. Meanwhile, prepare the following sauce.

title: spinach and artichoke casserole
directions: Soften the cream cheese and mix in the chopped artichokes, melted margarine, onion and cooked spinach.
Place in a well-greased casserole.
Sprinkle with bread or cracker crumbs and dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs until whipped; add sugar and flour.
Add pumpkin and milk.
Add all spices and mix well.
Makes 2 pies.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cook at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Add soup, Cheez Whiz and milk.
Cook until cheese melts.
Add broccoli.
In casserole dish put rice; add other ingredients and put in oven.
Preheat oven to 325° and cook for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: orange delight
directions: Dissolve orange Jell-O in 1 cup hot water.
Add vanilla ice cream, pineapple, oranges, bananas and cherries.
Mix together and chill.

title: 1, 2, 3, 4 cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two 9-inch cake pans.
Sift flour.
Add baking powder and salt.
Beat butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture to butter mixture; slowly add milk, mixing gently.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in glass baking dish for 45 minutes in 325° oven.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute onions in a small amount of olive oil.
Add garlic. Brown ground beef, sausage and mushrooms.
Cool mixture.
Mix the 2 beaten eggs into the mixture.
Add salt and pepper.
Toss cheeses together; set aside.

title: poppy seed tea ring
directions: Early in day, in 1-quart saucepan over low, heat butter or margarine and 2/3 cup water until very warm (120° to 130°).
In a large bowl with mixer at low speed, beat yeast, salt, 1 cup flour, 1/3 cup sugar and liquid ingredients until blended.
At medium speed, beat 2 minutes.
Stir in 1 cup flour.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Cream margarine and powdered sugar until fluffy in medium size bowl; stir in flour gradually, then pecans until well blended. Chill several hours, or until firm enough to handle.
Roll dough, a teaspoon at a time into marble size balls between palms of hands; place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until brown.
Cool for 5 minutes, remove carefully.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm to make a generous white coating.
Cool completely on wire racks.
Store with waxed paper between layers in container with tight fitting cover.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: zucchini with dill
directions: In a large skillet, saute zucchini in butter until crisp tender. Stir in flour. Add water, lemon juice, sugar and salt if desired; bring to a boil. Cook and stir for 2 minutes. Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes. Remove from the heat; stir in sour cream and dill. This has 15 grams carbohydrate.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Melt butter; stir in milk and sugar.
Bring to full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil over medium heat until mixture reaches 234° or soft ball stage, still stirring constantly. Remove from heat at soft ball stage and stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme and nuts until well blended. Pour into greased (buttered) 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature; cut into squares.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: toffee squares
directions: In a mixing bowl cream together butter and brown sugar.
Add egg yolk and vanilla; gradually add flour until blended.
(Dough will be thick.)
Spread evenly on ungreased 16 x 14 x 1-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until crust is brown and puffy. Remove from oven.
Arrange unwrapped chocolate bars evenly over surface of crust; let stand 5 minutes to soften.
Spread chocolate evenly over crust; sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Cool and cut into squares.
Yields 40 squares.

title: special potato soup
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter in a large Dutch oven until tender.
Add next 9 ingredients.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: broccoli-chicken-cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Put in dish; top with chicken.
In saucepan, melt butter; add flour and salt.
Stir until smooth and bubbly. Stir in bouillon and cook until thick.
Remove from heat and stir in 1 cup cheese and Worcestershire sauce until melted.
Pour this over broccoli and chicken.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly and pack firmly into a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix margarine and shortening together until smooth.
Mix in sugar and egg.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Fold in 1 1/4 cup blueberries.
Fold into the first mixture with the milk.
Transfer to oiled muffin tins.
Top each muffin with 1 teaspoon of the remaining blueberries.
Bake for 25 minutes at 425°.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Mix and season with garlic salt.
Place in covered container and refrigerate 12 hours.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix meat, soup mix, egg and bread crumbs. Form into bite size meatballs.
Brown in margarine or butter. Cool, cover and refrigerate.

title: linguine tuna salad
directions: Cook and drain linguine.
In a large bowl, combine ReaLemon, oil, onions and seasonings.
Mix well.
Add hot linguine and toss. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: ham and potato breakfast casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except paprika in a large bowl.
Pour in ungreased rectangular baking dish, 12 x 7 x 2-inch. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, until inserted knife comes out clean, 40 to 45 minutes.

title: saucy meatballs
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Shape into 20 meatballs (using a round tablespoon).
Brown well in shortening.
Drain off excess fat.
Sprinkle flour over meatballs.
Stir gently to combined tomatoes, 57 sauce, sugar and salt.
Pour over meatballs.
Simmer uncovered 25 minutes or until sauce is desired consistency.
Serve over hot buttered noodles.

title: fat free angel food cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on package.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake according to directions on package.
When done, cut holes in cake, prepare jello as stated on package and pour over cake.
Refrigerate until cool.
Mix package of Dream Whip with skim milk until thick and spread onto cooled cake. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: indian corn
directions: Peel onions and slice.
Fry in butter until partly tender. (Some green pepper, cut in small pieces, may be added, if desired.) Remove onions and put in hamburg.
Cook, stirring with a fork, until crumbly.
Season with a scant 1/2 teaspoon salt, pepper and a few grains of garlic salt.
Return onions to hamburg.
Add corn with liquid and mushroom soup diluted with 1/3 can cold water, mix well.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie shell and bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool and top with whipped cream or ice cream.
Can be served without topping.

title: angel food cake
directions: Beat egg whites in a large mixing bowl at high speed with an electric mixer until foamy.
Add cream of tartar and salt; beat until soft peaks form.
Add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating until stiff peaks form and sugar dissolves.
Sprinkle flour over egg white mixture, 1/4 cup at a time, folding in after each addition.
Fold in vanilla.
Pour batter into an ungreased 10-inch tube pan, spreading batter evenly in pan.
Cut through batter with knife to remove air bubbles.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes. Invert tube pan until cool.

title: john hoosier chocolate cake
directions: Melt oleo or margarine, cocoa and water; bring to a boil. Pour over dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: homemade bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, soda and salt together in a bowl.
Mix in cornmeal and whole wheat flour.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing only until all flour is moistened.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until golden brown.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Spread pineapple in bottom of dish (don't drain).
Put berries over pineapple.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup sugar over berries.
Spread dry cake mix over next, then pour melted butter over cake mix.
Pour pecans over butter and the remaining 1/4 cup of sugar over pecans. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese bread
directions: Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl, combine 2 1/2 cups flour, sugar, garlic salt and yeast.
In large saucepan, heat water, oil and cheese until very warm.
Add warm liquid and egg to flour mixture.
Blend at low speed until moistened.
By hand, stir in 3 to 4 cups flour until dough pulls cleanly away from sides of bowl.
On floured surface, knead in 1/2 to 1 1/2 cups flour until dough is smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
Place dough in greased bowl; cover loosely with plastic wrap and cloth towel.
Let rise in warm place until doubled in size, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch dough down.
Let rest on counter, covered with inverted bowl.
Shape dough according to variation desired.

title: company potatoes
directions: Boil together water and milk; add potatoes and beaten egg. Stir and add lid; let sit.
Whip.
Add sour cream and spices.
Put in an 11 x 8-inch greased (with butter) dish.
Add grated cheese. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Note:
You can use leftover potatoes instead of instant.

title: chicken and rice casserole(club member: lee higginbotham)
directions: Cook chicken until tender; remove bones. Combine soups, rice and chicken. Pour into casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Place sweet potatoes in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Combine eggs, margarine, half and half, sugar, vanilla and a dash of salt.
Pour this mixture over the top of potatoes.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 12 or more.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix together and fry patties until brown.

title: stew(lapskaus)
directions: Place meat, onions and barley in kettle.
Cover with water and simmer until tender.
When meat is almost done, add the potatoes. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: potato croquettes
directions: Add milk, salt, pepper, onion, butter and egg yolks to mashed potatoes. Mix well; chill and form into balls about 2-inches in diameter. Roll in crumbs, then in egg and water, beaten together; then again in crumbs. Fry a few at a time in deep fat until golden brown. Makes 14.

title: date nut roll
directions: Melt marshmallows in cherry juice.
Pour over fruit and 2/3 of crumbs.
Stir together.
Form into 3 logs.
Roll logs into remaining crumbs.
Lift from crumbs and wrap in foil.
Place in plastic bag and refrigerate.
Keeps for months.

title: chocolate crisps
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Line 11 x 15-inch pan with parchment paper. Score graham crackers and place on parchment paper. In a saucepan, melt the oleo and butter. Then add the sugar. Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute. Pour over graham crackers and bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes. Remove from oven and top with chocolate melts or chocolate chips. Spread evenly over all. Cool. Break at seams.

title: punch
directions: Mix juices.
Add sugar.
Add enough Kool-Aid to color the color you like.

title: orange pineapple jello
directions: Blend together pineapple, juice and jello.
Bring to a boil; cool.
Add Cool Whip and buttermilk.
Chill and eat.

title: slaw
directions: Shred cabbage (medium size) alternating it with thinly sliced onions.
Top with 7/8 cup sugar.
Bring remaining ingredients to boiling point.
Pour over cabbage while still hot.
Let stand 4 to 6 hours, then mix and serve.
It is even better after 2 or 3 days. It will keep for 2 or 3 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream margarine and brown sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Combine the 3 1/2 cups flour, soda and spices; add to the creamed mixture alternately with the 1 cup whiskey.
Cut up the fruit (cherries and pineapple) and dredge the extra cup of flour with all the fruits and pecans.
Add fruit and nut mixture to the batter.
Bake at 300° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: crusty curried fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Wash chicken.
Pat dry.
In oven, melt shortening and butter in baking pan.
Mix Bisquick, curry powder, salt and pepper.
Coat chicken pieces thoroughly with flour mix. Place chicken (skin down) in melted shortening.
Cook uncovered for 30 minutes. Turn chicken; cook 30 minutes longer or until pieces are fork-tender.
Serve hot.

title: biscuit pudding
directions: Crumble biscuits in mixing bowl and pour milk over crumbs and let stand 30 minutes.
Add softened margarine, sugar and eggs and mix well.
Add vanilla and mix.
Stir in raisins.
Spray a 9 x 12-inch loaf pan with Pam.
Pour biscuit mixture in and bake at 400° for approximately 30 minutes until brown.

title: oatmeal candy
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together in large pot.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Pour in a large pan and chill.
Cut and serve.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa well.
Add milk and bring to a boil.
Turn heat to low and let simmer until it forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water. Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Add butter or margarine and vanilla.
Beat until thick.
Pour in buttered pan. Let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: mrs. myrtle duncan's coca-cola cake
directions: Mix together flour, eggs, sugar and buttermilk.
Boil oleo, Coke, cocoa and vanilla.
Add the Coke mixture to the flour mixture.
Add marshmallows, salt and soda.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: delicious meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into loaf.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Fifteen minutes before removing from oven, spread this mixture over top:

title: too easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Place fruit in 8 x 8 baking dish.
Cut crust from bread and cut slices into five fingers. Place bread fingers over the fruit. In a bowl, mix sugar, flour, egg, and butter.
Pour over fruit and bread.
Bake 35-45 minutes until golden brown.
Serves 5-6.
Enjoy!

title: multi-grain bread
directions: Soak multi-grain cereal in 2 cups hot water until cooled to warm.
Mix water, milk, yeast, honey, grain, cereal, bran and 6 cups flour to make sponge.
Let sit 1 hour.

title: quick and easy homemade pizza
directions: Combine all ingredients, form
a
ball	and knead until smooth.
Press into pizza pan.
Spread dough with tomato paste or sauce.
Add browned hamburger
meat
or
any other meat you might prefer; add whatever spices you like best to taste.
Top with shredded
Mozzarella
cheese
or shredded Cheddar cheese. Bake at 425° until cheese is melted and crust is golden brown.

title: caribbean lemon chicken
directions: Place chicken quarters in large plastic bag.
Combine teriyaki sauce, lemon peel and juice, pepper sauce and cinnamon.
Pour into bag over chicken.
Press air out of bag and tie top securely.
Turn over several times to coat chicken.
Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight, turning bag over occasionally.

title: snowballs
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; blend well.
Stir in flour and chocolate pieces.
Form 1-inch balls and roll in chopped pecans. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar while warm or for holiday roll in red or green tinted sugar.
Yield:
5 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate peanut butter bars
directions: In mixing bowl, mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar, melted margarine and peanut butter.
Spread on cookie sheet.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Melt oleo; add to sugar and flour.
Mix until moistened.
Add nuts and press in bottom of pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for about 10 to 15 minutes or until light golden.
Let cool.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in deep 10-inch glass pie plate or 7 x 11-inch rectangular baking dish.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add milk and stir well.
Pour mixture into baking dish.
Do not stir.
Top with peaches.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Pour juice into small pot.
Bring to a boil.
Mix about 2 tablespoons cornstarch with a little water until smooth.
Pour into hot juice and stir until slightly thickened.
Pour over top cobbler and serve.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli flowerets into smaller than bite size pieces. Cut off the tough outer layer of the stalks and chop the tender part into small pieces.
You will need about 8 cups broccoli. (This can be done the day before and stored in plastic bag.)
In a small skillet, saute the bacon until crisp and set aside.
Slice onion lengthwise, then cut into julienne strips.
In a large bowl, combine the broccoli, onion strips, raisins and bacon.
In a small bowl, whisk together the mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar and pepper. Combine dressing with the veggies and refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving. Mix once during this time.
Top with sunflower seeds.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: potato-cheese casserole(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Grease 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Gently mix all ingredients together and place in bowl.
Top with one cup of corn flake crumbs, bread crumbs or crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until potatoes are soft.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Cut top off of bread and scoop out center of bread, leaving a bowl shape.
Combine all ingredients and chill.
When ready to serve, put mixture into bread bowl.
Break up the top of the loaf and pieces taken out of the middle and use as dippers.

title: emily's pecan crunch
directions: Combine butter, sugar, water, salt and vinegar.
Beat with strong spoon or mixer.
Bring slowly to boil, stirring occasionally.
Boil to 290°.
Cook slowly, without stirring, until very brittle when dropped in cold water.
Mix soda with pecan crumbs.
Add with pecan meats to boiled mix.
Stir only enough to blend.
Pour 1/8-inch thick into buttered pan.
Cover top with thin layer of melted chocolate.
Don't swirl with spoon.
Break with wooden spoon.
Leave in pan.
Store in airtight container. Do not refrigerate.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in double boiler over water and cook until thickens.
Stir at all times.
Remove from heat and let cool. Make a layer of vanilla wafers and bananas (sliced) until all mix is gone.
End with wafer crumbs on top.
You can put meringue on top if you like.

title: blueberry fluff
directions: Mix well the walnuts, butter or margarine and flour.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: parmesan delights
directions: Combine mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese, Worcestershire sauce, onion salt, garlic powder and sherry.
Mound on Ritz crackers. Sprinkle with more Parmesan cheese.
Broil 4 to 5 inches from heat until lightly browned.
Makes 24 canapes.
Delicious!

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl until smooth and even.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cinnamon applesauce salad
directions: Dissolve candy in boiling water.
Add jello and stir to dissolve.
Stir in applesauce.
Chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Pour in 10 x 7-inch pan.
Combine cream cheese and salad dressing.
Spoon on top of jello mixture and swirl to make a marble effect.
Chill until firm.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: buttermilk cookies
directions: Beat
eggs;
add
sugar and shortening.
Mix well, then add milk,
baking
soda,
baking powder and flour.
Mix well. Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
When
cookies are cool, frost with your favorite frosting.

title: granny's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 15 minutes in 425° oven, then for 40 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: the doctor's meat patties
directions: Select the desired amount of ground meats.
Add one or more eggs and a spoonful or two of peanut butter.
Add onion salt and garlic powder.
A small amount of catsup may be added if desired. Make into patties and place in the broiler section of the oven. Cook under the flame until done and browned on both sides.
Juices will seep out and make a hell of a gravy for mashed potatoes.

title: starter for amish cinnamon bread
directions: Day 1:
Either receive starter from a friend or start your own from ingredients listed.

title: chicken and tortilla casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Heat tortillas in oven until crisp. Combine tomatoes, yogurt, chiles, chili powder, garlic and onion. Layer half of toasted tortillas in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole pan that has been sprayed with nonstick spray.
Cover with a layer of sauce, chicken and cheese.
Alternate layers, ending with cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: fudge
directions: Use a large heavy stew pot, combine sugar and milk; mix well, using medium heat, bring mixture to a full rolling boil (continue to boil 11 to 12 minutes).
Do not stir.
Occasionally scrape down crystals that form on side of pan.
While sugar and milk mixture is boiling, combine chocolate chips, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla in medium size bowl.
When mixture has boiled 11 or 12 minutes, turn off heat; add softened butter, chocolate chips and Marshmallow Creme.
Stir until chips are dissolved.
Beat with electric mixer until medium thick.
Pour into greased cooking sheet, or cake pan (size about 11 x 17 x 4-inch deep).
Makes about 5 pounds.

title: chicken and stuffing
directions: Place chicken breasts in large baking pan or dish.
Add chicken soup and 2 cans of water.
Mix well and pour over chicken.

title: herb chicken with rice
directions: Mix salt, poultry seasoning, pepper, rosemary, onion salt and paprika in a paper bag.
Coat the chicken breasts with the mixture. Place rice in a casserole dish and add broth.
Place chicken breasts on top of rice and cover.
Place in oven and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter and jelly "fish" sandwiches
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Cut each slice of bread with a fish shaped cookie cutter.
Spread peanut butter mixture on half of fish shaped pieces of bread.
Top with remaining bread.
Make tiny slits on each piece of bread and insert currants for eyes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Beat the egg whites until stiff.
Mix egg yolks and other ingredients, except egg whites.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in a Bundt or tube pan for about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: little smokies
directions: Blend apple jelly and mustard until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into large skillet; bring to rolling boil.
Add all Little Smokies cocktail sausages.
Cook for 35 minutes, or until mixture has cooked to thick syrup on medium heat.
Stir often.
Serve cold on toothpicks.

title: ants on a log
directions: Clean celery.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Fill with cream cheese or peanut butter.
Sprinkle with raisins.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Mix with other ingredients.
Can be microwaved for 20 minutes, baked for 1 hour at 350° or cooked over barbecue grill until hot and bubbly.

title: jello cups
directions: Prepare Jell-O according to the directions on the box and pour into individual cups.
Add sliced bananas.
Refrigerate Jell-O until jelled.
Top with whipped cream and sprinkles and serve.

title: one bowl brownies
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate in pan.
(This can be done in microwave.)
Add all other ingredients.
Stir until well blended. Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: garlic cheese for stuffed celery
directions: Mix all together.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Stuff celery next day.

title: washington cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars together in a large bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to the mixture.
Stir in nut pieces, oatmeal and chocolate bits.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate cake(recipe in family for 65 years)
directions: Cream shortening with the mixture of sugar and cocoa.
Add and mix the unbeaten egg yolks.
Add the hot water into all; stir until smooth.
Sift the dry ingredients and add to the batter, then add the sour milk.
Fold in beaten egg whites last.
Bake in 350° oven.
Can be layer or sheet cake.

title: frozen orange delight
directions: Boil 2 cups water in microwave.
Add 1 cup sugar.
Pour water and sugar over other ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cool in fridge for 3 to 4 hours.
Freeze overnight.

title: dirty rice
directions: Mix in baking dish, cover with foil.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: arroz con jocoqui(rice and sour cream casserole)
directions: Cut Jack cheese in strips.
Thoroughly mix sour cream and chiles.
Butter (or spray) a 1 1/2-quart casserole well.
Season rice with salt and pepper, if necessary.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer ingredients in order given.
Use large glass oblong pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Top should be brown. I omit nuts and coconut.

title: buttermilk pie cake
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Combine cake mix and 2 eggs.
Pat into pan.
Blend cream cheese and 2 eggs.
Add powdered sugar and pour over cake.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sale creek strawberry pie
directions: Bring to a boil and strain 1 cup smaller strawberries, sugar and boiling water.
Now add cornstarch mixture.
Cook over the fire for a couple of minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from fire and beat.
Return to slow fire and cook slowly until thick. Have ready a baked pie shell.
Arrange the rest of the berries, which have been washed and picked over, in the shell.
Pour the hot sauce over them.
When cool, spread with whipped cream that has been sweetened with powdered sugar over the top.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Spread hamburger on bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Put frozen peas or French-style beans over top and cover with can of cream of mushroom soup.
Lay cheese over top and cover with Tater Tots.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cooked chicken is good in place of hamburger or turkey.

title: spritz cookie(this one is excellent)
directions: Mix butter, egg and sugar with beater (mix well together). Add almond extract and flour and mix well. Use cookie press, do not let dough harden. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 100 cookies.

title: brownies delectable
directions: Cream butter thoroughly.
Add sugar and mix completely.
Add vanilla.
Blend in eggs.
Set aside.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt together.
Sift dry ingredients into creamed mixture.
Mix well. Add chopped nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: sunshine carrots
directions: Bias cut carrots 1/2-inch thick.
Cook.
In a small pan, combine sugar, cornstarch, ginger and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Add orange juice.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and bubbly. Boil 1 minute. Stir in butter.
Pour over hot carrots. Toss to coat evenly. Garnish with parsley and orange twist.

title: copper pennies
directions: Slice carrots 1/4 inch thick.
Cut pepper into strips or chop. Also chop onion.
Cook carrots about 15 minutes in salted water; drain.
Then add green pepper and onion.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over carrots.
Let stand 2 hours.

title: mexican style salad
directions: Shred lettuce and dice tomatoes as making regular salad. Grate cheese on top of salad.
Pour corn chips on top of salad. Heat Ranch Style beans and brown hamburger meat.
Now pour hamburger meat on top of salad, then add Ranch Style beans, then add 1/2 cup medium picante sauce; stir, then serve.

title: never fail pie dough(this really does live up to its name.)
directions: Blend together flour, shortening and salt. Beat egg with fork until thoroughly mixed. Add vinegar and water. Mix and add to flour mixture all at once. Let stand a few minutes to absorb all the liquids. Finish as usual.

title: cocoa dump cake
directions: In a large saucepan, bring margarine, cocoa and water to a boil.
Add sugar, flour, cinnamon and eggs, blending thoroughly. Add buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Blend.
Pour batter (it will be thin) into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
While still warm, frost.

title: granny's canned tomatoes
directions: Let boil until foam rises.
Remove foam and can.

title: marinated tomatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: gazpacho (andalusian soup)
directions: In a blender, combine all vegetables (except chives, and garlic) portions at a time, with tomato juice until finely chopped.
Do not puree.
Mix in large bowl with spices, oil and vinegar, except save enough oil to saute croutons in skillet rubbed with garlic.

title: microwave 5-minute blueberry pie
directions: In medium bowl, combine sugar, cornstarch, and 1/2 cup water. Cook on High for 2 minutes, or until mixture boils 1 minute; mixture should be thick; stir.
Stir in blueberries; cook on high for 3 minutes, stirring once.
Pour into crust.
Makes 8 servings.

title: broccoli rabe souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs with Romano cheese.
Combine broccoli with ham, Mozzarella and eggs.
Season to taste.
Butter a 1 1/2 qt. casserole or souffle dish, pour mixture into dish.
Bake uncovered 25 - 30 minutes or until set.
Serves 6 - 8.

title: heavenly hash candy
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in a glass bowl and microwave on high 3 minutes stirring occasionally.
Remove and stir until creamy.
Add pecans and marshmallows and stir until well mixed. Spread in 9x13 greased pan and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Remove and cut into squares.

title: lazy day lasagne
directions: Cook
noodles in boiling salted water following package directions.
Drain.

title: overnight vegetable salad
directions: Combine vegetables in a bowl; set aside.

title: lasagna
directions: Season meat with salt, pepper and onion.
Cook until brown and drain.
Combine all other ingredients and blend in meat mixture. Grease casserole dish or 9 1/2 x 11-inch pan.
Put a layer of sauce, then noodles.
Repeat until gone.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Freezes well.

title: chipped beef ball
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Chop chipped beef in small pieces and mix into cream cheese along with mustard, mayonnaise and onion.
Shape into ball and chill.

title: raspberry whip
directions: Dissolve jello in water; add frozen raspberries.
Soften ice cream and blend into jello.
Chill until firm.
Place in chocolate cups and dot Cool Whip on top.

title: steak(oven broiled)
directions: Sprinkle steaks lightly with salts and peppers.
Place in shallow pan.
Put one pat of butter on each steak.
Broil for about 15 minutes on each side.
(Use a tender steak, such as porterhouse, ribeye, t-bone, etc.)

title: peach delight cobbler
directions: Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.
In pan 9 x 13-inch, melt margarine or butter.
Add peaches.
Mix together self-rising flour, sugar, milk, eggs and vanilla.
Pour over peaches and bake.

title: dilled onions
directions: Sprinkle onions with dill seed.
Layer in wide-mouth pint jar.
In a saucepan, combine remaining ingredients; cook and stir over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over onions. Cover and refrigerate for 36 hours.
Serve as a relish or on sandwiches.

title: rice and broccoli
directions: Cook rice.
Cook broccoli by directions on package or cook fresh broccoli.
Then add broccoli to cooked rice.
Add grated or finely chopped onion, Cheez Whiz and mushroom soup.
Pour into greased casserole dish or into 2 greased 8 x 8-inch dishes.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Can freeze 1 (8 x 8-inch) dish and cook later.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Sift flour and cornmeal.
Add soda, cream of tartar, salt and sugar; sift again.
Add beaten egg, milk, cream and melted butter. Beat thoroughly.
Pour into a greased pan (9-inch square) and bake for 20 minutes in 425° oven.

title: ground beef and vegetable stew
directions: In Dutch oven brown beef, add onions, garlic, water, basil, salt, pepper and potatoes. Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are almost tender. Add peppers and tomatoes; simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until all is tender. Serve in bowls. Good with crusty bread.

title: no mixer cake
directions: *You may replace more bananas for the pineapple.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt butter first.
Mix other ingredients together and add melted butter.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: bran hot rolls
directions: Mix shortening, boiling water, sugar, bran and salt.
Stir until melted; let stand until lukewarm.
Add eggs and yeast dissolved in the warm water.
Add flour and beat well.
Cover bowl and place in refrigerator.
When ready to bake, form rolls and place on well-greased pan.
Let rise and bake at 375° until well browned.
Dough will keep 4 to 5 days in refrigerator.

title: debi's jambalaya(start with medium fire)
directions: Grease large pot while warming pot.
Add enough cooking oil to cover the bottom.
Add onions; cook until very brown, about 30 minutes.
Add bell peppers and celery.
Boil chopped salt meat in a little water for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Drain.
Add to onion, pepper and brown.
Add sausage; brown.
Add shrimp; reduce heat to prevent sticking.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add rice and 2 cups water for each cup of rice (8 cups).

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix rice, water, soup and soup mix.
Mix in pan.
Place chicken pieces on top.
Cover and cook about 1 hour at 350°.

title: texas caviar
directions: Drain and rinse peas and hominy.
Combine remaining ingredients; add Italian dressing.
Mix well and marinate overnight.
Serves 8.

title: chinese egg rolls
directions: Cut shrimp in 2 to 3 pieces and slice chicken and pork in thin slices.
Marinate in wine, salt, pepper and garlic.
Put meat in hot oil, cook for approximately 3 minutes.
Then add all other vegetables.
Add ginger and soy sauce.
Leave pot uncovered and cook until all liquid is evaporated.
Directions on how to roll egg roll are on the package.
Put in hot oil to brown.
To remove excess oil, wrap in paper towels.
Ready to eat.

title: toffee
directions: Combine ingredients and stir over medium heat to boiling. Boil until very thick and mixture pulls away from sides of pan and bottom just begins to scorch.
Remove from heat and dribble test by dropping a 1/2 tsp. of toffee on a dish.
If it quickly hardens, it is ready.
If not, return to heat for 30 seconds and repeat.

title: turkey divan stuffed potato
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Scrub potato; pierce skin with a fork. Bake 40 to 60 minutes until done.
Or scrub, pierce and bake in microwave oven at full-setting 4 to 6 minutes, turning potato over once; set aside.
If you use frozen broccoli, cook in oven or microwave following package directions, but don't add salt or butter.
If you use fresh broccoli, steam it in microwave, covered with plastic wrap, at full setting for 2 to 3 minutes.
Or cook in a vegetable steamer 10 to 15 minutes or in a covered saucepan in 1/2-inch water for 10 to 15 minutes over moderate heat.
Split open cooked potato lengthwise.
Add cubes of cooked turkey. Turkey can be leftover or salt-free turkey lunchmeat.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella, chives, paprika and seasoning blend.
Reheat briefly in the microwave, about 2 minutes on High or regular oven 5 minutes at 425°.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Add brown sugar
to
eggs; beat well.
Add white sugar, pudding, cream and vanilla.
Add milk until mixture is about 4 inches from top of	ice cream freezer.
This recipe is for a 6 quart freezer.

title: hot ham and swiss sandwiches
directions: Melt margarine and add onions, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Put a small amount of sauce on the bottom bun (or roll, cut in half).
Add ham and cheese.
Place top on sandwich.
Add more sauce to top.
Place in a baking pan and cover with foil. Bake at 350° until hot.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Soften margarine; add vanilla, sugar and eggs.
Stir in flour. Add nuts.
Do not chop nuts.
Larger pieces look more festive when baked.
Pack dough into an 8-inch square wax paper lined pan. Chill overnight.
Divide dough into 3 slabs.
Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Bake on a cookie sheet approximately 8 minutes at 350°. Should be crisp and light brown.
Can be frozen and baked as needed.
Use a variety of nuts.
Black walnuts are very tasty.

title: italian olive salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Chill and serve.

title: no bake fruit pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar, orange peel and juice until smooth.
Carefully spread cream cheese mixture into pie shell.
Sprinkle peaches with lemon juice to prevent browning. Arrange the peaches and blueberries over the cream cheese mixture. Chill 1 to 24 hours.
If desired, sprinkle with powdered sugar. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked steak
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces.
Combine meat with soup, salt and pepper.
Bake in foil-lined baking pan or glass baking dish. Bake 1 hour or until done in a preheated oven at 425°.

title: black eyed pea salad
directions: Combine all the ingredients and refrigerate at least 12 hours.

title: texas pecan cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flavorings and mix well. Sift flour and baking powder together. Add part of flour to mixture and mix well. Add remaining flour, along with nuts, raisins, and candied fruit. Mix well. Pour into tube pan and bake at 275 for two hours. Reduce heat to 225 and bake an additional hour.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together cornmeal mix, salt, sugar, milk and salad oil. Add eggs and mix well.
Add corn, chopped jalapeno peppers, grated cheese and bacon (fried crisp and crumbled).
Last, add onion, chopped fine, mashed pimientos and garlic.
Bake in greased 3 x 8 x 8-inch pan at 450° for 35 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Rub the potatoes with oil.
Prick with a fork.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until tender.
Allow potatoes to cool to the touch. Slice a small portion off the top of each potato.
Carefully scoop out pulp.
Mash the pulp with butter, chives, salt, pepper and enough milk to obtain desired consistency.
Carefully stuff shells.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all together except bread and sausage.
Grease a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish with margarine.
Place bread and sausage in dish. Pour mixture over this.
Refrigerate for at least 12 hours.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: banana muffs
directions: Combine the Bisquick, sugar, margarine and egg. Fold in the bananas. Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Makes 48 tiny muffins or 10 to 12 regular muffins. Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 400°. Frost while warm with thick icing of 1/2 cup confectioners sugar and 1 tablespoon water. Sprinkle with grated nuts.

title: unusually delicious cake
directions: Mix cake and frosting mix; add eggs, oil and water.
Mix well and pour into well greased bundt pan or other pan.
Bake for 50 min. at 350 degrees.
Can put a glaze or frosting if you prefer (good with/without).

title: chicken and okra gumbo
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
In a large aluminum pan cook chicken.
Add 1 tablespoon oil until brown.
Remove and set aside.
Add 2 more tablespoons oil and fry chopped okra for about 10 minutes.
Stir.
Make roux, made with butter and flour.
Add chicken, sauce, chopped onion, celery, bell pepper, garlic and water.
Simmer.

title: mrs. lucy's coconut cake
directions: Mix all together; beat with mixer about 10 minutes on medium speed.
Make 4 (9-inch) layers or 3 (10-inch) layers.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool layers and ice with recipe below.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cocoa and salt together; add margarine, vanilla and eggs.
Mix together, beating well.
Add nuts and place in greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 325°. When finished baking, add 1 package miniature marshmallows on top of warm brownies.
Mix icing and drizzle on top of marshmallows.

title: pork chop stew
directions: In a skillet, brown pork chops; pour off fat.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 to 2 hours.

title: italian style pork chops
directions: Sprinkle pork chops with salt, black pepper and Italian herbs. Brown well in heated butter, on both sides, about 5 minutes per side.
Place chops in heavy skillet; add garlic.
Add tomatoes with liquid, lemon juice and 2 teaspoons lemon peel.
Simmer gently 30 to 40 minutes or until chops are no longer pink in the center and cooked tender.
Garnish with grated lemon peel.

title: oreo cookie surprise
directions: Put cookie crumbs at bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix the cream cheese, butter and sugar; set aside.
Mix pudding, milk and vanilla.
Add cream cheese mixture; fold in Cool Whip.
Put cookie crumbs on top and bottom.
Cool in icebox for 4 hours.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift together first the flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, cocoa and oil in a large bowl.
Blend applesauce, oil and sugar and heat.
Beat into dry ingredients.
Stir in raisins and walnuts.
Turn batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or two 8-inch pans.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Then reduce heat to 375° and bake 15 minutes longer.
Use your own desired icing.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients and stir until blended.
Add marshmallows and then Cool Whip.
Stir until blended. Refrigeration is required until marshmallows have softened.

title: potatoes supreme casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, soup, sour cream, Cheddar cheese, onions and salt and pepper.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with bread crumbs and drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: summer spaghetti with tomato and mozzarella sauce
directions: Combine tomatoes, Mozzarella cheese, basil, olive oil, garlic, parsley, salt and pepper and reserved juice in bowl; let stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
When ready to serve, combine fresh cooked pasta and sauce until cheese is melted; serve immediately. Enjoy!

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain and add a little flour.
Then add other ingredients and heat.
(May replace vinegar and a little of the catsup with barbecue sauce.)
Serve on toasted buns.

title: granny's sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream sugar with margarine.
Add eggs, sour cream and vanilla. Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture.
For topping, mix pecans, cinnamon and brown sugar.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: In a 12-inch skillet, heat oil over medium heat and cook green pepper, onion, and garlic powder 3 minutes or till vegetables are tender.
Add chicken and brown 3 minutes.
Stir in sherry and pepper, cook 3 minutes.
Stir in Ragu sauce and cook 8 minutes or till chicken is no longer pink.
Serve over cook rice or pasta. Serves 8.

title: mushroom and celery meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients except soups together; mix very well. Form meatballs (small); fry on medium heat until done.
When all meatballs are fried, put all meat balls back into pan.
