Mix soups together with one can of water.
Pour over meatballs.
Bring to boil, stirring well.
Then turn on low and simmer until time to serve.

title: buttermilk waffles
directions: Blend last 4 ingredients.
Add liquid ingredients.
Mix well. Pour batter onto preheated/prepared waffle iron.
Serve with choice
of	toppings.
Time
of preparation: 20 minutes. Serves 6.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Stir in pretzels and 1/3 cup sugar. Bake in 400° oven for 7 to 8 minutes.
Re-stir pretzels taking out of oven.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Mix together pineapple, eggs and sugar.
Add and mix flour, coconut, nuts and baking soda.
Do not over mix.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 inch pan.
Bake at 350°
for 40 - 45 minutes. Frost when cool.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 40 minutes, divided.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread whole graham crackers in single layer.
Mix pudding mix and milk until smooth.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour 1/2 of pudding mixture over graham crackers. Repeat layers, ending with graham crackers.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew and debone chicken.
Save broth.
Spread chicken in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine milk and soups; pour over chicken. Spread 1/2 bag of stuffing over chicken.
Pour 1 cup of chicken broth over casserole along with 1/2 stick of margarine.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and mix.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add vanilla, baking soda, salt and flour.
Mix well.
Add sour cream; mix well.
Grease and flour a tube pan or 2 loaf pans. Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Check with toothpick for doneness. Recipe can also be halved and put in 1 loaf pan.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix flour, milk and egg together until smooth.
Add squash and onion.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.

title: chocolate snow bears
directions: Fill blender 1/2 full with ice.
Add creme de cacao, Amaretto, cherry juice and chocolate syrup.
Blend, then blend again with ice cream.

title: trey's favorite pork tenderloin
directions: Blend ingredients in food processor.
Put in plastic bag and marinate tenderloin overnight.
Pierce meat with fork before putting in marinade.
Bake on rack in pan at 350 degrees for 1 hour or until done.
Let stand 5-10 minutes before slicing.

title: shortbread
directions: Measure all dry ingredients except sugar and cinnamon into a large bowl.
With mixer at high speed, beat until well mixed, occasionally scraping bowl.
Put dough in a 9 x 9-inch square baking pan.
In a cup, mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut into bars while warm.
Makes 20 bars.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup and broth together.
Grease a pan or baking dish.
Mix peas, chicken and Stove Top dressing.
Put a layer of stuffing mix and layer of soup.
Layer this until dish is full.
Sprinkle stuffing mix on top and bake at 350° until brown.

title: creamy chicken and mushrooms
directions: In skillet, in 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Remove.
In remaining 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook mushrooms and onion with garlic powder until tender and liquid is evaporated, stirring often.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Chop cabbage and boil in salted water until tender but still crisp.
Wilt onion in melted butter.
Add pieced cheese to melted butter, stirring.
Mix in soup and seasonings and continue to heat.
Place cabbage in casserole and pour sauce over cabbage and mix.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: italian cookies(bisquits)
directions: Blend together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, each one individually, beating well after each egg.
Add almond or anise flavor, salt, baking powder and flour.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook onions and pepper in shortening until onion is yellow. Add ground beef; cook until brown and drain fat.
Stir in tomatoes, noodles, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Pour into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove cover for last 15 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion in skillet; drain fat. At the same time, in large pot, heat salsa, tomato sauce, tomato paste, whole tomatoes and noodles. Add meat. Let simmer on medium until noodles are done.

title: asparagus golden rod
directions: Make a cream sauce, mix flour and butter until blended.
Add milk and mustard; stir
over low heat until thickened.
Put asparagus on toast and top with sauce.
Garnish with boiled egg.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground chuck, then add taco seasoning and simmer.
Let cool and toss with remaining ingredients.
Add 1 bottle of Catalina dressing and 1/2 bottle of taco sauce.
Mix well.

title: martha's baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bacon, and place in greased casserole.
Place bacon on top.
Bake in slow oven at 250° to 300° for 2 hours or longer until most of juice is gone.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer the ingredients.
Cover tightly.
Mix 3 hours before serving.

title: fresh blueberry waffles(serves 4)
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, eggs, salt, baking soda, oil and milk.
Stir until smooth.
Pour onto hot waffle iron and cook.
Continue to make waffles.

title: yummy caramel bars
directions: Melt caramels and cream.
Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly butter 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Mix flour, soda, salt, brown sugar and oats.
Cut in butter.
Put half in pan and press evenly with chocolate chips and pecans.
Then spread with caramel mixture. Sprinkle remaining oat mix evenly over the caramel.
Bake 20 minutes.
Cool 30 to 45 minutes.
Chill in fridge 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: fruit cremes
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine orange juice or water and ice cubes to make 1 cup.
Add to gelatin and stir until ice is completely melted.
Add milk.
Pour into individual dessert dishes.
Chill.
Soft set in 30 minutes.
Makes 5 servings.

title: apricot glazed cornish hens
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line a 14 x 10 x 2-inch baking pan with heavy-duty foil.
Salt the inside and outside of the hens. Combine apricot spread with the cinnamon.
Brush hens with part of glaze after placing them in pan.
Cover hens with a foil tent and bake for 20 minutes.
Brush with more glaze.
Remove tent and continue baking, brushing with glaze 2 more times.
Bake approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water; set aside.
Mix cake mix, oil, egg yolks and flour.
Add Jell-O to batter; then stir in 3/4ths of frozen strawberries.
Beat egg whites and fold into batter.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: bierock casserole
directions: Set frozen bread dough out to thaw and let rise at least 8 hours.
Brown hamburger and drain grease.
Add chopped cabbage and onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Divide raised dough in half. Roll out half to fit in bottom of lightly greased pan.
Add hamburger mixture.
Roll out other half.
Place sliced cheese on mixture, then other half of rolled out dough.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Easier than making Bierocks.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate and wax.
Form mixture into balls.
Melt chocolate and 1/2 paraffin wax bar.
Using toothpicks, dip balls into chocolate and set on wax paper.
Allow to dry.
Makes approximately 80 small balls.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Mix biscuits as usual.
Place butter in bread pan, place in oven to melt.
Remove pan from oven and leave 1/2 of butter in pan.
Use remaining butter to spoon on top of biscuit.
Bake at 375° until golden brown on top and bottom.

title: chicken quiche
directions: Cook and drain vegetables (mixed vegetables may be used). Butter a large pie plate.
Sprinkle a little of cheese on bottom. Add vegetables.
Sprinkle the rest of cheese.
Blend the other ingredients for 15 seconds.
Pour over cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until knife comes clean when inserted in the center of quiche.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix the ingredients and roll into balls.
Dip balls into melted chocolate and put on waxed paper to cool.
Kids love to help with this one!

title: peanut cinnamon toast
directions: Blend until smooth and spread on bread.
Toast in oven.

title: oatmeal coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except pie crust shell together.
Pour into pie crust shell.
Bake in a 350° oven about 45 minutes or until set.

title: dried beef filling for rye boat
directions: Cut up dried beef fine.
Add to other ingredients that have been mixed thoroughly.
Cut top off round loaf of rye bread. Scoop out center and cut into cubes.
Fill the "boat" with filling and put cubes around outside to be dipped.
Can also put filling in a dish and use for bread cubes, crackers or chips.

title: quick refrigerator cucumber chips
directions: Wash cucumbers well, but do not peel.
Cut cucumbers crosswise into 1/4-inch slices.
Combine cucumbers, bell pepper and onion in a large bowl.
Sprinkle in salt and dill seed; stir well.
Let stand, uncovered, 1 to 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Stir together sugar and vinegar until sugar is dissolved, then pour over vegetables and mix gently.
Spoon into glass container.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 day or up to 3 weeks.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Combine all crust mixture and put 1/2 in bottom of greased pan.
Pour in fruit and juice, then add rest of mixture over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fun mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Store for up to 2 weeks in an airtight container.

title: crescent hot dogs
directions: Slice the middle of each hot dog, leaving a 1/2 inch at each end.
Cut each piece of cheese into 6 slices.
Insert 3 of the slices into each hot dog.
Separate the crescent rolls.
Place the cheese side down on the widest part of the triangle and roll each hot dog towards the point.
Place the cheese side up on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: bean and bacon slaw
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Stir in vinegar, Miracle whip, salt, pepper and sugar.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown meat in a large saucepan. Drain off fat.
Add onion, ketchup, water, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and salt and pepper.
Mix well. Simmer over low heat for 45 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes in bottom of casserole dish.
Salt and pepper each layer.
Add onion.
Mix the soup and canned milk well. Pour over potatoes.
Place the browned pork chops over top of potatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: blueberry cream stuffed baked french toast
directions: Cut bread into cubes and place in the bottom of a greased 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle blueberries evenly over bread.
Microwave cream cheese in bowl for 2 minutes.
Stir carefully and add sugar, sour cream, and vanilla.
Spread over blueberries.
Cut French bread into ten one inch thick slices, place over cream cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, and half & half, cinnamon, and nutmeg and pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes covered, then uncovered for approximately 15 minutes.
Let set before slicing.
Sift powdered sugar over before serving.

title: candy balls
directions: Combine peanut butter, sugar, M&M's and margarine. Shape into balls (1/2-inch). Chill. Really good.

title: chili
directions: Mix well.
Add 2 cups tomato juice (can use all water) and probably 1 cup water (go by the way it looks).
You don't want to be too thin, but enough liquid to cook awhile.
After liquid is bubbling good, reduce to low and simmer at least 2 hours or longer. Better after setting overnight.
After heating, until warm, taste and add seasoning, if necessary.
The taco seasoning and soups contain some salt.

title: praline bars
directions: Line jelly roll pan or other pan with foil.
Place 24 graham crackers in it and bring foil up to form edges around crackers. Boil sugar and margarine together for 3 or 4 minutes (count to 200 after it starts to boil, stirring continuously).
Add nuts and spread very evenly over crackers.
Bake for 10 minutes in a 350° oven on middle rack.
Let cookies cool.
Cut, using indentation of crackers as guide.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: chocolate bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water with 1 tablespoon sugar until frothy.
Beat egg yolks with brown sugar until thick; then beat butter and add cocoa, salt and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Add the warm milk and flour.
Beat 2 minutes.
Fold in egg whites (beaten until peaked, not dry) and currants.

title: pam's truly different cupcakes
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter.
Stir in nuts to coat.
Set aside.

title: caramel cuts
directions: Melt butter and then add sugar.
While still warm, add unbeaten eggs.
When blended, add vanilla; then nuts.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to butter, sugar, egg mixture.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all the dry ingredients first, then add orange juice and margarine.
This will have to be done by hand.
When mixture is no longer dry, pinch off little pieces and roll into balls.
Keep in freezer. Take out 15 minutes before serving.

title: french toast
directions: Mix ingredients, then dip bread slices in mixture, coating both sides.
Place in nonstick skillet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Cook until golden brown.
Top with syrup or powdered sugar.

title: my mother's rice
directions: Saut the rice, butter, onion and green peppers in a heavy skillet until lightly browned. Add the consomm and stir until all the ingredients are hot. Add the mushrooms, salt and pepper. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vareniky
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well, until cottage cheese is in fine curds; set aside.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Heat sugar and vinegar until sugar dissolves; cool, then add 1/2 cup oil.
Mix. Cool and eat.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix beans together in a bowl; set aside.
Mix oil, vinegar, sugar, onion, salt and pepper; add this to bean mixture.
Mix well.
Let stand 4 hours or overnight.

title: baked crab meat spread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch pie pan.
Melt butter in skillet over medium heat.
Add bell pepper, green onions and garlic.
Cook and stir 2 to 3 minutes until vegetables are tender. Stir in flour and pepper.
Cook 1 minute.
Gradually add milk. Cook until mixture boils, stirring constantly.
Stir in Parmesan cheese.
Remove from heat.
Fold in crab meat.
Pour into greased pan.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until thoroughly heated and cheese is melted.
Serve with Melba toast rounds.

title: seafood italian style pasta and cauliflower au gratin
directions: Saute chopped onion, garlic and tomato in a small amount of oil until golden.
Stir in dry spices and a 1/4 cup chicken broth. Add seafood, stirring to coat well with spices.
Pour on tomato sauce diluted with some chicken broth.
Bring to boil.
Adjust seasoning and simmer, uncovered, for 5 to 10 minutes.
Remember "crabmeat" is ready to eat when purchased, so cooking time is short.
Prepare noodles according to directions on package.
When cooked, but not soggy, drain and toss with some oil and sauteed garlic (optional).
Saute chopped onion and garlic; stir in cauliflower pieces.
Pour 1/4 cup broth.
Season to taste and cook, uncovered, over reduced heat for about 5 minutes.
Top with sauteed seasoned breadcrumbs.

title: lemon buttered new potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and pare a 1-inch strip around the center of each one.
Place potatoes, sugar, salt and garlic in large saucepan.
Cover with water and bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain well. Combine butter, lemon juice and paprika.
Drizzle over potatoes and toss gently.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: pecan-chocolate chip pie
directions: Beat eggs until well mixed and frothy.
Add ingredients in order, mixing well after each addition.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 325° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: butterscotch fluff
directions: Mix together margarine, flour and nuts.
Press in baking pan. Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool.

title: hot turkey salad(microwave)
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together and place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch microwave-safe dish.
Top with crumb mixture and microwave on 70% power 10 to 12 minutes or until casserole is hot and bubbly. Rich and delicious!

title: hamburger chop suey
directions: Brown hamburger in large skillet and break up in pieces. Drain grease.
Sprinkle green pepper, onion and celery over hamburger.
Pour tomatoes over all and salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle rice on top, cover and cook over medium heat until rice is done and juice is absorbed.

title: diabetic apricot nuggets
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over water and allow to soften for 5 minutes. Heat and stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Combine apricots, flour and orange peel in food processor or blender.
Work until finely chopped.
Add to gelatin.
Add vanilla and stir until completely blended.
Line an 8-inch pan with waxed paper.
Spread fruit mixture evenly; set aside until cool and firm.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Dip in melted chocolate.
Exchanges 1 candy = 1/5 bread and 14 calories.

title: jerky(beef or venison)
directions: Freeze meat until firm, but not solid, to make slicing easier. Use a meat slicer or sharp knife to slice meat with the grain as thinly as possible.
Place strips into a shallow pan and marinate 2 to 3 hours in mixture of remaining ingredients.
Drain.
Place strips on racks over foil or cookie sheets in a 150° oven and let bake 8 to 12 hours.
The long time ensures a dryer product that will keep longer.
Let cool and store in plastic container in refrigerator.
Will keep without refrigeration at least 2 weeks.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix egg, milk, salt and pepper together.
Dry chicken parts in paper towel and season.
Dip each piece first in crushed potato chips, then in egg/milk mixture, then back in potato chips.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Spread pie mix in 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan.
Then sprinkle cake mix.
Next, chopped walnuts and coconut.
Then melt oleo and drizzle over the top.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly, 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve slightly warm topped with Cool Whip.

title: dirt
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and cream cheese together.
Add pudding mix that has been mixed with milk.
Finally, add Cool Whip.
Crush cookies to resemble potting soil.

title: beef-n-tater casserole
directions: Using
a 2 quart casserole, brown ground beef in microwave and drain off grease.
Stir in both cans of soup and put frozen Tater Tots on top.
Bake until Tater Tots brown (about 20 minutes) in 350° oven.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters.
Mix cinnamon and 3/4 cup sugar in plastic bag.
Shake biscuits in mixture, a few at a time.
Place 1/2 the coated biscuits in a Bundt pan.
Heat oleo and 1 cup sugar to boil; pour 1/2 of butter mixture over coated biscuits.
Coat remaining biscuits and place in pan.
Pour remaining butter mixture over biscuits.
Cover with foil for 20 minutes of baking time, then uncover for remaining time.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
May be sliced or simply pulled apart.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions, omitting salt. Drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain.
Combine pasta, peppers, water chestnuts, green onions and if desired, cherry tomatoes in a bowl.
Combine oil and remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour over pasta mixture, stirring to coat well.
Cover and chill 8 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: stuffed minute steaks
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: grandma hanley's chicken spectacular
directions: Cook rice according to directions on the box.
Mix rice with chicken, soup, mayonnaise, water chestnuts, pimentos and green beans.
Cover with foil; bake at 350°.
Heat.
Remove foil; top with crushed crackers and cheese.
Heat long enough to melt the cheese.

title: easy garlic bread(fettunta)
directions: Cut bread in halves lengthwise.
Place halves on baking sheet with a piece of foil.
Melt
butter in small skillet and add garlic and parsley.
Saute
for
to
minutes.
Brush bread with butter mixture
and
sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Place under broiler
until
lightly
golden.
Watch carefully. To serve, cut diagonally.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Combine broccoli, soup and milk in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cover with onions and top with crumbs.
Drizzle melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 well.

title: chocolate lover's cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 50 minutes in greased and floured Bundt pan.

title: creamy orange frosting
directions: Combine powdered sugar, vanilla, butter and orange rind. Blend in orange juice to spreading consistency.

title: french onion soup
directions: In saucepan, cook onions in butter until onions are tender. Add broth, water and Worcestershire sauce. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, 25 minutes.
Place croutons or French bread in ovenproof bowls.
Spoon onion soup over croutons or French bread. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Top with grated Mozzarella cheese. Broil until cheese melts and turns golden brown. Serves 4.

title: mock au gratin potatoes
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix ingredients together. Pour into greased pan.
Top with crushed potato chips (if desired).
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add milk, then flour, sugar, butter, coconut and vanilla.
Pour in pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix together and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Can be frozen after baking and reheated in a crock-pot.
Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: spanish rice
directions: Place oil in large skillet and heat.
Coat bottom of skillet well; add onion, bell pepper and rice.
Brown rice until most of the rice is medium brown, stirring often.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste, tomato sauce and bouillon cubes.
Add enough water to cover rice completely.
Bring to boil; cover and simmer slowly until all water is absorbed.
Don't stir, but poke rice when checking it.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In a saucepan, saute onions in margarine until tender.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add milk and stir over low heat until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat and add cheese.
Add potatoes. Place in a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours or until potatoes are done.

title: black forest torte
directions: Sprinkle cake layers with orange juice.
Spoon or pipe 1/2 cup whipped topping into 3-inch circle in center of 1 cake layer on serving plate.
Spoon or pipe 1 cup of the whipped topping around top edge of cake layer.
Spoon 1/2 of the pie filling between circle and border.
Place second layer on top.
Spoon or pipe remaining whipped topping around top edge of cake layer.
Spoon remaining pie filling in center.
Refrigerate 1 hour or until ready to serve.
Makes 12 servings.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix well the first 4 ingredients. Then add milk. Cook in a double boiler and stir until thick. Pour mixture over vanilla wafers and bananas.

title: cappuccino mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Makes 20 cups of mix.
Use 1/4 cup for each serving.

title: aggression cookies
directions: Dump all ingredients into a large bowl.
Punch it, pound it and knead it.
Take all your aggressions out on the cookie dough. The more you pound, punch and knead the better the cookies!
Roll into small balls and bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
They are really delicious.

title: ham and cheese pan rolls
directions: Mix last four ingredients together.
Remove rolls from package.
Do not tear apart.
Slice lengthwise through entire package of rolls.
Spread mixture on each side.
Layer ham and cheese.
Put both sides of rolls back together and heat in oven or microwave until cheese melts.

title: grandma's baked pecan pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° until done, about 12 minutes.

title: tuna delight
directions: Put tuna in bowl.
Add salad dressing, pickle relish and celery; mix well.
Put a lettuce leaf and 2 tomato slices on each plate.
Put a big spoonful of Tuna Delight on each lettuce leaf.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix together and pour into hot greased pan and bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Spread crumbled crackers in a casserole dish.
Lay seasoned pork chops on top of crumbled crackers and add a can of cream of chicken soup on top.
Crumble more crackers on top of soup.
Let bake for 30 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: kepela's steak-n-beans
directions: Cut steak into medium thin strips, then brown in 2 tablespoons oil in electric skillet or wok.
When brown, add a little water and soy sauce; simmer until tender.
Add green beans and simmer for 10 minutes.
Put tomato wedges on top of steak and beans and simmer about 15 minutes longer.
(May add more soy sauce to taste.)
Serve over rice.

title: frosting
directions: Beat until whipped cream consistency.
Add 2 1/2 cups powdered sugar, or more if needed to spread well.
Beat 7 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in the jackets and the eggs.
Peel and slice into small pieces.
Mix with mayonnaise, sweet relish and just a tad of mustard to a consistency to suit your taste.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and onion powder.
Place in a serving bowl.
Slice 1 boiled egg and place on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: rumika(china dish)
directions: Note:
Can use water chestnuts instead of potatoes, if desired.

title: sausage-apple ring
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix thoroughly.
Press lightly into a 6-cup ring mold and turn out onto a shallow baking pan.
(Or just mold it around a bowl.)
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or bake 30 minutes 1 day and 30 minutes the next.
Serve with scrambled eggs, grated cheese and paprika in the middle of the ring.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken unsalted.
Cut into chunks.
Mix soups and broth together.
Melt margarine and stir in stuffing mix.
Into casserole dish, put 1 layer of stuffing, 1 layer chicken and 1 layer soups.
Repeat layers, ending with stuffing on top.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: peanut oil cake
directions: Pour all ingredients in mixing bowl and mix well.
Bake in greased 9 x 13 inch pan for 45 minutes at 350° oven.

title: chop chop
directions: Chop first 5 ingredients.
Mix all together with olive oil and sugar and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: seasoned cheese biscuits
directions: Mix flour, salt, baking powder and parsley together in bowl. Cut shortening in.
Stir cheese in.
Add milk.
Stir only until ingredients are moistened.
Spoon onto baking sheet.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Bake until brown in preheated oven at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes in regular oven (375° for 7 to 10 minutes in conventional oven).

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and 1 egg.
Press in bottom of a jelly roll pan.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 2 eggs.
Pour over first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
When cool, dust with powdered sugar and cut in squares.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Mix everything together and pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan and bake at 350° until done.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Blend cheese and butter.
Stir in flour, salt and paprika. Mix well.
Wrap 1 teaspoon of this mixture around each olive. Place on flat pan and freeze.
Store in plastic bags.
When ready to serve, bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: estofado(spicy hot mexican beef stew)
directions: In a 10 x 2-inch skillet, heat 2 tablespoons of the oil over moderate high heat.
Saute the onion for 3 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove onion from pan using a slotted spoon and set aside.
Add the remaining oil to the pan and heat.
Place the meat in the pan and brown well, stirring frequently.
Return the onion to the pan.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Bring the mixture to a boil over high heat, reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until the meat is fork-tender.
Turn into a warmed serving dish and garnish with the parsley.
Serve with warmed fresh corn tortillas.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Stir dry ingredients together and add to the other ingredients.
Juice of 1/2 lemon is optional.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Use paper bake cups.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: At room temperature, cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs and flavorings.
In another bowl, sift together flour, soda and baking powder.
Mix dry ingredients and buttermilk with other mixture.
Beat well.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Ice or glaze as desired.

title: simple cinnamon rolls
directions: Beat biscuit mix and 2/3 c. milk until dough is stiff.
Knead on floured surface until dough is smooth, about 10 times.
Roll out until dough is in a thin rectangle.
Spread with about 1/2 the margarine, sprinkle with part of the sugar and about 1 tsp. cinnamon.
Roll up dough and press seam together.
Cut in slices about 2 inches apart.
In pan, put remaining sugar, milk, cinnamon and margarine.
Place rolls cut side down in mixture.
They look like they are swimming in it.
Bake at 400 degrees
until golden brown.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: In saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons butter over medium heat.
Mix in flour, stirring.
Stir in broth, milk and wine.
Cook, stirring, until sauce is smooth and thickened.
Stir in cheese, mushrooms and salt and pepper to taste; set aside.
Cook pasta; drain.
Cut chicken into 8 pieces; flatten to 1/4-inch thick. Heat 2 tablespoons butter in heavy skillet; cook chicken 2 to 3 minutes on each side.
Toss noodles with sauce, reserving 4 teaspoons.
Place on serving platter; place browned chicken on noodles.
Garnish with remaining sauce and parsley.
Serves 2.

title: diet stew(great)
directions: Fry turkey, onion and pepper in skillet.
Mix all ingredients together and place in large Dutch oven and cook until thick or place in slow cooker all afternoon.
Serves 6; 3 protein, 4 veggies and 1 fruit.

title: spanish pork chops
directions: Mix water, vinegar and sugar until dissolved.
Place pork chops in baking dish.
Pour mix over chops.
Add 1 tablespoon ketchup on each chop.
Add onion slices on each chop.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peggy herbst's smash cake
directions: Mix cake mix with melted oleo. Add 1 egg and cup of chopped pecans.
Pat into oblong pan that has been greased and floured. Set aside.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and box of powdered sugar together.
Pour over first mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour on top rack of oven.

title: rich mocha hot chocolate
directions: Heat milk and chocolate in a heavy saucepan until chocolate melts.
Whisk until smooth, or beat with an electric mixer until flecks of chocolate are incorporated.
Stir in sugar and salt; bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce the heat; simmer for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in coffee and half and half, then briefly bring to a simmer.
Add vanilla and serve immediately. Serves 5.

title: buttons and bowknots
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cut shortening into flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, baking powder, nutmeg, salt and cinnamon until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Stir in egg and just enough milk so dough leaves sides of bowl.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface. Knead lightly 10 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with floured doughnut cutter.
Hold opposite end of each ring and twist to form figure 8.
Place bowknots and buttons (holes) on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Dip into margarine, then into sugar.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 2 sticks butter, eggs and powdered sugar all together in mixing bowl.
Beat with mixer for 15 minutes (this cooks eggs). Melt 1 stick butter and add graham cracker crumbs.
Press in bottom of oblong pan for crust.

title: aunt clorena's date loaf candy(from the files of clorena williams griffith)
directions: Combine sugar and milk; cook until it forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Add chopped dates and cook 5 minutes more. Beat until it begins to thicken.
Add 1 cup chopped pecans.
Pour onto buttered platter and cool and cut.

title: peaches and cream french toast
directions: Arrange bread in a single layer in a baking pan.
Combine eggs, cream, peach preserves and nutmeg.
Beat until smooth and pour over the bread.
Turn the slices to coat evenly.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: caramel no bake cookies
directions: Bring to boil, sugar, margarine and milk.
Add pudding and oats.
Cool for 15 minutes, then drop on wax paper and refrigerate.

title: best ever pastry
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut in shortening and add water, vinegar and egg.
Stir lightly with a fork until dough is moist enough to hold together.
Form into a ball and roll out on floured surface for pie crust.

title: banutaberry cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Pour in a rectangular baking dish approximately 9 x 11 x 2-inch.
After the cake has cooled, cream the cream cheese and sugar with a mixer. Pour this mixture over the cake evenly to the edges.
Cut a banana, finely, to cover the entire surface.
Spread the chopped pecans over the cake.
Spread the pie filling over the cake.

title: simple and delicious swiss steak
directions: Place cubed steaks in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine stewed tomatoes and flour in a 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in gravy and chili sauce. Bring to a boil; simmer 1 minute.
Pour sauce over steaks.
Cover; bake in 375° oven 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve with hot mashed potatoes or noodles.

title: carrot cake (with nut icing)
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt. Combine oil and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating after each. Gradually add dry ingredients.
Mix well; add carrots.
Pour into three 8-inch pans; bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, or tube pan at 300° for 1 hour.

title: jalapeno pie
directions: Grease sides and bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan with shortening.
Place jalapenos in rows on bottom of pan.
Beat eggs and pour evenly over pan.
Grate cheese and spread evenly over eggs and jalapenos.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute onions and pepper in cooking oil and remove.
Cook meat briefly until red color disappears, but not until meat is brown. Remove excess fat.
Add tomatoes, pepper and onions combination, seasoning and rice.
Cook until rice is tender.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix ingredients together in large bowl; beat about 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with cream cheese frosting.

title: ma's fruit salad
directions: Mix all canned fruit together and cover. Refrigerate. Add bananas right before serving.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare pudding according to directions and place in refrigerator to get firm.
Stack, in a punch bowl, in the following order, using one-half of each ingredient:

1 cake layer, half of vanilla pudding, half of cherry pie filling, half of fruit cocktail, half of pineapple, half of nuts, half of coconut, half of Cool Whip, then add second cake layer and continue, in same order, using the remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.
This will keep several days in the refrigerator.
Serves 20 to 25.

title: quadrangle grille's pumpkin-walnut cheesecake
directions: Let cake cool to room temperature.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 6 hours or overnight to allow cake to set.
At service, carefully loosen the collar on the spring-form pan and remove.

title: sharon's chocolate cake
directions: Melt
butter
in a saucepan.
Add water and oil.
Bring to a boil.
Mix a little at
a time with dry ingredients.
Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour
in
a
greased sheet cake pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamy peach pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; beat until smooth.
Fold in whipped cream and gently stir in peaches.
Pour filling into graham cracker crust.
Chill well.

title: square dance cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, and salt together.
In a saucepan bring to a boil margarine, water, shortening, and cocoa, then add to dry ingredients.
Beat together eggs, soda, vanilla, and buttermilk then add to batter.

title: cream cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage, covered, 10 minutes in a small amount of boiling salted water.
Drain well and set aside.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk and whipping cream; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Add cabbage to white sauce, mixing well.
Spoon into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese and top with breadcrumbs; drizzle with 2 tablespoons melted butter and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Serve 8.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Mix okra and tomatoes in a saucepan; add remaining ingredients. Bring to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 15 to 20 minutes or until okra is tender. Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: easy rice
directions: Combine in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat together eggs, cooking oil and vanilla.

title: turkey burgers
directions: Mix turkey and dry soup mix together.
Spray pan with nonstick Pam.
Form into patties and fry.

title: overnight slaw
directions: Core and shred cabbage; mix with other vegetables.
Mix dressing and pour over slaw.
Stir well and cover.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter.
Mix other ingredients in a bowl and add butter mixture.
Pur in casserole and top with the cheese and sour cream.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Use at least 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: plum bundt cake
directions: Sift flour and spices together and set aside.
Beat sugar, eggs and oil together until mixed well.
Add baby food to egg mixture and mix well.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in greased and floured Bundt pan.

title: uncle john's breakfast casserole
directions: Arrange buttered bread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer sausage and cheese over bread.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Pour over cheese.
Chill overnight.
Remove from fridge 15 minutes before baking.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes, or until set.

title: yogurt pound cake
directions: Cream margarine or butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to mixture. Stir in lemon rind, vanilla and yogurt.
Grease and flour a 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes, then remove and cool completely on rack.

title: kahlua mousse cheesecake
directions: Combine and press in bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: mama's famous barbecue sauce
directions: Heat, but do not boil.
Pour over any meat you wish to barbecue.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook all ingredients except strawberries until thick.
Slice strawberries and place in a graham cracker crust.
Pour thickened sauce over strawberries.
Top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: brown sugar frosting
directions: Cook sugar and water to soft ball stage (236°).
Gradually add to whites, beating until mixture forms peaks.
Frosts tops and sides of two 8-inch layers.
Real good on spice cake.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine dry pudding mix in pineapple and juice.
Let set until dissolved.
Then add your choice of the following (drain the canned fruit):
peaches, mixed fruit, fruit cocktail, mandarin oranges, strawberries, coconut, nuts, bananas (mix bananas with a little lemon juice to keep them from turning dark).

title: fresh rhubarb crunch
directions: Combine oats, flour and brown sugar; add nuts.
Cut in butter with pastry blender until crumbly.
Combine sugar, rhubarb and cinnamon.
Place half the crumb mixture in a greased 8-inch pan; cover with rhubarb mixture.
Top with remaining crumb mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream.

title: brer rabbit's carrots
directions: Scrape carrots with vegetable peeler; cut into penny slices. Place carrots in saucepan and cover with cold water.
Add salt (you can leave salt out).
Cover pan and heat over medium-high heat until water starts to boil.
Turn to low.
Remove cover and cook 15 more minutes.

title: shrimp florentine
directions: Put spinach into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Blend shrimp, soup, sherry, parsley and pepper.
Spoon over spinach.
Combine cheese and crumbs.
Sprinkle over all.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Combine first four ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Stir and knead until well blended.
Chill for about 30 minutes.
Melt chocolate and roll peanut butter mixture into balls.
Dip balls into melted chocolate.
Chill until firm.

title: mock filet mignon
directions: Combine chuck with salt and pepper.
Shape into 4 patties. Wrap each with a piece of bacon.
Secure with toothpick.
Broil on one side.
Turn and broil on other side.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Put half of the bread cubes into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with cubed cream cheese, distributing evenly.
Top with rest of bread cubes.
Pour beaten mixture over all.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
The next morning, bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serve with warm maple syrup.

title: almond butter crunch
directions: Line bottom and sides of 8 or 9 inch cake pan with aluminum foil (not plastic wrap or wax paper). Butter foil heavily; set aside. Combine almonds, butter, sugar and corn syrup in 10 inch skillet. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Boil, stirring constantly, until mixture turns golden brown, about 5 to 6 minutes. Working quickly, spread candy in prepared pan. Cool about 15 minutes or until firm. Remove candy from pan by lifting edges of foil. Peel off foil. Cool thoroughly. Break into pieces. Makes about 3/4 pound.

title: three thing pie
directions: Dissolve candy bar in double boiler.
Mix in Cool Whip, stirring well.
Put in pie shell and chill for 1 hour.

title: pete's fast baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and boil until not quite done.
Cool and refrigerate.
When you need baked potatoes, take out amount needed and put under broiler for 15 minutes, turning once.

title: pizza roll (sausage roll)
directions: Stir and crumble sausage, and cook until done.
Add drained mushrooms, spices, and tomato sauce from pizza mix.
Prepare dough as directed.
Grease cookie sheet well, as well as your hands. Spread dough on cookie sheet.
Add cheese to sauce mix, and pour onto dough.
Pull dough up around sausage mixture, and bake in 425° oven 15-20 minutes, or until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken breast in strips.
Dip in beaten egg, milk, salt and pepper. Dip in self-rising flour. In heavy skillet, melt 1 stick margarine.
Place chicken strips in hot skillet. Brown quickly.
Place in baking dish.
Pour orange juice over chicken, about 1 1/2 cups to cover chicken. Bake until orange juice has cooked down thick.

title: oatmeal coconut cookies
directions: Mix butter, shortening, brown sugar, sugar, eggs and vanilla until creamy.
Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add oatmeal and coconut.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Roll in sugar and bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.
Don't overbake!

title: sweet and crunchy cookies
directions: Melt butterscotch bits with peanut butter in heavy pan, over low heat.
Stir until well blended.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Stir until well covered.
Press into buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Let stand.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together the first 11 ingredients and put in a pan. Stir-fry the almonds, corn flakes and margarine; sprinkle over the first mixture.
Bake at 350° in oven for 30 minutes.

title: dumplings with sauerkraut
directions: Cook sauerkraut, adding just enough water to cover, for 20 minutes. Mix flour, baking powder, salt, egg and milk. Drop by tablespoon over sauerkraut. Cook 5 minutes, uncovered; then cover and cook 7 minutes longer.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour and all other ingredients except beans and cracker crumbs.
Cook until thick.
Add to beans and place in 2-quart casserole.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish; bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: mother's banana bread
directions: Blend sugar and shortening, then add eggs.
Slice bananas into mixture and beat well.
Mix dry ingredients and add to batter along with milk. Beat well.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Let cool 10 minutes before removing from pan to wire rack.

title: easy divinity(club member:  renee evans)
directions: Bring sugar, Karo and water to full boil; turn flame to medium low and cook until small drops form a hard ball when dropped in cold water.
(Take about 12 to 15 minutes.)
Stir frequently to prevent scorching.
While this is cooking, beat 3 egg whites until very stiff.
Leave mixture on and pour cooked syrup into egg whites.
Add vanilla.
Do not stop beating.
Continue to beat until mixture is very stiff.
Stop and stir in nuts.
Drop immediately by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Store in tight container to preserve fudginess.

title: frosty jello
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add the ice cream by spoonfuls until melted.
Chill.

title: haggis(old scottish recipe)
directions: Clean paunch; soak in cold salted water overnight. Then turn inside out. Simmer 3 hours the heart, lights and liver. Mince lights and heart. Grate half of liver. (The other half is not used.) Mix in bowl all the ingredients with finely chopped suet. Add oatmeal and onions, browned in fat. Season highly with salt and black pepper and moisten with water in which the pluck was boiled. Put mixture in paunch and sew up the opening, being careful to leave space for oatmeal to swell. Put in a large saucepan of hot water. Boil 3 hours, being careful to prick with needle as soon as the Haggis begins to swell.

title: marzetti
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Brown hamburger.
Drain, then add 2 cans tomato soup and 1 can milk.
Stir and heat to bubbly.
Remove from heat and add noodles and cheese to meat mixture.
Mix well.
Then serve with sprinkled Parmesan if you'd like.

title: eggplant patrice
directions: Slice unpeeled eggplant 1/4 inch thick.
Parboil until partially tender.
Place layer of eggplant slices in large casserole which has been sprayed with cooking spray.
Add layer of sliced tomatoes.
Fill spaces with chopped green peppers and onions.
Sprinkle lightly with each of the seasonings.
Add layer of cheese and repeat until casserole is filled, ending with cheese. Cover; bake at 400° about 1/2 hour.
Remove cover, reduce heat to 350° and cook until sauce thickens and is golden, about 1/2 hour. Serves 6.

title: pineapple jello salad
directions: Feeds 20; may be cut in half.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 500° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine ingredients and beat until smooth.
This works well with Granny Smith or Golden Delicious apple slices that have been dipped in apple juice.
Use the fat-free cream cheese for a more healthful dip.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Wash, don't peel, and cut up potatoes into bite-size; cook. Layer potatoes, then cheese, bacon and butter in ovenproof dish. Repeat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Heat until hot.

title: nut roll cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pack in a tube pan lined with wax paper.
Wet hands with water before attempting to pack mixture in pan.
Refrigerate 1 1/2 days before removing from pan and cutting.

title: sugarplums
directions: Blend eggs and 1 cup sugar.
Stir in chopped dates, coconut, walnuts and vanilla.
Butter a 2-quart casserole dish and pour in mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes. Remove from oven and let cool until mixture can be handled.
Roll into walnut sized balls.
Roll balls in remaining sugar.

title: campers' chili beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large crock-pot.
Cover and cook on High for 1 hour.

title: best ever sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the sugar and butter.
Combine with remaining ingredients and mix well.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts. Place two inches apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Yields 60.
Dip with ice cream scoop.
Flatten with sugared glass.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Melt butterscotch chips and peanut butter in a double boiler on low heat. Add noodles and nuts.
Drop on waxed paper as to size you want.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Cook until thick.
Add 3 cans drained hominy.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with paprika.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: potato salad for a crowd
directions: Cook potatoes in skins;
cool
in
ice
water
in sink. Remove skins; cut in cubes.
Use
the biggest pot you can find and add other ingredients;
mix with dressing and chill.
Best if sits overnight.

title: heavenly dessert
directions: Drain juice from pineapple into small bowl.
In medium saucepan mix sugar and eggs until smooth.
Add pineapple juice to mixture.
Cook at medium heat until it thickens.
Remove from heat.
Cool.

title: tortilla rolls
directions: Beat the cream cheese until smooth. Add jal., ketchup, chili powder, and garlic powder mix well. Spread over flour tortillas and top with turkey. Roll up and chill for 2 hrs. Slice in 1 in pieces.

title: kookin'
directions: Combine oleo, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, vanilla and salt. Put batter into an ungreased pan.
Reserve 1/4 of batter.
Put pie filling on top of batter and cut in with a knife.
Put rest of batter on top.
Cook at 350° in oven for 45 minutes or until done.

title: mrs. parker's favorite brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate and margarine over hot water.
Beat sugar and eggs.
Blend in flour, baking powder and salt.
Combine with chocolate mixture. Mix in nuts.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes, cool and frost.

title: momma's fudge
directions: Butter the sides of a heavy 3-quart saucepan.
In it combine sugar, evaporated milk and butter.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to boiling.
Cook to 236° (soft ball stage) for about 12 minutes, stirring frequently.
(Mixture should boil gently over entire surface.)
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients; stir until combined and chocolate is melted.
Turn into a buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch or a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Score into squares while warm; cut when firm.
If fudge is soft, chill. Makes about 3 1/2 pounds.

title: mulled wine
directions: Mix everything together except brandy and port.
Heat and let spices permeate.
Add brandy and port at the last minute.

title: easy swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 375° until bubbling everywhere.

title: sugar-free new york cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat cream cheese and sweetener for about 3 minutes until very smooth in a large bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add lemon juice, vanilla and salt.
Beat in sour cream until just mixed.
Grease an 8-inch spring-form pan with 2.5-inch sides and line bottom with greased parchment or waxed paper.
Wrap pan with foil to avoid seepage.
Pour batter into pan.
Set pan in a larger roasting pan/casserole and surround with 1-inch very hot water.
Bake 45 minutes.
Turn off oven, without opening door, and cool one hour. Then, cool on a rack for one hour.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight. Garnish with mint and enjoy!

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, onion, salt, pepper, 1 can tomato sauce and egg.
Form a loaf.
Place in shallow pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate before serving.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Beat egg, salt and pepper together. Dip chicken into egg and coat with breadcrumbs. Saute chicken in butter in skillet. Arrange chicken in slow cooker. Pour pizza sauce over chicken. Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours. Layer Mozzarella cheese over top and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Cook an additional 15 minutes.

title: christmas wassail
directions: Pour the apple cider into a large saucepan.
Strip the peels from the oranges and lemons, using a vegetable peeler (trim only the zest, none of the white).
Add peels to cider.
Squeeze juice from lemons and oranges; add.
Stir in cloves, allspice and cinnamon sticks.

title: crispy chicken
directions: Remove
skin
from chicken.
Wash and pat dry.
Combine cornflake
crumbs,
onion
salt, paprika and garlic salt.
Dip chicken pieces in milk, then coat with crumb mixture.
Arrange chicken
pieces
in 2 quart utility dish with larger pieces at corners
and
small
pieces toward center.
Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture over top.
Cover loosely with heavy-duty plastic wrap.
Cook
covered
on
full
power
for 18 to 20 minutes or until chicken is cooked.
I sprinkle with lemon pepper.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Combine first 5 ingredients in order.
Cook mixture over low heat until it becomes thickened.
Pour over drained macaroni.
Mix well.
Stir in carrots, celery and peppers.

title: norwegian white fudge
directions: Brown the almonds and butter in oven for 15 minutes, turning. Melt the cream cheese.
Add the powdered sugar and vanilla.
Stir, then add hot almonds.
Pour into pan; put in refrigerator until soft.
Cut into squares when set.

title: hearty bean soup
directions: Wash dried beans and cover with warm water.
Let soak overnight.
Pour off water.
In large Dutch oven or stock pot, put all ingredients and about 1 quart of water.
Bring to a boil, turn down heat and let simmer for two or three hours or until beans are tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add water occasionally as needed.
Serve with hot cornbread or crackers.

title: strawberry angel dessert
directions: Cut angel food cake into cubes and press flat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix jello according to directions.
Pour over cake pieces.
Chill in refrigerator.
Make instant pudding according to directions.
Spread over cake and jello mixture.
Chill.

title: fruit pizza pie
directions: Cook until thickens and dribble over fruit. Refrigerate.

title: upside-down lemon puffs
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
In a small bowl, combine sugar, lemon peel, water and margarine; divide among 10 ungreased muffin cups. Sprinkle with nuts.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Place in prepared muffin cups.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately invert onto a serving tray.
Serve warm.
Makes 10 rolls.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix hot sausage, regular sausage, bread crumbs and eggs together.
Roll into balls and fry; drain.

title: wine party punch
directions: Mix frozen juices with wine and blend until smooth.
Just before serving, pour in sparkling water.
Add ice cubes or block of ice.
Garnish with berries, cherries or slices of orange, lemon or pineapple.

title: elegant meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and milk. Add flour sifted with baking powder and salt. Add corn meal, stirring only enough to mix. Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full; bake in hot oven for 25 minutes. Makes 1 dozen.

title: wilt-proof salad
directions: Cook vegetables according to label directions. Drain. Cool slightly. Toss with mushrooms in a large bowl.
Sprinkle dressing, pepper and parsley over all.
Toss lightly and refrigerate until ready to serve.
May be served alone or in a lettuce lined bowl.

title: chocolate or butterscotch "mousse"
directions: Mix together and bake in a 9 x 12-inch pan for 15 minutes at 350°.
The crust will not be brown.
Cool.

title: pineapple sour cream pie
directions: In
saucepan,
combine	sugar, flour and salt.	Stir in pineapple,	sour
cream
and lemon juice.
Cook and stir until mixture
thickens
and comes to boiling; cool 2 minutes.
Stir small
amount
of
hot
mixture into egg yolks;
return to hot mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes.
Spoon into
cooled
pastry shell.
Spread meringue atop pie, sealing meringue to
crust	and bake in a moderate 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cranberry-raisin cookies
directions: Combine dried fruit and water.
Cook for 3 minutes and cool. Cream shortening, eggs, sugar and vanilla.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Mix mayo and taco sauce in large bowl.
Mix the rest of the ingredients in bowl.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Add your chips and lettuce.

title: monkey bread
directions: Sprinkle pecans evenly over the bottom of a well-greased 10-inch Bundt pan.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Cut biscuits into quarters; roll each piece in sugar/cinnamon mixture and layer in pan.
Combine brown sugar and melted butter.
Pour over dough. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool only 10 minutes and invert onto plate.
Serve this with Egg Casserole Dish.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat sugar, oil and eggs. Combine dry ingredients and add to the first mixture slowly, mixing well. Add pecans and carrots. Grease and flour 2 round cake pans or a 9 x 13 cake pan.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle apples with lemon juice to keep them from discoloring.
Combine apples with celery.
Add mayonnaise, mixing well.
Arrange leaves of crisp cold lettuce on six salad plates and spoon in salad mixture.
Just before serving, sprinkle with nuts.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mostaccioli sausage bake
directions: Brown sausage, drain.
Add sauce, noodles and Parmesan cheese. Mix well.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In saucepan, saute onion in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Simmer for 10 minutes covered.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Melt butter and stir in flour, salt, pepper, sugar and onions. Add sour cream and stir until thick.
Add grated cheese. Fold in beans.
Pour into greased casserole.
Add melted butter to crushed cornflakes and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: soft oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cream the sugars and shortening.
Add eggs and dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in oatmeal and raisins.
Drop on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350°.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Arrange ingredients in casserole dish ending with cracker crumbs and a sliced egg on top.

title: swedish potato dumplings
directions: Cook onions and bacon with margarine until clear.
Brown meat and drain.
Mix onions, bacon, meat and spices (set aside).
Grate potatoes at medium speed in blender.
Add 2 tablespoons salt to grated potatoes.
Start boiling salt water in 2 large pots.
Add flour and oatmeal to potatoes.
Make round balls of potato mixture, place and seal 1 tablespoon of meat mixture in center. Plop into water filled wooden spoons.
Cook on medium-high 1 hour after last dumpling has been added.

title: bonbons
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and roll into balls. Melt chips in top of double boiler. Roll balls in melted chips. Put on wax paper and cool.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Brown trout quickly in bacon grease and take care not to cook them through. Reduce heat and pour a cup of dry sherry into skillet.
Simmer for 5 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger; drain fat.
Mix all ingredients and simmer until hot.
Remove green pepper.
Serve hot on buns.
Serves 6.

title: yellow squash casserole 1
directions: Pour melted margarine over bread crumbs.
Steam squash and onion, then mix with soup, sour cream and carrots.
Put half of bread crumb mixture in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Add all of squash mixture, top with remaining bread crumb mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: party dogs(fast-fun-delicious)
directions: You will need a crock-pot and wooden toothpicks (not colored).

title: rocky road candy
directions: Add the 3 ingredients together and stir.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper and let set.

title: orange salad
directions: Stir puddings, gelatin and hot water together and boil, stirring, constantly, until thickened.
Completely cool.
Add pineapple with juice and drained oranges.
Fold in whipped cream and chill about 3 hours.
Can be used as salad or dessert.
Good!

title: cheese manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti according to package directions. Rinse in cold water and drain.

title: cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Increase oven temperature to 450°.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix all together. Makes 1 gallon.

title: coconut rum balls
directions: In large bowl, combine crumbs, coconut and nuts.
Add sweetened condensed milk and rum; mix well.
Chill 4 hours.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in coconut.
Store tightly covered in refrigerator.
Makes about 8 dozen.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Cut up potatoes like medium thickness potato chips; rinse and drain.
Then make 3 to 4 layers of potatoes, cheese, salt and pepper, butter pieces.
Put several butter pieces on last layer. On top of shredded Cheddar, add 4 ounces grated Mozzarella cheese. Then pour over all 1 pint of heavy cream.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.
Top cheese will brown.
Poke with fork.
If not tender, add 15 minutes to baking.

title: chicken tortillas
directions: Mix chicken, onion, garlic, soups and tomatoes together.
In greased casserole, layer chips and chicken mixture twice.
Put grated cheese on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: turtles
directions: Boil milk and syrup to soft ball stage, stirring constantly. Lay pecans in 3's on buttered cookie sheets.
Spoon on caramel mixture; lay a square of plain Hershey on each and spread to cover caramel.

title: dirt plant
directions: Mix all ingredients except Oreos in bowl.
Separately blend Oreo cookies until fine.
Cover bottom of a planter with Oreos. Layer pudding mixture, Oreos, pudding, Oreos, pudding, etc.
Cover top with Oreos.

title: toffee squares
directions: Cream butter, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Add flour and salt.
Spread into well-greased with butter cookie sheet pan. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Ice with melted sweet chocolate and cut while warm.

title: seven minute icing
directions: Cook in double boiler for 7 minutes, then use over any cake. May add 1 can of coconut flakes.

title: chicken fried steak
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces.
Roll in flour seasoned with salt, pepper and paprika; pound with edge of heavy saucer.
Brown in hot oil.
Add water, cover and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour. Serve hot with meat drippings spooned over or make gravy.
Gravy can be made by adding milk or water to drippings, 2 cups liquid and 3 tablespoons flour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate covered pretzels
directions: Melt almond bark over low heat, stir in pretzels and peanuts, spread on to waxed paper and cool.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Mix butter, syrup, brown sugar and salt together; boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add baking soda.
Pour over popped corn and mix well.
Pour corn in large shallow pan and bake 45 minutes at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: soups
directions: Simmer 2 hours.
Skim fat off and strain.
Can be frozen.

title: simple chicken italiano
directions: In large skillet, combine chicken and about 1/3 of Italian dressing.
Saute until chicken starts to brown.
Add vegetables and remaining dressing.
Cover; simmer 7 to 9 minutes until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring frequently.
Serve over pasta.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 5 servings.

title: standing rib roast in a modern way
directions: Bring roast to room temperature and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place on rack on shallow roaster.
Preheat oven to 375°. Place roast in oven for 1 hour.
Do not open oven door.
After cooking 1 hour, turn off heat.
Do not peek.
May be left all day. Before serving, still not having opened oven door, turn on oven to moderate 350°.

title: chocolate cherry bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan or 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, pie filling, extract and eggs; stir until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° in 15 x 10-inch pan for 20 to 30 minutes, or in 13 x 9-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: cappuccino punch
directions: In a small bowl, combine the sugar and coffee; stir in boiling water until dissolved.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled.
Just before serving, pour coffee mixture into a 1-gallon punch bowl. Stir in milk.
Add scoops of ice cream; stir until melted.
Yield: about 1 gallon.

title: white chip orange dream cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt in small bowl. Beat butter, sugar and brown sugar in large bowl until creamy. Beat in egg and orange peel. Slowly beat in flour mixture. Stir in morsels. Drop dough by tablespoon onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Let stand 2 minutes before removing.

title: california bundt cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients well. Add oil, vanilla, eggs and pineapple.
Mix well and blend in bananas by hand.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour and test with toothpick.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: p-nut butter bars
directions: Melt butter; add 1 cup peanut butter and mix well.
Add powdered sugar and graham cracker crumbs.
Mix well.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan; cool.

title: chinese spaghetti
directions: Boil 1 pound spaghetti.
Brown bacon, onion and garlic; put in a pot of water with cabbage.
Cover cabbage with water and steam. Drain spaghetti; mix with cabbage and serve with soy sauce.

title: brownies
directions: Mix in mixer, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and salt. Mix well.
Melt and add to mixer, squares of chocolate and the butter.
Mix and add chopped pecans.
Spread in jelly roll pan, 10 x 15-inch.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chili dip
directions: Heat in microwave until cheese is melted and mixture is warm. Serve with Fritos or tortilla chips.

title: rhubarb and fig preserves
directions: Cut rhubarb in small pieces.
Add sugar and let stand overnight.
In the morning, boil until thick over medium flame. Add chopped figs and sliced lemon.
Cook rapidly for 20 to 30 minutes.
Pack into hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Pour can of cream of asparagus soup over mixture.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.	Remove from oven and sprinkle 1 can onion
rings
on
top;
bake until onion rings are brown. Watch closely to avoid overbrowning onion rings.

title: not edible oatmeal dough
directions: Or use 1 part flour, 2 parts oatmeal and 1 part water.

title: salmon patties
directions: Chop salmon into small chunks and remove bones. Add egg and stir. Add enough crackers to make mixture stick together. Fry on low heat until brown.

title: party pizza
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add other ingredients and simmer until cheese melts.
Spread on English muffin halves and heat until muffins are hot.

title: apricot slush
directions: Mix together and freeze.
Serve with 7-Up.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, water and Karo on high until it threads or 300° on candy thermometer.
Then add 2 or 3 cups of raw peanuts.
Turn heat to medium until peanuts are parched or the color of peanut butter. Take off heat and add salt, butter and soda.
Stir for 1 minute, then pour into a large cookie pan which has been buttered well.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Layer chips, nuts and coconut in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix German chocolate cake as directed on box.
Pour cake mixture on top of chips, nuts and coconut.
Mix powdered sugar, oleo and cream cheese.
Mix in mixer.
Drop mixture by teaspoon on top of cake mixture. Bake at 350° in oven for 1 hour or until springs back to touch or tests clean on toothpick. Cake will crack much like an earthquake when done.

title: monster cookies
directions: Bake at 350 degrees for 12 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: vegetable casserole(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Cook frozen vegetables according to directions.
Cook celery and onion in 1/2 cup of water until tender.
Drain all vegetables well and cool.
Mix mayonnaise and cheese together.
Add vegetables and pour into greased casserole.
Top vegetables with crackers and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese pie
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients until smooth.
Put in greased 8-inch Pyrex pie plate.
Bake for 50 minutes in a 325° oven.
Cool for 20 minutes, then beat next 3 ingredients together.
Pour over pie and bake for 15 minutes at 320°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Peel, quarter and boil sweet potatoes until soft.
Drain liquid and mash, adding milk as needed.
Add the egg and brown sugar.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Crush sugared cereal. Sprinkle over top to cover evenly, enough for a good crust.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 325° until set.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all together.
Refrigerate 8 to 12 hours.
Stir often.

title: cajun onion soup
directions: Melt butter in heavy 6-quart soup pot over medium heat.
Add onions; saute, stirring until wilted, about 20 minutes.
Sprinkle sugar over onions; stir to blend.
Increase heat to medium-high; cook, stirring, until onions are lightly browned, about 5 minutes. Reduce heat to medium.
Add flour; stir until combined.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes, stirring.
Slowly stir in broths.
Bring to a boil to thicken slightly.
Reduce heat.
Season with salt and pepper; simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Taste for seasoning; adjust, if necessary.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Use 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Cook sausage; drain and rinse. Butter bread on one side or melt butter and dip.
Cube bread. Layer bread in bottom of casserole.
Sprinkle sausage over bread. Sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Combine eggs, milk and mustard; stir.
Pour over mix.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 to 12 hours (as long as 24 hours).
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve with a fresh salad, crescent rolls and orange juice, if desired.

title: soft gingersnaps
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar. Add molasses or syrup and egg. Beat. Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon, cloves and ginger. Add to oleo, sugar and molasses mixture; mix well. Roll into small balls. Roll in sugar. Place 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes. DO NOT OVERBAKE!
Makes 4 dozen.

title: basic easy crust
directions: In medium bowl, stir together the flour and salt.
Using a pastry blender, cut in the margarine and shortening.
Keep working the flour and shortening until the mixture is rather grainy, like coarse cornmeal.
Mix the egg and vinegar together and, using a wooden fork, stir the mixture into the flour.
Mix enough of the ice water so that the dough barely holds together.
Place on a marble pastry board or a plastic countertop and knead for just a few turns, enough so that the dough holds together and becomes rollable.
Makes a top and bottom crust.

title: tater beef bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown ground beef in pan.
Add salt, pepper, soup and chili powder; cook for 5 minutes.
Pour beef mixture into bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Layer Tater Tots and corn on top of beef.
Bake for 20 minutes.
A couple of minutes before you take out of oven, you can sprinkle cheese on top.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Melt first 4 ingredients in a saucepan.
Place frozen hash browns in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour cheese mixture over potatoes and bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine brown sugar, syrup, butter and salt in 2-quart dish. Cook on High 2 minutes or until boiling.
Remove and stir in baking soda.

title: cherry surprise
directions: Layer a 9 x 13-inch pan with crushed pineapple.
Next layer cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle cake mix on top of filling.
Sprinkle on walnuts.
Cut the sticks of butter on top.
Bake 45 minutes to an hour at 350°.
Check middle of cake to see if done.

title: raisin carrot nut bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients, except sugar.
Combine sugar, eggs and oil.
Add to flour mixture; mix well.
Add carrot, raisins and nuts; blend lightly.
Pour into greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan; carefully smooth top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Cool 5 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool before slicing.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: buster bar dessert
directions: For the topping, mix powdered sugar, evaporated milk, chocolate chips and margarine; bring to a boil. Boil for 8 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add vanilla.

title: curry chicken with broccoli
directions: Place chicken in shallow baking dish.
Top with broccoli.
Mix together soup, Miracle Whip, lemon juice and curry.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Melt margarine and mix in herb crumbs, sprinkle over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy sukkot apple kugel
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray an 8x8-inch baking dish very lightly with a nonstick cooking spray.

title: 5-cup salad
directions: Mix together well and chill.
Best made 6 to 8 hours in advance.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: retreat chocolate brownies
directions: Put sifted flour and sugar in a bowl and set aside.
Melt margarine, oil, cocoa, water and bring to a boil.
Pour this over dry mixture and beat.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla. Beat together.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400 degrees on a greased and floured 12x17-inch jelly roll pan.
Top with the following:

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Beat together.
Pour into tube pan and bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef (drain), onions and bell peppers.
Pour in beans.
Cook slow 2 to 3 hours.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add brown sugar.

title: squash casserole
directions: Pour 1/2 stuffing into casserole dish.
Combine margarine, soup, sour cream and squash.
Pour over stuffing mix.
Top with cheese.
Put remaining stuffing on top.
Put other half of margarine on top in small pats.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: gertrude flechinger's cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream the butter and cream cheese until smooth.
Add flour, one cup at a time, and mix until smooth.
Roll out on a floured table until paper thin.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Put about 1/4 to 1/2 teaspoon prune or plum butter in center of square.
Fold closed.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: rivels
directions: Mix until crumbly; drop into chicken broth (4 cups broth).

title: chicken chili
directions: Heat oil in a large heavy pot over high heat.
Add garlic, red pepper, green pepper and onions; saute 5 minutes.
Add chili powder, cumin and cayenne; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Add tomatoes, breaking them up with a spoon.
Add broth and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in kidney beans, chicken, salsa and corn.
Cover, increase heat to high and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium and simmer for 5 minutes or until chicken is cooked through.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.
Freezes well.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix ingredients until light and fluffy.
Add 7-Up.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: pear butter (preserves)
directions: Pare and chop pears.
Measure pear slices.
Add 1/2 cup sugar to 1 cup pear pulp.
Add 1 teaspoon cinnamon to 3 cups pulp.
Cook until tender.
Put into sterilized jars and seal.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Mix well all ingredients, except coconut.
Then stir in coconut.
Pour into 9-inch glass pie plate (greased and floured). Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Don't allow to get too dry.

title: two tone bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, shortening, salt and milk.
Mix and then add 3 cups white flour. Beat.
Divide in half. Stir in enough white flour to make a stiff dough.
To the other, add molasses and enough wheat flour to make a dough. Knead both doughs well and let rise until doubled. Roll out both doughs to a 12 x 8-inch rectangle.
Place dark atop light. Cut in half and roll up, placing in a greased loaf pan.
Let rise until doubled, then bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: crunchy apple crisp
directions: Put pie filling in shallow, 1-quart baking dish.
In a bowl, combine oats, flour, spices and sugar.
Cut in butter and mix well.
Spread topping evenly over apples.
Bake in 375° oven about 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: honey perch
directions: In shallow bowl, beat egg.
Add honey.
In a plastic bag, combine crackers and salt. Dip fish in egg mixture, then shake in bag.
Cook fish in skillet with oil for 3 to 5 minutes per side of fillet or until golden. Serve with lemon, if desired.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple (don't drain).
Fold in Cool Whip, nuts, oranges and mini marshmallows.
Make a day ahead.

title: cousin ina's fudge peanut oaties
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and boil 1 minute.
Add immediately to peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Stir well and drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: moist banana bread
directions: Cream together in medium sized mixing bowl the margarine, sugar, eggs, baking powder soda and salt.
Beat on high speed until very well creamed.
Add bananas and mix well.
Add flour and mix on low speed until just well mixed.
Fold in the nuts with a spoon.
Pour into a greased loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3 inches.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.
Cool on rack. If you don't have quite 1 cup bananas, use evaporated milk to fill the cup.

title: baby ruth cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Beat in egg.
Cut Baby Ruth bars into small pieces; stir into creamed mixture, as well as other remaining ingredients.
Chill and drop in half teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderately hot oven (375°) for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 50 to 75 cookies.

title: mustard sauce
directions: In a small glass mixing bowl, combine egg yolks with salt and pepper.
Add vinegar and beat.
Add half of oil slowly while beating with mixer.
Beat in lemon juice and remaining half of oil.
Add mustard.
Mixture thickens as you beat.

title: fantastic fruit salad
directions: Combine fruit cocktail and sour cream; mix well.
Chill until ready to serve.
Fill lettuce cups.

title: christmas melt-aways
directions: Beat sugar replacement, cream of tartar, salt and flavoring into egg whites.
Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan right away.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts for 1/2 hour.
Remove and cool.
Debone and slice chicken.
In same water, boil broccoli; drain and place in greased casserole.
Place sliced chicken on top.
