Melt soup; add a little cream to thin and pour over chicken and broccoli. Garnish with capers, shaved almonds or paprika.
Bake 1/2 hour or until bubbly on top.

title: grandmother's oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine eggs, vanilla and raisins and let stand 1 hour.
Cream sugars and shortening.
Add flour with seasonings.
Add oatmeal and nuts, then blend in egg mixture.
Push dough from a large tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with hand.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until very slightly browned.
Do not overbake.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble sausage in skillet.
Cook over medium heat until done. Drain well.
Spread bread cubes in a buttered 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with sausage, then cheese.
Combine eggs, milk and salt; beat well and pour over sausage and cheese.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until set.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: holupky
directions: Coat meat with seasoned flour and brown in hot oil.
Reduce heat to medium low.
Drain off all but 1 tablespoon of drippings. Add onions, carrots, potatoes and celery to pot.
Cook about 5 minutes, stirring once in a while until lightly browned.
Add broth, tomato paste and mustard, stirring to scrape up browned bits.
Bring to a boil.
Return browned meat to pot.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 hour, stirring once.
Correct seasoning if needed.
Cook 1 hour longer until meat is tender and sauce is thickened.

title: strawberry pretzel pie
directions: Toss pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar and melted margarine in bowl.
Press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Cream remaining 3/4 cup sugar and cream cheese in mixer bowl until light.
Blend in whipped topping.
Spread over cooled layer.
Chill.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling pineapple juice in bowl.
Stir in strawberries.
Chill until partially set.
Spoon over cream cheese layer.
Chill until set.
Yields 12.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Microwave margarine, onions and celery until tender.
Add cooked rice, soup, mushrooms and Cheez Whiz.
Add drained broccoli.
Pour into greased casserole or crock-pot.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in crock-pot.
Serves 12.

title: pastry for quiche crust
directions: Stir salt into flour.
Cut shortening into dry ingredients until crumbly and size of peas.
Sprinkle milk over flour and shortening mixture, stirring lightly with fork to blend.
Don't overmix.
Shape into 2 balls with hands.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll out, using as little flour as possible.
(Use pastry cloth and rolling pin cover to prevent sticking.)
Place crust in pan, pressing firmly around edge.
Do not stretch crust but rather ease it in so that the crust doesn't shrink away from side of pan while baking. Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.

title: cranberry cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, baking powder, butter and vanilla. Roll fruit in flour. Add flour and milk. Grate rind of 3 oranges. Add to mixture. Put cake mix in greased cake pan. Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until golden brown.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Cook spinach according to directions.
Drain very dry.
Fry bacon and onions together until onions are tender, about 10 minutes.
Add flour, seasoned salt, pepper and garlic.
Blend thoroughly.
Slowly add milk; cook and stir until thickened.
Add spinach and mix thoroughly. Serves 4.

title: cream wafers
directions: Mix butter, cream and flour thoroughly.
Chill 1 hour.
Heat oven to 375°.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured board. Cut into 1 1/2-inch rounds.
Transfer to waxed paper heavily sprinkled with sugar.
Turn to coat both sides.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Prick in 4 places with fork.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes until slightly puffy.
Cool.
Sandwich with cream filling.

title: meat loaf
directions: Saute the onion in a little oleo.
In a large bowl, mix stuffing mix, bouillon, ground meat, parsley, Parmesan, egg, salt and pepper. Blend and form into a loaf pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Pour tomato sauce and oregano over meat loaf and return to the oven to bake 20 minutes longer.

title: tomato soup
directions: Blend arrowroot and water.
Put in pot and add pureed tomatoes and salt; bring to a boil for 3 to 4 minutes to cook arrowroot. Stir in 2 cups hot soy or nut milk. Keep from curdling.
Makes 4 to 5 cups.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Saute celery, onion and bell pepper.
Brown ground chuck in skillet. Add garlic salt, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix these ingredients together in oblong baking dish. Drain corn.
Now add cooked macaroni, corn and tomato sauce and more spices to taste. Grate cheese and mix half of the cheese in with ingredients.
Use the other half of the cheese to top casserole. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cheese is golden brown on top.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Layer pork chops in large baking dish.
Slice potatoes and layer on pork chops.
Layer onions, if used.
Repeat procedure until all ingredients are used.
Cover and bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip date cake
directions: Mix, in a bowl, dates and hot water; let cool.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Gradually add sifted flour and baking soda.
Add date mixture, vanilla and 1/2 package chocolate chips.

title: pot pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add onions and flour; cook over low heat.
Add milk and broth.
Heat thoroughly.
Add turkey or chicken and vegetable mix; pour into deep dish crust.
Cover with another crust.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: banana split
directions: Crust:
Mix 1 cube melted margarine and cracker crumbs and press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: tart cherry salad
directions: Drain fruits, reserve juices to make 1 5/8 cups.
Stir in sugar.
Bring to boil, stir in gelatin until it is dissolved.
Add fruit and ginger ale.
Chill until very thick, but not set.
Stir in nuts or coconut.
Pour in large ring mold.
Chill until set.

title: rhubarberry sauce
directions: Wash strawberries and remove stems.
Heat water to boiling in a pan on medium-high heat.
Add the rhubarb and sugar.
Reduce heat.
Simmer for 5 minutes, stirring with fork to break rhubarb apart.
Remove from heat.
Stir in strawberries and ginger.
Serve warm or cold.

title: chicken specialty casserole
directions: Combine soups (undiluted), mushrooms (drained), milk, water chestnuts (drained) and pimentos.
Add additional seasonings, if desired.
Spoon into a 3-quart casserole dish; cover with cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: knoll stew
directions: Brown onions in oil with meat.
Combine flour, salt, pepper and thyme; add to meat.
Stir in cider and ketchup.
Cover; cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours.
Add more liquid.
Add potatoes and carrots; simmer 1 hour.

title: rich cranberry coffee cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, butter, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Combine 2 cups flour, baking powder and salt; gradually add to butter mixture.
Mix remaining flour with cranberries and nuts.
Fold into batter.
Batter will be very thick.
Spoon into a greased 10-inch fluted tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes or until cake tests done.
Let stand 5 minutes before removing from the pan.
Cool on a wire rack.
Before serving, dust with confectioners sugar.
Great dessert!

title: picante sauce
directions: Boil to consistency desired.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: potato deluxe casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes for 1/2 hour.
Mix with rest of ingredients except potato chips.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with crushed chips or cereal.
Cover with foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: syrup cake
directions: Mix all ingredients using a fork to blend - DO no use electric mixer.
Bake
in greased baking pan.
350° about 30 minutes or until done.

title: delicious pudding
directions: Cream butter with sugar; add egg.
Beat well.
Stir in flour mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add nuts and fruit.
Pour into a 3-quart Pyrex bowl and steam, uncovered, in a heavy kettle with tight fitting lid for 1 1/2 hours.
No peeking!
Be sure water is at least 2 inches up sides of bowl.
Serve with Vanilla Sauce.

title: mexican pie
directions: In saucepan, heat Mexican Meat and beans.
In deep dish glass pie dish, layer with tortilla chips and layer of cheese.
When meat and bean mixture is boiling, pour over chips.
Top with another layer of chips and cheese.
Garnish with sliced jalapenos and bake in 450° oven (preheated) until cheese is melted.
Serve with side dish of corn.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over remaining ingredients.
Keep refrigerated.

title: mystery rolls
directions: Mix ingredients by hand and spoon in hot greased muffin pan. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 6 large or 12 small rolls.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak bread crumbs in scalded milk in bowl for 5 minutes.
Add sugar substitute, cinnamon and raisins.
Mix well. Pour bread mixture over eggs in bowl. Stir in vanilla.
Pour into buttered baking dish. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Crumble raw ground beef and spread to cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Season with salt and pepper, if desired.
Add a thin layer of sliced onion.
Layer frozen vegetables over meat and onion.
Spread 2 cans cream of chicken soup over vegetables. Cover with cheese slices.
Top with frozen Tater Tots.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: banana punch
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil on medium heat.
Let cool.
Add all ingredients except ginger ale.
Put into containers and freeze. Take out 5 hours before serving.
Add cold ginger ale.
Good for summer parties or to serve at wedding receptions.
Makes 2 1/2 gallons.

title: grape dumplings
directions: Mix flour and salt. Cut in shortening. Add enough water to make a good dough. Roll out on floured board to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut in 1-inch squares. Drop squares, one at a time into boiling juice and cook until dough is done.

title: 7 layer taco dip
directions: Layer in order listed.

title: layered salad
directions: Place vegetables as listed in bowl.
Spread mayonnaise over the top of salad.
Sprinkle cheese over mayonnaise.
Chill overnight.

title: ice cream with chocolate
directions: Melt chocolate and marshmallows. Cool.
On top of chocolate, line pan with 1/4 of ice cream. Add layer of Nestle and marshmallows.
Alternate mixture.
Refreeze. Cut in squares to serve.

title: honey mustard chicken breasts
directions: Mix low-fat mayonnaise, mustard

and honey until well blended. Place chicken breasts in baking pan. Brush chicken with honey mustard mixture and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Turn chicken breasts over and brush with honey mustard mixture. Continue baking another 20 to 30 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar.
Add melted margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in unbaked pie crust at 375° for 45 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: yummy french bread
directions: Cut French bread loaves lengthwise.
Cover each section generously with a garlic butter spread.
Put slices of Swiss cheese on top.
Next, sprinkle dill weed and garlic powder on top of cheese.
Wrap in foil and heat slowly in oven about 20 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together, except cheese and almonds.
Place in casserole. Top with grated Cheddar cheese and slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Softened cream cheese.
Mix with other ingredients and chill. Serve with crackers or pita chips.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Mix chuck, oregano, 1 small can tomato sauce, salt, pepper, eggs and crumbs.
Flatten in an oblong shape.
On top of meat loaf, put the 1 cup of Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese, then roll up like a jelly roll, tuck or pinch edges together and press top seam closed.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Take out and put 1 small can of tomato sauce and 1 cup of Mozzarella cheese on top.
Cover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix
flour,
cocoa,
baking powder and soda; set aside. Beat sugar, eggs and vanilla well. Add half the flour and half milk; mix well.
Mix rest of the flour and milk well.
Fill a greased and
floured baking pan or 2 layer pans.
Bake at 375° for 25
or 35	minutes
until	cake springs back when lightly touched near center.

title: flop cake
directions: Mix together.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 3-inch greased and floured baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until soft peaks form.
Add sugar gradually, beating well after each addition.
Beat until stiff and glossy.
Beat egg yolks and vanilla until thick and lemon colored. Add to egg whites and fold in gently but quickly.
Fold in flour.

title: punch for a crowd
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and store in container in refrigerator.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.
Great for Christmas!

title: quick southwestern pizza
directions: Move oven rack to lowest position.
Heat oven to 450°.
Grease cookie sheet or 12-inch pizza pan.
Mix baking mix and water; beat vigorously for 20 strokes.
Turn onto floured surface; knead about 60 times or until no longer sticky.
Press onto pan.
Mix chicken and salsa.
Sprinkle crust with 1 cup cheese.
Top with onion, chicken mixture and pepper.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes, or until crust is brown and cheese is bubbly.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together except strawberries.
Fold in strawberries and add enough strawberry juice (about 1/4 cup) to make good batter consistency.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in a pound loaf pan or bake for 45 minutes in 4 small loaf pans.

title: caramel dip for fruit
directions: Boil gently the entire can(s) Eagle Brand in water, covered, for 3 hours.
Contents will caramelize to a golden brown inside. Open.
Serve and enjoy.

title: asian greens
directions: This dish will probably need to be done in at least 3 batches, depending on the size of your wok or pot. Divide the ingredients proportionally for each batch. Saut the garlic and ginger in oil on medium heat for 1 or 2 minutes. Add the greens and stir-fry for 1 minute. Add the remaining ingredients, except the soy or fish sauce. Continue to stir-fry until the greens are tender. Toss the soy or fish sauce with the greens right before serving.

title: prune cake
directions: Combine sugar and oil.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Sift together flour, allspice, cinnamon, nutmeg, soda and salt.
Alternate dry ingredients with buttermilk into batter.
Add nuts and prunes. Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and combine juice with the sugars, cranberries, raisins and spices.
Cook 15 minutes or until boiling. Reduce heat and simmer 25 to 30 minutes or until cranberries are tender.
Add the pineapple and nuts.
Mix well.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours or until chilled.
(Each serving has about 338 calories, no cholesterol, 7 grams fat, 4 milligrams sodium.)

title: orange float mix
directions: Combine ingredients in a large bowl.
Blend well.
Put in a large airtight container.
Label.
Store in a cool, dry place. Use within 6 months.
Makes about 7 cups.

title: coffee punch
directions: Mix coffee, chocolate milk and white milk together.
Cut ice cream into small chunks and pour mixture over ice cream.
Stir until desired consistency is reached.
Serves 40 cups.

title: chicken salad
directions: Whip cream and put in salad dressing. Pour over chicken and vegetables. Before serving, add shoestring potatoes and peas.

title: lover's wedding cake
directions: Put flour of love, good looks and sweet temper into a well furnished house.
Mix together the blindness to faults, self-forgetfulness, dry humor, gentle arguments and powdered wit. Add to above.
Pour in rippling laughter and common sense.
Work until well mixed, then bake gently in the warm oven of the heart forever.
Recipe for a couple getting married.

title: garlic potatoes
directions: Fix Hungry Jack potatoes for 12 people as directed on box, using 1/4 cup less water than what it calls for.

title: wreath cake(kransekake)
directions: Beat butter until light and fluffy.
Sift powdered sugar and gradually add to butter.
Beat in egg yolks.
Stir in flour, flavoring and almonds.
Beat until smooth.
Put dough in a cookie press, using no cookie tip.
Press out into well-greased and floured rings.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Turn over to remove and cool.
Frost as desired, using almond flavored butter icing.
Stack rings one on top of the other to make a graduated tower (largest to smallest).

title: ranch oyster crackers
directions: Whisk together the first 5 ingredients.
Pour over crackers, stirring to coat.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 275° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: strawberry tartlets
directions: Sweeten the Petit Suisse with sugar.
Add the vanilla and spread a little in the bottom of each pastry shell.
Wash the strawberries if necessary and remove the hulls.
Set a whole berry on top of each tartlet.
Warm the red currant jelly with the squeeze of lemon juice and brush over the tartlets.

title: "kaak naim" - egyptian cookies
directions: Heat butter to boiling and skim it.
Mix flour and sesame seed; add hot butter to the mixture.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 water and sugar.
Add yeast to mixture.
Dissolve salt in remaining water (for blessing) and add to the dough.
Knead until smooth. Roll out dough into pie-shaped circle and cut with a cookie cutter and design each one with a fork or special tweezers.
Bake at 375° until golden; cool for 1 hour and cover cookies with powdered sugar.

title: tender marshmallows
directions: Lightly butter a 9-inch square baking pan; set aside.
In a small bowl, combine gelatin and cold water.
Stir with a spoon until very thick.
Allow to stand 5 minutes.
In 2-quart saucepan, combine hot water, 1/2 cup corn syrup and sugar.
Place over high heat and stir with wooden spoon until mixture comes to a boil.
If sugar crystals are present, wash off with wet pastry brush.
Cook to 238° or soft-ball stage.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining corn syrup.
Pour into medium bowl and mix at high speed, adding gelatin mixture 1 tablespoon at a time.
Continue until candy is thick and has cooled to lukewarm, about 10 minutes.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into prepared pan.
Cool 3 hours or until marshmallow is firm enough to cut.
Using knife dipped in hot water, cut marshmallows into pieces about 1 3/4-inch square.
Roll cut marshmallows in powdered sugar to prevent sticking.
Makes about 25 pieces.

title: hot spiced punch
directions: Keep warm on stove.
Will make your house smell good.

title: aunt e's cheese nibbles
directions: *Aunt E. uses Kraft very sharp Cheddar cheese.

title: out of this world salad
directions: In pan combine the sugar, cornstarch, red food coloring and juice from the pineapple.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Stir until the jello is dissolved.
Add the pie filling, pineapple chunks, pecans and sliced bananas.
Chill well before serving.
Store in refrigerator.

title: fourth of july cinnamon sticky buns
directions: Combine and heat.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: tortilla rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread on large flour tortillas.
Roll tortilla and cut crosswise into 1/2-inch pieces. Serve with picante sauce.

title: ranch pasta and turkey
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package. In a saucepan, combine margarine, dressing mix, peas and carrots. Heat until margarine has melted. Toss with pasta and turkey. Place in a 2-quart casserole. Heat at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: dill and sour cream potato salad
directions: Cook unpeeled potatoes in salted, boiling water to cover, 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain and let cool to touch.
Leaving skins on, cut potatoes into eighths.
Place into large bowl. Combine mayonnaise and next 5 ingredients; add to potatoes.
Toss gently.
Cover and chill for 8 hours.

title: sausage stuffed shells
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add chopped onion, parsley, bread crumbs, beaten egg and milk into meat.
Stuff mixture into cooked shells. Drizzle sauce over top.
Add cheese on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: party punch
directions: Mix jello as on package, then add sugar.
Add frozen lemonade and orange juice with water they call for on cans.
Add pineapple juice.
Chill.
Before serving, add ginger ale and sherbet.

title: chop suey cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening. Add eggs, then flour and salt alternately with milk.
Mix well. Add all other ingredients.
Mix thoroughly. Drop on greased pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches into a 10-inch pie pan.
Mix sugar, flour and egg and pour on top of peaches. Dot with butter and bake at 400° until brown, about 20 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel apples; cut each into 8 parts.
Separate each biscuit into 3 parts.
Wrap a piece of biscuit around each apple slice and place in a buttered baking dish.
Bring water, sugar and margarine to a boil; pour over apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken corn stew(lo-cal)
directions: Melt margarine; add chicken parts and brown on all sides.
Add remaining ingredients except corn; cover and cook until chicken is tender (about 35 minutes).
Add corn and cook until heated through, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples, sugar and nuts and let stand for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally so it makes a juice.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Add to apple mixture.
Bake in tube pan at 350° until done.

title: kabak tatlisi(pumpkin dessert)
directions: Peel the pumpkin, slice into pieces 3 inches long and 1/3 inch wide.
Wash well and line up in a wide pan.
Put in enough water to reach to the lower half of the pumpkins, then cover and cook on moderate heat until they are tender.
When approximately half a glass of water is left in the pan, sprinkle the sugar over.
After the steam of the pan has melted the sugar, uncover the pan. Remove from heat after the sugar thickens and allow to cool. Place on a serving plate, sprinkle ground walnuts over and serve.

title: pirishki
directions: Mix the first 4 items together and roll out.
Cut into 4 to 5-inch squares.
Place a tablespoon of cut-up apples on the dough. On the apples, put a teaspoon of sugar.
Pinch sides together and bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Do not brown meat.
Mix all ingredients well.
Cover and bake 4 hours at 300°.
Yield:
8 servings.
Carbohydrate 24 g, protein 23 g, fat 20 g, calories 368.
One serving = 3 meat medium fat exchange, 1 bread starch exchange, 1 vegetable exchange, 1 fat exchange.

title: oven "fried" potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Pat dry with paper towels.
Do not peel.
Cut each potato in half lengthwise; cut each half into five wedges. Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray cookie sheet with nonstick cooking spray.
Place potato wedges, cut side down, on cookie sheet. Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Bake 15 minutes; turn wedges.
Sprinkle with additional salt and pepper.
Bake 15 minutes longer or until wedges are golden and fork-tender.

title: veal scallopini
directions: Pound veal cutlets with a meat mallet until very thin. Lightly sprinkle with pepper and arrowroot starch.
Melt margarine in a large skillet.
Add cutlets and saute until broth sides are browned, but do not burn.
Transfer cutlets to a covered baking dish.
Add wine and tarragon to pan juices.
Cook over medium heat until liquid is reduced by half.
Pour over veal cutlets.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: sugar coated nuts
directions: Whisk egg whites with sugar and coat nuts with mixture.
Melt butter on cookie sheet.
Spread nuts on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Stir nuts and bake 10 minutes more.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Make pastry for 2-crust pie or mix up a batch of drop biscuits.
Cook onion in butter until tender, but not browned. Stir in flour and salt.
Add broth all at once.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add the remaining ingredients.

title: quick cheeseburger bake
directions: Preparation Time: 12 minutes.
Baking Time: 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken and soup together.
Put into casserole.
Cover with grated cheese.
Top with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together and drain.
Mix together in mixer the soup, sour cream and carrot.
Add squash and beat again. Make crust out of cornbread mix and butter.
Put cornbread mix on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican salad
directions: Brown meat; add onion.
Cook until tender.
Stir in beans, Catalina dressing, water and chili powder.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: coffee punch
directions: Mix coffee, milk and vanilla.
Add ice cream.
Save some ice cream to float on top.
Serves about 30.

title: taco salad
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and taco sauce.
Spread in middle of a plate.
On top layer, put other ingredients.
Put tortilla chips on the plate around the salad.
Dip chips into salad.
Enjoy.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix melted margarine and graham crumbs.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix margarine, powdered sugar and eggs 15 minutes until thick.
Pour over crumb crust.
Slice bananas over layer. Drain pineapple; pour over banana layer.
Over all, make a layer of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle nuts and place maraschino cherry on each serving.
Refrigerate couple of hours.

title: creamy broccoli soup
directions: Heat 2 cups water to boiling in 3-quart saucepan.
Add broccoli flowerets and pieces, celery and onion.
Cover and heat to boiling.
Boil until tender, about 10 minutes; do not drain. Place in blender container.
Cover and blend until of uniform consistency.

title: taffy apples (cookies)(makes 72 cookies)
directions: Use pastry blender to blend ingredients.
Blend flour and sugar.
Cut in margarine
and yolks.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Place toothpicks in center of each ball right from oven.
Let cool.
Melt caramels and milk in double boiler.
Dip balls into melted caramel 3/4 of the way.
Then dip in nuts.
Set on wax paper until caramel hardens.

title: pea salad
directions: You will need a medium casserole dish.

title: seafood shells
directions: Defrost patty shells as directed.
Cook frozen vegetables as directed.
Stir in soup and fish.
Heat through and serve on shells.

title: very easy red velvet cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix together all ingredients with an electric mixer.
Spray three 9-inch cake pans with nonstick coating.
Pour batter equally into the three pans; bake for 20 minutes.
Cool layers in pans on wire racks for 10 minutes. Carefully remove layers from pans to rack to cool completely.

title: california chicken casserole
directions: In a bowl, combine soup and milk.
Stir in vegetables, chicken, 1 1/4 cups cheese, pimentos, salt and pepper.
Transfer to a greased 9-inch square baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Uncover; top with remaining cheese and bake 5 to 10 minutes longer or until bubbly.
Let stand for 5 minutes. Serve over rice.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: barbecued baby back pork ribs in honey, tamari and orange marinade
directions: Place rib racks in a large glass baking dish.
Pour marinade over; refrigerate, covered, 24 to 48 hours. Turn ribs several times.
Remove ribs from marinade and place in one layer on rack of broiler pan, reserving marinade.
If ribs do not fit on broiler pan, bake in 2 batches.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated moderate oven at 350° for 40 minutes, basting several times.
Preheat grill. Grill rib racks, covered, over medium-high fire for 20 to 30 minutes, basting with reserved marinade and turning frequently to prevent burning.
Ribs should be glazed brown and tender.
Carve into individual ribs to serve.
Makes 4 servings at $2.63 each.

title: fudge
directions: Mix together sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil for 8 minutes. Then add chocolate, marshmallow cream, pecans and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into buttered pan.
Allow to cool before slicing.

title: chocolate boiled oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine to full boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper. Cool.

title: beef stroganoff(makes 50 servings, 4 ounces each)
directions: Cut meat in 1 1/2 x 1/2-inch strips, flour thoroughly, and brown in hot fat.
Add sliced onions and mushrooms.
Saute 5 minutes.
Add other ingredients, except sour cream.
Cover and simmer slowly for 1 1/2 hours, or until meat is tender.
Add sour cream and heat thoroughly.
Do not boil.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: reese's cup cake
directions: Put margarine, cocoa, buttermilk, water and eggs together; bring all these almost to a boil (do not boil).
Add sugar, flour and vanilla; beat well.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.

title: super burger sandwiches
directions: In 10-inch skillet, cook beef and onion until browned and onion is tender.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup, mustard and pepper. Reduce heat to low.
Heat through, stirring occasionally. Serve on buns.

title: egg stew
directions: Place 1/2 tablespoon oil in a skillet over low heat. Add chopped onions and cook until onions begin to turn a golden brown. Add shrimp and mushrooms.

Continue to cook for about 3 minutes. Remove from skillet and drain on paper towel. Combine water, shrimp, onions, mushrooms, parsley, salt and pepper (to taste) in a saucepan. Cook over low heat for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: aunt bee's apple pie
directions: In large bowl, combine 1/2 cup of butter or oil and the cream cheese and let come to room temperature.
Add 2 cups flour and blend well.
Chill.
Roll out half of the dough and place in a 9-inch pie plate.
Reserve the remaining dough for the top crust.

title: "eat your heart out charlie" tuna salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; place in serving bowl.
Chill; garnish top with paprika.
Serve instead of lettuce salad with meals.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and condensed milk; add lemonade.
Pour into precooked and cooled pie shell.
Place in refrigerator overnight.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Pour mixture of the first 5 ingredients into lightly greased casserole.
Break the bread; place on top of pineapple.
Slice the margarine or butter over bread.
Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes.

title: pork tenderloins with orange pepper sauce
directions: Cut pork into 1/4-inch thick. Dust lightly with flour. Melt butter; add pork. Brown on both sides, making sure it is cooked all the way through. Take pork out of pan. Set aside.

title: pink arctic freeze
directions: Beat cream cheese, mayonnaise and sugar with electric mixer. Add cranberry sauce and pineapple.
Mix well.
Fold in whipped cream.
Freeze in a 9 x 9-inch dish.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: healthy turkey chili
directions: Add olive oil and onion in a 2-quart pan.
Saute 2 minutes on medium heat, add turkey.
Saute until turkey is all opaque.
Add rest of ingredients; stir.
Cook over medium heat for 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Serve with croutons or crackers.
Yields 4 servings.

title: california carrot cake
directions: In large bowl, cream sugar, vegetable oil, eggs and vanilla together and beat well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour batter into 3 well-greased 9-inch cake pans or 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: all-purpose dipping sauce and marinade
directions: Mix and store in refrigerator.

title: impossible crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients and pat into patties.
Roll into flour (or corn meal) and fry.

title: yogurt cream frosting
directions: Blend cream cheese and yogurt until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill before using.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Cook the cranberries in 3 cups water for about 5 minutes (until skins pop open) and strain.
In another pan, cook sugar and 4 cups hot water for 5 minutes and let cool.
Add orange and lemon juice; mix in cranberry juice.
Chill.
Just before serving, add 1 quart of ginger ale.
Put in punch bowl.
Slice bananas into punch bowl.
Makes about 25 cups.
It takes 7 1/2 cups of cranberry mixture for each quart of ginger ale.

title: champagne salad
directions: Mix sugar and cream cheese.
Add thawed strawberries, then Cool Whip.
Right before serving, slice and add bananas.

title: old timey tea cakes
directions: Sift flour into mixing bowl.
Make well.
Add rest of ingredients and mix with hand until you have stiff dough.
Roll thin and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.
Cookies will be crisp and will hold their shape.

title: pinto beans
directions: Put all ingredients in large pot; fill 3/4 way with water. Cook on high for 4 hrs. You may need to add water.

title: michele's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Soak beans for about 2 hours.
Cook beans in medium size pot until tender. Chop all vegetables.
Keep separate.
Saute in vegetable oil the onion, bell pepper, garlic and carrots.
Chop canned tomatoes a little and add to beans along with sauteed carrots, onion, bell pepper
and garlic.
Add chili powder, pepper, cumin and salt. Let simmer 20 minutes.
Add broccoli. Serve with cornbread or spicy hot cheese cornbread and rice.

title: lemon cheese icing
directions: Boil all ingredients except eggs until mixture bubbles. Then slowly add egg yolks. Beat until ready to spread.

title: baked tomatoes with mushroom topping
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove to chop.
Brown chopped onion in bacon grease.
Drain.
Mix soup and milk.
Cut tomatoes in half crosswise.
Place pieces, cut side up, in casserole.
Mix bacon, onion, half the bread cubes and milk-soup mixture.
Top tomatoes with this sauce.
Sprinkle remaining bread cubes on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked french toast
directions: Measure corn flake crumbs into shallow dish.
Set aside.
In a bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Stir in a pinch of salt, milk and vanilla.
Dip bread halves into egg mixture, turning once to coat both sides.
Do not soak bread in the liquid.
Coat bread evenly on both sides with corn flake crumbs.
Place bread in a single layer on well-greased baking sheet.
Bake in oven at 400° for about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve with jelly, maple syrup or powdered sugar.

title: gibson house soup
directions: Wash beans thoroughly and place in large kettle.
Cover with water.
Add 1 tablespoon of salt and soak overnight.
In morning, drain.
Add two quarts of water and smoked turkey leg, ham or ham hocks.
Bring to boil and simmer slowly until beans are done, 3 to 3 1/2 hours.

title: fluffy apple and celery salad
directions: Mix apples, celery, pineapple and marshmallows.
Add sugar to Cool Whip.
Fold in mayonnaise, lemon juice, vanilla and nutmeats. Fold in carefully to keep salad fluffy.
Serves 10.

title: rice pudding (diabetic)
directions: Combine milk, rice, cinnamon and raisins in saucepan.
Bring to rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat; boil slowly for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Slowly pour hot mixture into eggs.
Beat well.
Add vanilla and Equal.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: szechuan nuts
directions: Mix spice seasoning, salt and water.
Add to nuts.
Stir well before adding oil. Then mix and toss well before spreading on microwave dish (leave center area open).
Cook on High 3 minutes. Stir well and leave center open.
Cook on High 5 more minutes. Cool to room temperature. Stores well.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions in oleo.
Combine cream of chicken soup, cheese, boiled broccoli, then rice.
Bake in oven at 375° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cream pies(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix Dream Whip and make as directed on package.
Add cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Whip together in mixer until smooth and put in 2 cooled pie shells.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In
a large bowl, mix together broccoli, raisins, onion and bacon.
Mix
together mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar until sugar is dissolved.	Pour over broccoli mixture.
Toss gently. Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.

title: franks 'n bacon
directions: Split franks lengthwise.
Place slices of cheese and pickle in split frankfurters.
Wrap franks with strips of lean bacon.
Fasten bacon with toothpicks.
Place on broiler rack.
Broil 6 inches from flame for about 8 to 10 minutes per side.

title: fried vegetable batter
directions: Stir the first 5 ingredients together.
Pour 1 quart of corn oil in a large skillet to 1/2 inch.
Don't fill over 1/3 full.
Dip 4 cups cut up vegetables or chicken (cut small, boneless, skinless), a few at a time, into batter.
Stir now and then.
Fry 2 or 3 minutes, turning once.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Unwrap tamales and cut into small pieces into a baking dish; spread chili over the tamales.
Sprinkle onions over chili; top with chips.
Cover and cook in the microwave for about 10 minutes. Remove from microwave and sprinkle cheese on top and let melt.

title: sausage cornbread
directions: Grease 10 1/2 inch skillet. Brown sausage and onion (drain well). In bowl mix eggs, cornmeal, milk, cream corn and oil pour 1/2 mixture in skillet, sprinkle sausage on top, pour remaining batter on top. Bake 40 -45 minutes at 425°.

title: cheesecake
directions: Crust:
Combine graham cracker crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar, cinnamon and margarine into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: biscuits
directions: In a medium bowl, mix flour and shortening together.
Add milk, a little at a time.
Roll out on a floured countertop; cut into shapes.
Place on an ungreased baking dish.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chinese cookies
directions: Melt chips over hot water.
Add balance of ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper and cool.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Slice top of bread off.
Take the middle out and break into bits.
Mix bread bits and all ingredients together.
Place in the bread.
Put top back on and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spicy oven fried potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Spray nonstick baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray.
Arrange potatoes on sheet and drizzle with
out.
Turn potatoes, coating well with oil.
Bake for 10 minutes, turn potatoes over and bake until edges are lightly browned, about 10 minutes longer.
Transfer potatoes to mixing bowl, sprinkle with spices and mix well.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Roll dough 1/8-inch thick, then paint.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well, place in loaf pan.
Cover with 2 slices bacon, over this pour 1 (8 ounce) can tomato soup.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: cheese spread
directions: Serving suggestions:
Serve on toast points or quartered toasted English muffins; slip into microwave to melt cheese.
2. Slice tops off of small hard rolls; use fork to remove inside of roll and stuff with cheese.
Wrap with waxed paper (twist ends) and warm in a 250° oven for 20 minutes.
Excellent served with corn chips.

title: glazed fresh apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add eggs and beat well. Add dry ingredients and vanilla; beat.
Add by hand apples, nuts, and raisins.
Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: bow tie pasta with roasted red and yellow peppers
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients plus 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper in a medium bowl; set aside.
Bring 6 quarts water to boil in a soup kettle.
Add 1 tablespoon salt and pasta; cook until just tender, about 9 minutes.
Drain and return pasta to the soup kettle.
Add pepper mixture and Parmesan cheese; toss to combine.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook and drain beef and pork.
Saute onion and green peppers. Stir all ingredients together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza bread
directions: Thaw bread dough and flatten.
Spread pizza sauce down the length of middle.
Spread rest of ingredients.
Bring up edges to form loaf of bread and pinch together.
Toothpicks work good to hold everything together.
Bake at 350° until bread is done.
Cut and serve hot.

title: lemon bread
directions: Blend well the butter and sugar. Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add extracts.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to egg mixture alternately with 7-Up.
Blend just enough to mix. Fold in lemon peel and nuts. Turn into greased loaf pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: fourth of july salad
directions: Mix lime jello and chill only until congealed.
Mix together in top of double boiler the marshmallows, cream cheese and orange jello (dry).
Heat until all is melted and creamy. Set aside. Whip the whipping cream. Add pineapple (liquid and all).
Add this to melted mixture in double boiler.
Put in large Pyrex dish.
Pour congealed lime jello over this.
Put in refrigerator and chill until served.

title: cheese soup
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in large saucepan.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Add milk to flour and blend well.
Add milk to vegetables and cook until thickened, stirring continuously.
Add bacon or ham.
Add cheese and stir until melted.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Crush the Doritos; put in bottom of large casserole dish.
Pour margarine over the Doritos.
Put ground beef over the Doritos and margarine.
Put both cans of refried beans over the beef.
Sprinkle over the beans with the garlic powder.
Put the onion over the beans.
Add grated cheese on top.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Saute peppers and mushrooms until soft. Drain.
Prepare frozen spinach. Drain thoroughly and mix with Ricotta cheese. Slice Mozzarella cheese into cracker size pieces.

Spread thin layer of sauce in bottom of baking pan. Add noodles, sauce, spinach mixture, vegetables, slices of Mozzarella and more sauce. Repeat layers, ending with noodles and remaining sauce. Top with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until bubbly.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in tightly sealed container.
When ready to use, mix 2 heaping teaspoonfuls per 1 cup hot water.

title: glazed raisin-cinnamon biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by rounded teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken with green rice
directions: Saute onion and celery with 1 tablespoon oleo.
Brown meat in 2 tablespoons oil.
Drain and set aside.
Mix sauteed onion, soup, milk, rice, broccoli and seasoning.
Spoon into greased casserole. Top with cheese.
Top with chicken.
Bake (uncovered) at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat, bell pepper, onion, garlic and salt.
Drain.
Mix soup, water, chilies and enchilada sauce.
Grease a large casserole dish.
Layer tortillas, meat mixture, soup mixture, and cheese layer, twice.
Let stand covered in refrigerator for 24 hours cooking.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat and add pureed fruit (1 cup).
Put in ice cream freezer and add milk to about 2-inches below top of freezer.
Freeze!

title: meat loaf
directions: Lightly mix ingredients and form a loaf.
Place in shallow pan in 350° oven.
While it is starting to bake, combine the following sauce.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain blueberries and pineapple.
Save juice.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add enough water to juices to make 1 3/4 cups; add to dissolved gelatin.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan. When gelatin is partially thickened, fold in fruit.
Chill until set.

title: rutabagas
directions: Peel, cut and boil rutabagas until done.
Drain and mash.
Add butter, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix milk, eggs, brown sugar and farina and pour over rutabagas in a buttered casserole dish. Sprinkle bread crumbs over top and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate lover's cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets.
Make golf ball size balls, 6 to a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: corned beef dinner(by coe)
directions: Cook spaghetti as per instructions; drain.
Cube corned beef. Mix soup and milk.
Add corned beef, cheese and onion; mix.
Add spaghetti.
Place in 2 quart casserole.
Sprinkle croutons on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple fritters
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Combine milk and egg (well beaten) and add to dry ingredients (beating constantly).
Dip apples in batter, spreading batter evenly over apples.
Fry in deep hot fat, 275° for 2 to 3 minutes or until fritters are golden brown.
Drain.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift flour with soda.
Combine butter, sugar, pudding mix and vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture, then stir in chips and nuts.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mac 'n cheese supreme(reduced fat, micro magic)
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package.
Drain and put aside. Combine butter and onion in 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe casserole and microwave on High, uncovered, 2 to 3 minutes until onion is tender.
Blend in salt, pepper and cornstarch, and stir in milk. Microwave uncovered on High 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes to boiling and thickening, stirring once.
Stir in yogurt, cheese and pasta and mix well.
Microwave on High, uncovered, 5 to 6 minutes to heat through.

title: cheesecake delights
directions: You will need cupcake papers.

title: bean salad
directions: Open beans and drain; add salad dressing and onions and let set overnight.

title: peach crumble
directions: Beat egg.
Add sugar and nuts.
Spread on greased foil-lined 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool and crumble up. Combine pudding mix, milk and sour cream.
Beat at low speed for 2 minutes.
Fold in peaches.
Alternate layers of pudding mixture and crumb mixture in 6 parfait glasses.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: smoked turkey artichoke salad
directions: Mix together dressings and seasoning until well blended.
Stir in turkey, artichoke hearts and peppers. Chill. Serve on lettuce lined plates.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Beat together the first 5 ingredients for approximately 10 minutes.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Meanwhile, combine the apples, 3 teaspoons of sugar and cinnamon.
Alternate batter with fruit mix in greased Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cheese souffle
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine milk and flour.
Bring to a boil, stirring.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Add butter.
Beat until melted. Remove pan from heat.
Separate eggs.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, and beat until incorporated.
Add cornstarch, shredded cheese and seasonings.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Carefully fold into cheese mixture.
Lightly grease a souffle dish (or use individual serving dishes).
Carefully pour mixture into dish. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes for large souffle, 25 minutes for individual souffle.
Do not open oven door during baking time. Serve immediately.
One hour total, 40 minutes baking time.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Break up the candy.
(Pound with a meat tenderizer or small hammer.)
Mix all ingredients together and add sweet milk, enough to fill the freezer can 3/4 full.
Freeze as regular ice cream in electric or crank freezer.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: baked pineapple casserole
directions: Cream oleo with sugar.
Beat in eggs. Add crushed pineapple. Stir in cubed bread.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with ham or pork.
Use a 2-quart casserole.

title: no bake peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Beat well.
Pour into graham cracker crust.

title: bourbon slushes
directions: Steep tea bags in boiling water for 3 minutes.
Take out tea bags and add sugar to hot water until dissolved.
In large container, pour in tea-sugar mixture and remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Freeze at least 24 hours before serving.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Add the mixed ingredients to chicken, cover and bake in 325° oven for one hour and 20 minutes or until tender.

title: tarragon potato salad
directions: Scrub potatoes well.
Leave skins on.
In a 4 1/2-quart Dutch oven or kettle, cook potatoes covered in boiling, salted water 20 to 25 minutes, until just tender.
Drain.
Cool slightly (or do the day before) and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Dissolve bouillon in water.
Combine with mayonnaise, vinegar, parsley, tarragon and pepper.
Toss gently and chill several hours or overnight.
Serve on leaf lettuce.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: jalapeno black-eyed pea casserole
directions: Pour all ingredients in baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Garnish with crisp bacon bits.

title: baked chicken kiev
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a small bowl.
Shape margarine mixture into 6 (2-inch) sticks.
Freeze until firm.
Place chicken breast halves on flat surface and pound each to 1/4-inch thickness.
Place one portion of margarine mixture on each chicken breast.
Fold over ends.
Roll up and secure with toothpicks.
Dip chicken rolls in milk and coat well with bread crumbs.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Pour pan juices over chicken before serving.

title: bunny salad(kids dish)
directions: For each serving, place crisp lettuce leaf on plate.
On top of it, place upside down one pear half.
Make bunny with narrow end for face, 2 raisins for eyes, 1 red cinnamon candy for nose, 2 blanched almonds for ears and cottage cheese ball for tail.

title: ice cream divan
directions: Mix butter and wafers.
Put in greased lasagna pans (9 x 13-inch). Refrigerate. Crush bars finely onto crumbs.
Soften ice cream and mix with Heath bars. Spread over crust and freeze.

title: caramel bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs.
Add dry ingredients, vanilla and nuts.
Bake in well-greased 9 x 12-inch pan at 300° for 30 minutes.
Turn out on cookie sheet and cut in squares while warm.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Saute onion in 2 tablespoons bacon grease.
Add kraut, cabbage, tomatoes, sugar and salt.
Simmer 1 hour.
Good with pork and small sausages.

title: toll house pie
directions: Mix together. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: * beef mushroom loaf *
directions: Pour milk over bread crumbs.
Add ground beef, salt, pepper, soup, mushrooms and mushroom liquid, catsup and eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Pack in 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: ham and egg cheese noodle casserole
directions: Boil noodles until tender. Add margarine. Add salt and pepper to noodles while cooking. Pour into casserole dish. Add milk and cream of chicken soup. Stir. Add cut up boiled eggs, ham and cubed cheese. Mix well. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. I cover mine with foil.

title: red bean soup
directions: Soak red beans overnight in cold water to cover.
When ready to cook, drain in colander and put them with the other ingredients into a heavy 8 to 10-quart pot or kettle.
Bring to a boil over high heat, then lower heat and simmer for 5 hours.
Turn off heat; remove ham bones and scoop out the pieces of ham.
Strain the soup through a coarse sieve into a large bowl, mashing whole beans with a wooden spoon.
Remove about 3/4 cup of bean solids from sieve and put them in bowl with ham.
Cover with plastic wrap; refrigerate for later use.
Put the thick creamy soup back into pot and warm over low heat for about 5 minutes, stirring to keep it smooth.
Serve piping hot over rice.

title: quick next-mex-chili
directions: Saute garlic, pepper and onion.
Scramble meat over medium to high heat; drain.
Add tomatoes, beans and water (broth).
Stir and cook 20 minutes over low heat until done.
(If you prefer a slight sweetness to your chili, add 1 tablespoon sugar as soon as heat is turned down.)
Add jalapeno and/or chili peppers.
Cook 5 minutes more.
Serve with crackers, tortilla chips or over rice, Sloppy Joe style.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in raisins, carrots, coconut and pecans. In a separate bowl, combine eggs, oil, apple and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir only until combined.
Do not beat.
Spoon into greased or lined muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes (check for doneness).
Yields 18 muffins.
These freeze well.

title: magic squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in sheet cake pan. Sprinkle crumbs over butter and spread evenly.
Sprinkle a layer of each:
coconut, chocolate chips then nuts.
Pour Eagle Brand over all.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: clam corn casserole
directions: Drain liquid from clams in a cup and fill cup with milk. Combine with beaten eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into a greased casserole.
Bake in a moderate oven, 375°, until firm, about 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: brisket
directions: Place brisket in large baking pan lined with foil.
Lay garlic and onions on top of brisket.
Combine soy sauce and liquid smoke.
Pour over brisket.
Seal foil and marinate overnight in the refrigerator.
Cook one hour at 400 degrees.
Reduce heat to 250 and continue cooking for 4 to 6 hours.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Coat pan with oil and sugar.
Can use Bundt or pound cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crackers and margarine.
Pat on bottom of pan.
Mix cream cheese, egg and sugar and put on cracker crust.
Slice bananas over that and drain pineapple, then pour over bananas.
Then put Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle cherries and nuts over this.
Keep refrigerated.

title: bacon-cheddar chicken
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper; coat chicken.
Saute in oil about 5 minutes on each side (add a dash of Worcestershire to each piece while cooking).
Sprinkle 1/4 cup of shredded cheese on all pieces.
Cover with bacon bits.
Top with remaining cheese.
Cover and cook on low heat about 10 minutes longer or until cheese melts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: easy cranberry wild rice
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Add water to sauce to make 4 1/2 cups.
Add cranberry sauce and rice to bring to boil.
Cover tightly about 22 minutes until all liquid is absorbed.
Stir in celery.

title: pineapple torte squares
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and sugar.
Add remainder of ingredients, except coconut and brown sugar.

title: copper kettle fudge
directions: In a heavy saucepan, preferably with a copper bottom, heat the butter, sugar and evaporated milk, stirring constantly to prevent mixture from sticking, until the mixture reaches 238° (the soft ball stage on a candy thermometer).
Remove from heat.
Add the chocolate chips, marshmallow cream, vanilla and salt.
Beat vigorously by hand until all ingredients are thoroughly blended. Fold in nuts.
Lightly butter a 7 1/2 x 11 3/4-inch baking dish. Pour into the dish and allow to cool at room temperature.

title: dirt cake
directions: In a medium
size
bowl,
mix
butter, cream cheese and sugar with a mixer.
In a second medium bowl, mix the milk and pudding. Add the
whipped
topping
to
the	pudding mixture. Combine the 2 mixtures.	Cover
the
bottom of each flowerpot with a plastic lid,
a
piece
of	foil, or a piece of plastic wrap.
Start layering
the
cookie
crumbs and the creamy mixture, making several layers of each, ending with Oreos on top. Cover with plastic
wrap
and	refrigerate
for several hours. Before serving "plant"
the
flower and lay the gummy worms on the "dirt" if desired.
To serve, use a clean garden trowel or spoon.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
Brown sausage lightly and drain.
Put in rest of ingredients and bake at 375° for 30 or 35 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Beat ingredients until thick. Pour into graham cracker crust and chill in refrigerator.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Put in skillet; cover and cook until done.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Dump ingredients in layers in the following order.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Grease a baking dish, 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch.
Arrange oysters (with liquor) in baking dish.
Pour 1/2 of cream over oysters. Combine bread crumbs, butter and seasonings over ingredients. Liquid should come about 3/4 of way up on oysters.
If desired, sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Combine sugar and butter with mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add vanilla.
Add flour and sour cream alternately to batter, mixing on low speed.
Pour into buttered tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 to 30 minutes or until sides are golden brown.
Cool for 5 to 10 minutes. Remove from pan.
Sprinkle cooled cake with powdered sugar or top with fresh fruit.
Store at room temperature.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Sift together into a large mixing bowl all dry ingredients. Add shortening, eggs and bananas.
Beat 1 1/2 minutes at low speed.
Stir in nuts. Bake in well-greased, lightly floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together and spread in a 9-inch square pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar and pecans.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: caramel pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually add milk to blend; add egg yolks and remainder of milk.
Cook over direct heat, stirring constantly.
Place 1/2 cup of sugar and 2 tablespoons of margarine in heavy iron skillet.
Cook simultaneously until sugar melts and turns a golden brown.
(Be careful not to scorch).
By the time the sugar is browned the custard should be thickening. Pour browned sugar into custard and stir until blended.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shells.
Top with meringue and bake at 325° until golden brown.
Enjoy!!!

title: butterscotch peanut drops
directions: Melt chips over low heat.
Stir in noodles and peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper until firm.
May need to refrigerate.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in enough water to cover until tender; drain.
Add salt, pepper, margarine, onion, green chilies and beaten eggs. Put in buttered casserole dish, half of the squash, stuffing mix and cheese; repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese cooks through and browns on top.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat the first 4 ingredients together.
Dump in apples (I use Granny Smith apples; don't chop real small) and let mixture sit for 20 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Pour apple mixture into flour mixture.
Blend with a spoon or spatula (will be thick!).
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
If using a Pyrex pan, bake at 325°.
If using a metal pan, bake at 350°. Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
(Cake will go from a light brown to a darker brown when cooked.)

title: punch
directions: Make tea and sweeten with sugar.
Add lemonade and pineapple juice; stir well.
Rinse orange and slice thinly; do not peel. Cut orange slices in half and add to punch.
Chill well.

title: artichoke cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and put in a shallow baking dish. Place in preheated 350° oven and bake 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly and slightly brown on top.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Place zucchini and lemon juice into a saucepan, cooking until tender.
Add sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Simmer 5 minutes longer. Cool.
Pour into pie plate lined with crust.
Dot with butter. Top with second crust.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven or until golden.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Place margarine in a casserole.
Put in oven and melt.
Remove from oven and add all other ingredients.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until liquid is absorbed.

title: peanut butter eggs
directions: Mix together.
Roll into egg shape, then refrigerate until stiff.
Then chocolate coat.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine ground or chopped cranberries with sugar; let stand 2 hours.
Whip cream; combine with marshmallows and let stand 2 hours.
Combine mixtures; add pineapple and refrigerate overnight.

title: red hot salsa
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender and blend well.
If it's too thick or hot, add water.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, onions, saltines, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper, milk and 1/2 cup catsup.
Make into a loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Pour rest of catsup on top, halfway through cooking.

title: frozen banana punch
directions: Boil sugar and water for 5 minutes.
Let cool completely.
Add bananas and fruit juices.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer 1 hour before serving.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: nutcracker sweets
directions: Lightly butter a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan or cookie sheet. In a large bowl, combine popped popcorn, pecan halves, almonds and the 1 to 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Sprinkle lightly with 1/8 teaspoon salt.
Spread on buttered pan.

title: banana coconut bread
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and baking powder together.
Beat sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Blend in flour mixture. Add milk, bananas, lemon juice and almond extract; stir, then add the toasted coconut.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes in well-greased and floured bread pan.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: jambalaya
directions: Place chopped vegetables in very heavy bottom pot with butter, margarine or oil. Saute for several minutes. Add sausage and saute 5 minutes longer. Add rice; stir and add chicken stock, tomato sauce and shrimp. Bring to a boil and cook uncovered slowly until almost all liquid is absorbed, stirring twice. Cover tightly and continue cooking with very low flame for 30 minutes or until rice is done. Serves 6 to 8.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Pour 1/2 of mix into prepared pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels, butter and milk.
Pour over baked cake.
Sprinkle chopped nuts and chocolate over caramel mixture.
Pour rest of cake batter over ingredients and bake 20 minutes longer at 350°.
Remove from oven and let cool.
Cut in squares.

title: ice cream fudge
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave slowly; stir until all is melted good.
Add softened ice cream and slowly stir into melted chocolate.
If hardness, reheat in microwave for couple seconds. Mix good and pour into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate; after 1 hour, cut into squares.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Combine cake mix, fruit cocktail (and juice), 1 cup of coconut and eggs in large mixing bowl.
Blend, then beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until springs back to touch.

title: sauteed green peppers
directions: Saute onion in oil until golden.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring gently to mix.
Cover and cook over medium heat about 5 minutes or until all vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Stir flour and sugar together and add water.
Melt margarine in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Add batter, then fruit.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown.

title: banana chiffon cake
directions: Sift together in a large bowl the cake flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Make a well in center of mixture and add in order the oil, egg yolks, lemon juice and bananas. Stir with spoon until well blended and smooth.

Beat together in separate large bowl the egg whites and cream of tartar. Beat whites until foamy. Gradually beat in the sugar until soft peaks form. Fold batter gently into beaten whites until no streaks of white remain.
Turn into an ungreased 10-inch tube pan. Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until top springs back when lightly pressed with fingers.
Invert pan, placing tube of pan over funnel or large bottle.
Cool completely.
Loosen cake around tube and sides with a spatula. Remove cake from pan.

title: herbed chicken-a la francais
directions: Arrange chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with green onions and tarragon on top.
Dot chicken with butter and season with salt and pepper.
Add the wine.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Beat egg whites to stiff peaks.
Fold in mayonnaise.
Spoon mixture on top of the chicken and sprinkle with Parmesan.
Return to oven and bake for 12 to 15 minutes more or until light brown.
Before serving, sprinkle chicken with parsley.
Serve with carrots.

title: easy apple kuchen
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large mixer bowl.
Blend in eggs and half of dry cake mix.
Beat for 1 minute at medium speed. Add remaining cake mix and beat for 3 minutes at medium speed. (Batter should be quite stiff but not dough-like.)
Let rest 5 minutes.
Sprinkle flour on board.
Scrape batter out onto prepared board.
Knead batter until the flour is worked in, about 100 strokes.
Place in greased bowl, cover and let rise in warm, draft-free place for 30 minutes.

title: jack-o-lantern cake
directions: Prepare batter according to package directions but use 1/2 cup less water then called for.
Fold in pumpkin and cinnamon.
Pour batter evenly into two greased and floured 1 1/2-quart ovenproof (Pyrex) bowls.
Bake at 325° for an hour.
Test with toothpick. Cool.
Place one cake, rounded side down, on serving plate.
Frost top of it with orange frosting (2 teaspoons grated orange peel can be added).
Place second cake flat side down over the bottom cake, so that cakes form a pumpkin shape.
Frost the outside of cake with remaining frosting.
Run spatula down sides of cake for pumpkin ridges effect.
Make pumpkin stem with large green gumdrops and Jack-O-Lantern eyes, nose and mouth with black gumdrops.
Makes 12 servings.

title: country style vegetable sauce
directions: Chop tomatoes, onions and peppers.
Mix all ingredients.
Cook over low heat for 2 hours.
While cooking, wash and scald jars. Put mixture into jars and seal.

title: vegetable bread
directions: Cook chopped vegetables in margarine.
Stir in Cheddar cheese until melted.
Let cool.
Mix together vegetables, bacon and cut biscuits.
Put in greased Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: In small bowl with mixer at high speed, beat egg whites, cream of tartar and salt until stiff peaks form.
Gradually beat in sugar until smooth and glossy.
Gradually beat in corn syrup and vanilla until stiff peaks form.
If desired, beat in food coloring.
Will cover a 9-inch layer cake or a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake.

title: spinach supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Crust or base:
With hand mixer, blend Bisquick, milk and 2 eggs.
Spread in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Chop first 3 ingredients in food processor.
Add and mix garlic powder, black pepper and Miracle Whip.

title: old-fashioned beef stew
directions: Coat beef with flour, shaking off excess. In a large nonstick pot, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add beef; saute until browned, about 6 minutes. Place on a plate.
Add onions and mushrooms to pot; saut for 6 minutes. Add garlic. Saut, stirring for 1 minute. Pour off fat.

title: fudge
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients. Add milk; blend good. Cook on high until mixture starts to boil, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat to medium. Cook on medium until mixture starts to thicken. Test mixture in a bowl of cold water. If mixture forms ball, remove from heat. Add vanilla and margarine. Beat by hand until thickened. Pour in buttered plate or square bowl. Cut into squares before it gets cold.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Place berries and sugar in a pan over low heat.
Bring to a boil.
Add cornstarch, smoothed in a little water.
Stir until thick; remove from heat.
Let cool.
Pour in pie shell and spread meringue from egg whites over pie and brown.

title: mushroom-barley casserole
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add celery, green pepper, onion, mushrooms, garlic and seasonings. Saute 5 minutes until tender.
Spoon into a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Stir in barley and mix well.
Add broth and water.
Cover and bake 1 1/4 hours until barley is tender.
Stir occasionally. Raise temperature to broil.
Uncover casserole.
Add cheese to the top.
Broil 3 inches from heat for about 3 minutes and serve.

title: quick energy pickups
directions: Crush
to
graham crackers.
Mix all ingredients, except crumbs,
thoroughly
in
mixing bowl.
Use Pam on hands and shape teaspoonfuls of the mixture into 1-inch balls.
Roll the balls
in graham
cracker crumbs or coconut.
Arrange the balls
on waxed paper-lined cookie sheet and refrigerate about 15 minutes.

title: tomato and olive salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss gently.

title: cream puffs
directions: Using a saucepan, bring water to a boil.
Melt margarine in water.
Add flour, all at once.
Remove from heat.
Stir (with wooden spoon) until water, margarine and flour form a big ball in center of pan.
Eggs are added next, one at a time.
Beat 1 egg immediately, until mixture becomes thick and stiff and all 4 eggs have been used.
Be certain the mixture is very stiff after the addition of each egg.

title: slow ball dip
directions: Cut top from bread with sharp knife.
Hollow loaf leaving 1 1/2 to 2 inch thick shell.
Cut bread into cubes and set aside.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Wash 4 to 5 potatoes; cook in microwave until middle is soft. Cut and scoop middle out; put in bowl.
Add Parmesan cheese, sour cream onion dip and oleo.
Beat all together.
After mixed together, scoop back into middle of potatoes.
Put back in microwave for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel and chop eggplant.
Cook in just enough boiling water to cover; until soft.
Drain and mash smooth. Saute onion in butter and add to eggplant.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole dish and cover with grated cheese.
Bake until firm.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil and sugar together.
Add baking powder, salt, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and flour, mixing well.
Stir in apples, nuts and raisins.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheddar herb biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In bowl, combine flour, cheese, parsley, baking powder, salt and pepper.
With pastry blender or knife, cut in butter until mixture forms coarse crumbs.
Stir in milk.
Quickly mix until mixture forms soft ball.
Transfer dough to lightly floured surface.
Knead slightly to combine thoroughly. Roll or pat dough to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut biscuits and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until golden. Makes 1 1/2 dozen biscuits.

title: beefy salsa mac
directions: Brown meat in a large skillet and drain.

Stir in salsa, water, uncooked macaroni, dry cheese sauce mix and Miracle Whip; mix well and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; cover. Simmer 7 minutes or until macaroni is tender, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat. Let stand, covered, 5 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: penuche bars
directions: Cream butter and 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Add 1 cup flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Spread this mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan and brown at 350°.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread over the first layer; bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool real good before cutting.

title: alabama corn bread
directions: Mix all at once. Fold in corn last.
Pour into hot greased skillet. Bake at 450° until brown.

title: mud hens
directions: Crust:
Cream butter, adding sugar slowly.
Add 3 egg yolks and 1 egg white, beating well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Add slowly to creamed mixture, beating well.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Spread dough on bottom of a well-greased pan.
Sprinkle nuts over top and pat nuts lightly into dough.

title: southern tuna salad
directions: Combine tuna and mayonnaise.
Stir in other ingredients and chill.
Serve with lettuce or use for sandwiches.

title: lasagne presto
directions: In saucepan, brown beef and cook onion, garlic and oregano; add soup and water.
Simmer for 30 minutes, stirring now and then. In baking dish (12 x 8 x 2-inch), arrange three alternating layers of lasagne, cottage cheese, meat sauce and Mozzarella.
Top with Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Blend cream cheese, mayonnaise and sugar.
Add pineapple, cranberry sauce and nuts.
Mix well.
Fold in whipping cream. Pour into foil loaf pans and freeze.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into 3 pans and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: autumn soup
directions: In large skillet, brown hamburg and drain off fat.
Cook and stir onions with meat until onions are tender.
Add all ingredients into a large saucepan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until vegetables are tender.
(A variety of vegetables can be added.)
Great meal with your favorite muffins.

title: maw maw's hot rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, shortening and salt.
Stir to blend. Cool until lukewarm.
Break yeast in cup; add milk to dissolve yeast, then add yeast and beaten egg to milk.
Add flour gradually; stir until smooth, and then a soft dough.
Place in a greased bowl; let rise about 1 hour.
Punch down, then shape into balls.
Dip in melted butter and place in muffin cups or on a cookie sheet.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.

title: double trouble chocolate peanut butter squares
directions: Melt peanut butter and butter in saucepan over low heat. Add 10X sugar and blend well. Pour into 13x9x2 inch pan and smooth out. Melt 4 to 6 Hershey bars in pan over very low heat.
Pour over peanut butter mixture and smooth out with spatula. Refrigerate overnight. Allow to return to room temperature before slicing into small squares. Refrigerate to keep firm.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Mix egg, sugar and sour cream well.
Sift dry ingredients together and mix with egg mixture.
When you add the flour it will make a soft dough.
Roll out 1/2 inch thick.
Cut out cookies and place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: petite pinwheels
directions: Separate dough into 4 rectangles; firmly press perforations to seal.
Spread with cream cheese.
Sprinkle with ham, pressing lightly.
Roll up, starting at short end.
Seal edges.
Cut each roll into four slices.
Place, cut side down, on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 17 minutes or until golden brown.

title: tooty fruity saladrooty
directions: Chop apples, leaving peeling.
Chop grapes in half.
Peel and chop orange.
Combine in large mixing bowl.
Add coconut, walnut pieces and Cool Whip.
Mix until all fruit is covered with Cool Whip.
Let chill 5 to 10 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: baked pancakes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine flour, milk, eggs and nutmeg. Beat lightly.
Leave batter a little lumpy.
Melt butter and pour in 9 x 13-inch baking dish; pour batter over butter.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Sprinkle with sugar and return to oven for a minute.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix chicken, soups, sour cream and poppy seed.
Line a baking dish with 1 stack Ritz crackers.
Pour chicken mixture over crackers.
Top with other stack of crackers.
Melt margarine.
Pour over cracker crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate pecan fudge(microwave)
directions: Place first 5 ingredients in a large glass bowl.
Do not mix. Microwave, uncovered, on High for 2 minutes; remove from oven and stir well.
Return to microwave, uncovered, on High for 1 minute. Remove and stir well.
Repeat this step twice for a total cooking time of 5 minutes.
After the final stirring, add nuts and spread in an 8-inch glass dish.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill until firm.
Yields 36 pieces.

title: gladys smith's baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift all dry ingredients; beat egg into milk.
Cut Crisco into dry ingredients.
Pour milk over mixture.
Roll on floured board. Don't roll dough too thin.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: quick mixer bread or rolls
directions: Place the water, salt, yeast, sugar and 2 cups of flour in a large mixing bowl.
Mix at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add 2 eggs and oil; beat one minute.

title: key lime pie
directions: Blend limeade, milk and food coloring well.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Pour in graham cracker pie shell and chill.

title: pickled squash
directions: Combine sliced squash and onions. Cover with water; sprinkle with salt. Let stand 1 hour. Combine vinegar, sugar, celery seed, mustard seed and bring to a boil. Drain squash and onions, then add them and green peppers to vinegar mixture and let come to a hard boil. Remove from heat; add pimentos.	Pack into jars with enough juice to cover and seal.

title: chicken stuff
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot. Cook slowly until rice is tender. Sprinkle chow mein noodles.

title: stir-fry sausage with yellow boiled rice
directions: Boil 2 cups of rice separately.
In a separate pan, place sliced sausages.
After, place sausage in a bowl.
Then add 1 tablespoon of oil.
Then place the adobo, garlic powder, black pepper and the salt.
Then add the onions, the green peppers and tomato.
Stir a little and then add your 6 ounces tomato sauce. If you want more sauce, add 6 ounces of water.
Add sausage.

title: fig preserves
directions: Sprinkle soda over figs.
Pour 4 quarts boiling water over figs.
Let set for 5 minutes, then pour cold water over figs, rinsing well.
Boil sugar and water for a few minutes.
Add well drained figs and boil until of desired thickness.

title: nutty graham picnic cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and flour 12-cup fluted tube pan or 10-inch tube pan.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients but nuts.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Add nuts; bake in prepared pan for 45 to 50 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Cool upright 15 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate and cool completely.

title: apple crisp
directions: Arrange apples in buttered 8-inch baking dish.
In another pan (bowl), combine oatmeal, brown sugar, flour and cinnamon, then cut in butter.
Sprinkle on top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix altogether, put in dish and refrigerate.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer first 9 ingredients for 20 minutes, uncovered.
Add Worcestershire sauce and catsup.
Let come to rolling boil.
Remove from heat.
Store in refrigerator.

title: pickled jalapenos
directions: Wash and pack fresh jalapenos, sliced carrots and garlic cloves into clean, sterilized jars.
Combine vinegar, water, olive oil, canning salt and pickling spices in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cover peppers with boiling liquid, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Close and process 10 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix strawberries, eggs and oil in medium bowl.
Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, soda, salt and pecans in large bowl.
Add strawberry mixture to dry ingredients.
Stir just until mixed. Pour into greased and floured 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
