Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Yields 24 slices.

title: corn casserole
directions: In large skillet, saute onion and peppers in butter until tender.
Stir in flour and remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients except for 1/2 cup cheese.
Pour into a greased 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes. Top with remaining cheese.
Let stand 2 minutes.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Slowly add milk, blending thoroughly into mixture. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Freeze until firm.

title: spinach hors d'oeuvres
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Spread in pan.
Bake 45 minutes uncovered. Let stand 10 minutes to cool.
Cut into 30 to 40 (2-inch) squares. Serve warm.
Can be frozen and reheated to serve.

title: cheesy bacon grits
directions: Fry bacon just until crispy. Drain. In medium saucepan, combine milk, salt, cayenne and butter. Bring to a boil. Add grits and reduce heat to medium. Stir for 30 seconds, then add cheese and stir until melted. Cook, covered, until grits are tender and creamy.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine all ingredients.
Spoon into a muffin tin, filling each cup approximately 2/3 full.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes until biscuits have browned.
Batter will make approximately 6 large or 12 small muffins.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt oleo in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour melted butter into mixing bowl.
Add sugar, eggs, flour, baking powder and nuts.
Mix together.
Pour mix into baking dish and sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Cut up and boil potatoes; put aside and save.
Cook and crumble bacon and save.
Saute in butter, Tabasco and Worcestershire the onion, carrots and garlic until tender.
Drain potatoes, saving 1 cup water.
Slightly mash; add half and half, water and vegetables.
Let simmer for 30 minutes.
Top with bacon and cheese when ready to serve.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Mix oleo, flour and nuts together and press down in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Cool.

title: appetizer ham ball
directions: Combine ham, olives, mustard, hot sauce and 1/3 cream cheese; blend well until smooth.
Shape into ball.
Combine remaining cream cheese and milk; use to frost ham ball.
Chill.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before serving.

title: pork chops and potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown pork chops in hot shortening. Place 3 pork chops in bottom of shallow baking dish.
Cover pork chops with sliced potatoes.
Place last 3 pork chops on top of potatoes.
Cover with soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients except Parmesan cheese.
Pour into a buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch casserole.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine and mix with stuffing.
Put half in bottom of pan or casserole dish.
Combine all the ingredients and put in dish.
Add remaining stuffing on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: down south barbecue twists
directions: In a large bowl, add peanut butter, yeast, garlic powder and paprika to raw gluten.
Mix well by pulling and stretching.
Saute onions in oil.
Add onions and hot oil to seasoned gluten.
(Hot oil breaks the gluten down and helps seasonings to penetrate.) Continue to mix gluten well by pulling and stretching until consistency is stringy, but doesn't tear apart.
Pull off small pieces of gluten and stretch and twist pieces into shapes similar to 6 to 8-inch bread sticks.

title: tamale pie
directions: Mix all together.
Save 1/2 of cheese for top.
Crush Fritos and put on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: yummy breakfast rolls(reduced fat version)
directions: Unroll 1 can of rolls and lay in bottom of 13 x 9 pan.
Don't press seams together.
Mix cream cheese with 1 cup Splenda and vanilla.
Spread over rolls.
Place 2nd can of rolls on top.
Pour melted margarine over rolls.
Mix 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon with 1/4 cup Splenda and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Let cool.
Best served a little warm.

title: evergreen chili sauce
directions: Tie allspice and cloves.
Cook all in 350° oven; it is easy to scorch.
Stir fairly often.
Do not use lid on container.
Add all ingredients together except pepper.
Boil down to nearly half quantity.
Take several hours before removing from oven.
Add 2 Tbsp. flour thickening and pepper stirring well until sauce thickens.
Yield:
One gallon makes around 8 pints.

title: hot mustard
directions: Combine dry mustard and vinegar; mix well.
Let stand overnight.
Add eggs and sugar.
Cook until thick.
Let cool and store in refrigerator.

title: creamy chocolate frosting
directions: This makes a very smooth frosting and is easy to manage.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower into bite size pieces.
Add onions and green peppers.
Combine remainder of ingredients and stir into vegetables until all are covered.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Microwave for 10 minutes on High; stir halfway through.

title: yuletide toffee squares
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan. Combine oats, brown sugar, margarine/butter, corn syrup, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Firmly press mixture into greased pan.
Bake about 18 minutes or until the mixture is brown and bubbly.
Then remove from oven.
Immediately sprinkle chocolate morsels evenly over toffee.
Let stand 10 minutes; spread chocolate evenly over toffee and sprinkle with nuts.
Cool completely and cut into squares.
Store in a cool dry place.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in salted water.
Drain, peel and cube potatoes. Combine potatoes and all ingredients except cheese.
Spoon into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 15 minutes. Top with cheese and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: back-to-basics coleslaw
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Toss, cover and chill 1 hour.
Toss before serving.

title: chinese duck sauce(condiment)
directions: Combine everything in a medium sized sauce pan and bring to a boil.
Turn down heat and simmer uncovered for about 30 minutes or until fruit is very soft.
Cool thoroughly and then chill.

title: tossed tuna salad
directions: Drain tuna.
Break into large pieces.
Rub the inside of a salad bowl with the cut surface of a clove of garlic.
Combine all ingredients except tomatoes.
Toss lightly.
Garnish with tomato wedges.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Spread bread with butter, then spread cucumber mixture over bread.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix ground beef, rice, onion, salt, pepper and egg together. Divide meat into equal portions; stuff peppers.
Place in roaster and cover with tomato sauce and water.
Bake slowly for 2 to 3 hours at 300° or until peppers are soft and beef is done inside.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Sift together into a large bowl the first 4 ingredients.
Add the next 5 ingredients and beat well until all are well blended. Fry on preheated griddle, turning to brown on both sides.
This recipe makes about 10 medium-sized pancakes.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix cream cheese, flour and butter together; chill for 1 hour. Roll into small balls and chill again.
Mix filling by combining the remaining ingredients.
Press balls into tart pans; fill each 3/4 full with filling.
Bake for 25 minutes in a preheated 325° oven.

title: chocolate-coconut dessert
directions: In saucepan, melt chocolate in milk.
Bring to boiling; boil gently, uncovered, for 4 minutes, or until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add marshmallows; heat and stir until melted.
Chill.

title: sweet potato casserole(with coconut)
directions: Blend first 6 ingredients and pour in greased casserole.
Mix brown sugar, nuts, 1/2 stick butter and flour and pour this mixture over potato mixture.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: engine juice
directions: Pour half of the vodka into a separate container, set aside. Pour all of the honey in with the bottled vodka. Shake WELL. This may take some time. After that is well mixed add the juice from the 2 lemons, top off with the set aside vodka.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Defrost broccoli and drain.
Place into casserole dish.
Heat mushroom soup and cheese together.
Pour over broccoli.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° with cover on.

title: pineapple nut salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple.
Put juice in pan.
Add sugar and cornstarch.
Bring to a boil.
Chop pecans into pineapple.
Add marshmallows.
Cut cheese into 1/2-inch squares.
Mix all ingredients.
Serve.

title: family rice sausage dish
directions: Cook and stir sausage in Dutch oven.
Drain and add rice, cheese, milk, soup and mushrooms.
Put into large casserole dish and bake, covered, at 350°
for 50 minutes.
You can also sprinkle cheese on the top.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sinful cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
While warm, poke holes in top of cake and pour canned milk over top, followed by ice cream topping.
Put in refrigerator and let cool. After cake is cool, ice with Cool Whip.
Break the Heath candy bars in pieces and sprinkle on top.

title: e z cream cheese bars
directions: Pat 1 can crescent rolls into 9 x 13 pan.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread on rolls.
Pat second can of rolls on top. Drizzle butter over top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Can substitute almond flavoring for vanilla.

title: one dish macaroni and beef(microwave)
directions: In a 2-quart glass casserole dish, combine all ingredients. Mix well.
Cook, covered, for 18 minutes.
Stir.
Let stand for 5 to 8 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Sift flour and measure; add baking powder, soda and salt. Sift again.
Add nuts.
Mix well.
Melt butter or shortening in saucepan or microwave.
Remove from heat.
Mix in sugar (add 2 tablespoons hot water if vegetable shortening is used).
Cool; stir in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture, small amount at a time.
Spread in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch sheet cake pan. Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool in pan; cut into 15 bars.

title: gumbo
directions: Fry bacon and drain on paper towel.
Mix bacon grease with flour and brown.
Put all seasonings (except bay leaves) into a cup and crush.
Add remaining ingredients except shrimp, crab and okra.
Cook on low; simmer 2 hours.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove from broth and debone.
Add water to chicken broth to make 3-quarts.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions in the chicken broth.
Saute celery, onion and bell pepper in cooking oil until transparent.
In a very large pot, mix all ingredients together.
Put into baking dishes.
Bake at 350°.
This makes about 20 or more servings.
I make and freeze in 3 or 4 serving dishes, then bake as I need it!
Delicious.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Mix spaghetti, eggs and milk and put into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Brown 1 1/2 pounds hamburger.
Drain and add 1 large Ragu sauce. Pour over spaghetti.
Cover with sliced pepperoni, 2 cups shredded Mozzarella cheese and olive slices.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry delite
directions: Piece angel food cake up in bottom of 9 x 13 dish. Cut strawberries up on top of cake. Mix Jell-O up according to directions on box and pour on top of cake. Top with Cool Whip. Chill until Jell-O is congealed.

title: beef fiesta
directions: Brown meat in oil, then drain.
Add onion, salt, chili powder, pepper, tomatoes, corn and broth.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and add pepper strips.
Simmer a few minutes, then add rice. Remove from heat and cover.
Let mixture stand for 3 minutes. Then fluff with fork and it's ready to serve.
tags: thin strips of green bell pepper

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potato chips, and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or 1 hour.
Put potato chips on top when about done.

title: french toast casserole
directions: Place cubed bread pieces in a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Add cream cheese on top of bread.
Mix eggs, milk and syrup together.
Pour over bread and cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle top of casserole with cinnamon.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes or until set.
Serve warm with warm syrup.

title: cioppino(fish soup)
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil until transparent.
Add chicken broth and bring to boil.
Add tomato and seasonings; simmer 10 minutes.
Add shrimp and fish and simmer only until shrimp is pink and fish is cooked through, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Pour in chopped clams with the juice.
Turn off the heat; add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with lots of Italian bread.
Pour soup over cooked angel hair pasta.

title: harvest loaf
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and eggs well together.
Add pumpkin and spices; add flour and mix well.
Add chocolate chips and walnuts. Bake about 1 hour at 350°.
Small loaves take about 45 minutes. Glaze with Spice Glaze.

title: tortilla rolls
directions: Combine cream cheese, olives and peppers.
Spread on tortillas and roll.
Slice into pinwheels.
Dip in salsa or add salsa to cream cheese mixture before spreading on tortillas.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix in blender and freeze.
Serve with equal amounts of ginger ale.

title: bubble cake(breakfast rolls)
directions: Spray bundt pan with cooking spray if not using non-stick pan.
Put frozen rolls in bundt pan.
Do not use whole package or overfill pan because rolls will rise over rim.

title: shrimp curry
directions: Chop onion; saute in margarine.
When onion turns yellow, add undiluted soups, then add curry powder, grapes, salt and pepper. Add sour cream, lemon juice and shrimp just before serving.
If uncooked shrimp are used, cook according to directions before adding.
After all ingredients are added, heat thoroughly.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: broccoli casserole  wirh cheese nips
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Drain thoroughly. Combine all other ingredients except cracker crumbs.
Pour into buttered casserole. Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake uncovered 20 minutes at 400°.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Combine
flour,
3/4 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa; stir in
milk,
butter and vanilla.
Pour batter into a 9-inch square baking pan.
Combine
cup sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa and salt; mix well and sprinkle over batter.
Pour water over top;
bake at 350° for
minutes.
Serve
warm.
Top
with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and cut in shortening with 2 knives or a pastry blender.
Add milk and mix quickly. Knead for a few seconds on a lightly floured board.
Pat out to 1/2 inch thickness and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place in greased pan close together for crust on top and bottom only, far apart if crust is desired on sides also.
Bake at once in very hot oven (450°) for 12 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth, beat in sugar and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip, blending well.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, at least 4 hours.
Garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: german potato salad
directions: In large skillet, fry bacon until crisp.
Remove and place on paper towels to absorb grease.
Drain all but enough grease to coat the skillet.

Add onions to skillet and cook until tender. Pour flour in a small jar with 1/3 cup of the water and shake until blended. Add vinegar and remaining 1 cup water to skillet. Slowly stir in flour mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir until slightly thick.
Add sugar.
Crumble bacon.
Gently stir in bacon and potatoes.
Heat through, stirring lightly to coat potato slices.
Serve warm or cold.

title: mom's special quick quiche
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly spray a 9 or 10-inch pie plate or quiche pan with Pam.
Sprinkle cheese, bacon, mushrooms and onion evenly over bottom of pan.
Mix Bisquick, milk, eggs, salt and pepper in blender or food processor.
Pour mixture over ingredients already in pan.
Bake about 30 to 35 minutes, until golden brown.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese while hot.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Great for breakfast or brunch! Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 6 servings.

title: molded salad
directions: Combine gelatins and boiling water, stirring until dissolved. Add remaining ingredients.
Drain pineapple before adding.
Mix together and put in mold.
This salad is good with ham or pork.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute butter and onion.
Mix soup, milk and Cheez Whiz over medium heat until thickened.
Stir in onion and butter.
Combine frozen broccoli cuts and Minute rice in casserole dish.
Pour cheese mixture over broccoli and rice and mix together.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Beat egg.
Add other ingredients and whisk until mixed. Marinate chicken overnight and barbecue.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, mix flour with next 7 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until blended. Turn batter into greased pans. Bake about 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 3 loaves or 6 mini loaves.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and flour. Add a little milk until mixture is moistened well to prevent lumps, then add remainder of milk. Add egg yolks. Cook on medium heat until ready thick. Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon of butter and 1 teaspoon of vanilla. Pour into prepared pie shell. Beat egg whites with mixer until stiff. Add 3 teaspoons of sugar. Beat again and put on top of pie. Place in oven and brown meringue.

title: blintz souffle(breakfast)
directions: Melt butter in pan you will be using for baking.

title: chocolate brownie pie
directions: Beat eggs in mixer bowl until fluffy.
Add sugar and margarine; mix well.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt together.
Add to egg mixture, beating until smooth.
Stir in chocolate chips, pecans and vanilla.
Spread into greased 8-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until set.
Pie will not test done in center.
Cool completely.
Cut into wedges.
Top each with a scoop of ice cream.
Spoon fudge topping over ice cream.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: black walnut carrot cake
directions: While grating carrots, allow the sugar to sit at room temperature in oil.
Separate the eggs.
Fold in beaten egg whites before pouring mixture into Bundt pan.
Mix flour, oil, sugar mixture and beaten egg yolks together.
Mix in grated carrots, spices and nuts.
Fold in beaten egg whites and gently blend. Pour into greased Bundt pan and bake at 350°.

title: flan (spanish caramel custard)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.

title: play dough i
directions: Sift dry ingredients into pan.
Mix liquids and add coloring. Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly until dough pulls away from pan.
Dough should not feel sticky.
Store in airtight container.
For longer shelf life, store in refrigerator.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: In a large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk until smooth.
Add eggs and ReaLemon; mix well.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 300° (preheat oven) for 50 to 55 minutes or until center is set.
Chill before serving.

title: oatmeal crunchies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Combine flour, granulated sugar and soda. Add brown sugar, shortening, egg and vanilla, beat well. Stir in oats and nuts. Form dough into small balls, place on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 7-12 minutes. Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: carrot cake
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl and mix with spoon.
Do not use mixer.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and butter.
Mix together like pie dough.
Keep out 1/2 cup crumbs for on top of cake.
Beat egg yolks and add thick milk and vanilla.
Mix, then add to first ingredients.
Beat the egg whites stiff and fold into mixture.
Put in pan and sprinkle the 1/2 cup crumbs on top. Cinnamon may be sprinkled on top if you like.
Bake at 350°.

title: mom's banana bread
directions: Mix margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix in bananas and buttermilk.
Sift dry ingredients and add to beaten mixture.
Add nuts last.
Bake at 325° in greased loaf pans for 1 1/4 hours or until done.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Heat together everything except carrots.
Add carrots; marinate together.
Best if made a few days earlier.

title: cottage cheese chili dip
directions: Prepare vegetables for dipping.
Place in plastic bags and chill.

In a bowl, prepare dip by blending together cottage cheese and yogurt. Add vinegar, garlic and red onion. Stir in chili sauce and parsley until well combined. Cover and chill 1 hour to blend. When ready to serve, transfer dip to serving bowl. Surround with celery sticks, green pepper slices and quartered mushrooms.

title: frozen slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, peppers and carrots.
Add salt.
Refrigerate for 2 hours, then drain off water.
Boil the sugar, vinegar, water, mustard seed and celery seed.
Let cool and pour over slaw. Put in plastic container and freeze.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper; coat meat cubes in seasoned flour.
Brown in hot shortening in small dutch oven; add soup, water, onion and basil.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Add potatoes, carrots, and wine.
Cover and bake 1 hour longer, or until tender.
Good served over Bisquick drop biscuits.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pecans, coconut, eggs and margarine or butter. Mix well.
Mixture will be stiff and greasy.
Pat in 13 x 9-inch pan, ungreased and unfloured.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Beat well. Pour mixture over unbaked cake.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: quick fruit cream pie
directions: Prepare fruit and put in pie shell.
In bowl, beat eggs lightly and blend in sugar, flour, cream and vanilla.
Pour over fruit.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: lemon whippersnaps
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Stir until well blended.
Drop by teaspoons into powdered sugar; roll until coated.
Place 1 1/2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove the cookies while warm.

title: orange angel food cake
directions: To egg whites, add salt and beat until foamy; add cream of tartar and beat until stiff.
Very gradually fold in sugar. Divide egg white mixture into equal parts.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix the ham, pork, eggs, bread crumbs and milk; form into balls.
Bring to a boil the brown sugar, mustard, vinegar and water.
Pour over balls.
Bake for about 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Prepare corn bread according to directions. Cool. Crumble into very small pieces. Cook bacon, drain and crumble or chop.
In a large glass bowl, layer half of the corn bread.
Top with half of the pickle relish, juice, tomatoes, pepper, onion, bacon and 1/2 cup mayonnaise. Repeat layers, reserving small amount of tomatoes and bacon for garnish.
Refrigerate and serve chilled.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in gallon container.
Finish filling with water.
Chill and serve.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; beat 5 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer or until smooth.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour filling into crust; bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Remove from oven. Combine remaining ingredients; sprinkle over top.
Bake 10 additional minutes.
Chill before serving.

title: strawberry salad(yield: 8 servings)
directions: Fold in crushed pineapple and 1/2 cup chopped nuts and partially set jello.

title: raisin bars
directions: Cream butter, brown sugar and salt.
Blend in flour and oatmeal until fine.
Press 2/3 of crumbs into bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Let butter stand at room temperature until soft.
Preheat oven to slow 350° for shiny metal or 325° for dark metal sheet.

title: pot roast supreme
directions: Cook roast in pressure cooker or boil, retaining one cup liquid until very tender.
Remove from pot.
Add potatoes, onions, celery, green peppers, mushrooms and gravy.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Put roast back in pot and simmer until hot.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Place broccoli in greased casserole, then add cubed chicken. Combine next four ingredients and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle on cheese and bread crumbs; dot with butter.
Garnish with pimento (optional).
Sprinkle with wheat germ (optional).
Place in preheated oven at 350° and bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes. Serves 10.

title: divinity
directions: In heavy pan over medium heat cook syrup, sugar, salt and water until sugar is dissolved, stirring constantly. Cook without stirring to firm ball stage (248° on candy thermometer) or until small amount of syrup forms a firm ball when dropped in cold water. Just before syrup reaches 248°, in another bowl, beat egg whites with mixer until stiff. Slowly pour hot syrup into whites and continue beating with mixer until it holds its shape. Add vanilla, continue beating, it will be ready when mixture goes from shiny to a flat look. Add the nuts if desired. Immediately drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper. Use two spoons if necessary since the mixture is very hot. Makes 1-1/4 pounds.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix and beat at medium speed for 5 minutes.
Grease a Bundt pan and flour.
Place whole pecans in bottom of pan.
Pour in the mix batter and bake at 350°
for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let cool 15 minutes and place on wire rack to cool.
Serve with cream.

title: easy asparagus
directions: Put asparagus in bottom of 2-quart casserole dish.
Add soup, top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken salsa
directions: Pound chicken flat and cut into small pieces, pat dry.
Fry chicken until lightly browned.
Put in 9 x 13 baking dish.
Cover with chunky salsa.
Cover with grated cheese.
Heat in microwave or bake in regular oven until bubbly.
Serve with tortillas.

title: sweet potato loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; turn into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until done.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Slice and serve.
Is delicious with bacon or pork sausage.

title: candied dill strips
directions: Mix ingredients in pan and heat until sugar is dissolved. Pour over pickles.
In 4 or 5 days, they will be ready.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake loaves at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tang pie
directions: Mix together and pour into crust.
Refrigerate for several hours.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: While they are still hot, beat sweet potatoes fluffy and add all other ingredients.
Beat until fluffy.
Spoon into a greased 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle topping over and bake 1/2 hour in 350° oven.
Serves 8.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

title: mom's impossible pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add beaten eggs and remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased 9-inch aluminum foil pie tins or unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° until brown on top, about 35 minutes.

title: round steak and gravy
directions: Pound steak or use meat tenderizer.
Cut steak into pieces. Salt and pepper, then cover both sides with flour.
Fry meat in hot oil until done.
After frying all the meat slowly, stir in remaining flour.
Add hot water to mix until it is smooth and the texture you want.
Add sliced onion and let simmer until onions are tender.

title: chocolate cherry dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Prepare brownie mix in a 13 x 9 inch pan, as directed on package, except bake only 20 minutes.
Beat vanilla, egg, milk, and cream cheese in a large bowl until smooth. Pour over baked brownie layer.
Bake until topping is set, about 25 minutes.
Cool 2 hours.
Spread with pie filling.
Cut into squares.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Wrap a bacon strip around each piece of chicken.
Spread dried beef on bottom of 2 1/2-quart or 7 x 11-inch dish.
Place chicken on top of beef.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Spread on top of chicken.
Bake 3 hours, uncovered, at 275°.

title: brownie mud puddle cake
directions: Microwave chocolate and butter in large bowl on high for 2 minutes or until butter is melted.
Stir until chocolate is melted. Stir in sugar.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and stir until well blended.
Spread into greased 12 inch pizza pan.
Bake at 350 for 25-30 minutes, cool in pan.
Add milk to pudding mix. Beat with wire whisk until well blended.
Spread over brownie, leaving a 1 inch border around the edge.
Sprinkle with crushed cookies.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream the sugar, oil, eggs and 1 cup apples.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Add the dates, nuts, 2 cups chopped apples and vanilla.
Place in ungreased pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 to 15 minutes.

title: easiest apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Peel, core and thin slice apples and arrange in 13 x 9 baking pan. Combine remaining ingredients; mix until crumbly. Sprinkle evenly over apples. Bake 35 to 40 minutes. Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan, bring to a boil.
Stir until transparent.

title: mexican potato soup
directions: Saute onion in bacon drippings until translucent. Combine ingredients into large pot. Crumble bacon into small pieces. Cook slowly for about 1 hour or until potatoes are done. Serve with corn tortilla chips and cheese.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets and save juice.
Mix flour or cornstarch and sugar together; add vinegar slowly, stirring to prevent lumps. Add beet juice and cook over low heat until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Add the beet slices, simmer until they are thoroughly hot.

title: rigatoni
directions: Brown stewing meat in oil.
Add onion, salt and pepper. Drain.
Add sauce and medium paste and equal parts of water and paste.
Add chili powder and garlic powder to taste.
Simmer; pour over strained, cooked rigatoni.

title: graham cracker cookie
directions: Line a cookie sheet with graham crackers.
Melt butter in a small saucepan.
Add sugar and boil for 3 minutes.
Add nuts. Drizzle over graham crackers.
Bake at 275° for 10 minutes.
Let cool until hard.

title: crab stew
directions: Combine margarine, onion, bell pepper and crab meat in pan. Cook until tender.
Then add soups and milk.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: sauerkraut bits
directions: Partially cook meat and drain excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients and shape into small balls (1 inch).
Refrigerate. Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
May be frozen and reheated.

title: homemade rolls
directions: The sugar must be granulated.

title: moist meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in a mixing bowl; pour into a loaf pan. Spread ketchup over top of meat loaf.
Cover with aluminum foil. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Remove foil and bake about 5 more minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch pan. Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: danish jam cookies(thumbprints)
directions: In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat margarine and sugar until smooth.
Beat in corn syrup and egg yolks.
Stir in flour.
Chill 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Dip into slightly beaten egg whites.
Roll in nuts.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
With thumb, make indentation in center of each. Bake in a 325° oven 20 minutes or until golden brown.
If necessary, press again with thumb.
Remove from cookie sheet; place on rack.
While still warm, fill with jam or jelly.
Let cool completely.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: capitol hill bean soup
directions: Sort and wash beans; place
in a Dutch oven.
Cover with water and soak overnight.
Drain beans; add ham bone and cover with water.
Cover and bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 1 hour. Add remaining ingredients; simmer 1 hour or until beans are tender.
Remove ham and dice (remove gristle and fat); return to soup.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Mix graham crackers, soda crackers and margarine; press 3/4 of mixture in bottom of a 9 x 13 inch glass pan.

title: 3-point nacho spread(three-layer black bean dip; low-fat)
directions: In a food processor or blender, whirl the beans and 1/4 cup of the salsa briefly.
Spoon into the bottom of
a 1-quart serving bowl.
In a small bowl, whisk together the sour cream and 1/4 cup of the salsa.
Drop by spoonfuls over the beans; spread gently to cover.
Spoon the remaining salsa over the sour cream.
Sprinkle with cheese and cilantro, if using.
Cover and refrigerate for at least two hours and up to 24 hours.
Serve with reduced-fat crackers.
Makes 4 cups.

title: potato rolls
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and salt.
Add eggs and potatoes; blend well.
Add milk to creamed mixture.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water; add to rest of mixture.
Stir in enough flour to make a fairly stiff dough.
Turn out on floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic.
Put in greased bowl, cover and let rise until double.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and slice thin. Fry bacon until crisp. Drain on paper towel. Saute onions and pepper in bacon grease until brown. Add flour and mix well. Add sugar, salt, celery seed and black pepper. Cook over low heat stirring until smooth and bubbly. Remove from heat. Stir in water and vinegar. Heat to boiling. Cook 1 minute.
Add potatoes, eggs and crumbled bacon.

title: fried mushrooms
directions: Mix flour, salt, baking powder and pepper.
Beat egg yolk and milk together. Blend in dry ingredients.
Beat egg white until foamy.
Add sugar and beat until stiff, but not dry. Fold this into milk mixture.
Dip mushrooms in batter.
Drain.
Roll in crushed cereal and fry until golden brown.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 325° to 350° until bubbly.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Place margarine and sugar in large bowl.
Stir in milk, stirring to melt margarine.
Add eggs, yeast and salt. Mix well.
Add 2 cups flour, beating very well.
Add rest of flour. Knead well.
Let rise in warm place.
Punch down.
Make into rolls, cinnamon rolls or tea ring.
Let rise again until double. Bake at 350° until golden brown and done (30 to 40 minutes).

title: chicken and rice
directions: Pour rice in bottom of Pyrex dish.
Mix soups and milk.
Place chicken pieces over rice.
Pour soups over chicken and rice. Sprinkle onion soup over all.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.

title: plain cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening together; add sugar.
Cream with shortening until blended.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add coconut and mix.
Mix into preceding, alternating flour and milk until all used.
Add vanilla.
Bake in angel cake pan, greased and floured, at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Beat eggs; add cheese, cornbread mix, onions, melted oleo and broccoli.
Mix well and pour into iron skillet that has been well-greased.
Bake 40 minutes at 400°.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, oats, salt, pepper, onion, tomato sauce and egg. Mix thoroughly .
Pack firmly into an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch pan.
Bake.
Let set a few minutes before slicing.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: pasta with broccoli
directions: In large pan, cook the broccoli in enough boiling unsalted water to cover until just tender, 2 or 3 minutes.
Rinse under cold running water, drain and set aside.

title: oven goulash
directions: Put meat and soup with water in a heavy casserole.
Cover and bake at 300° for 2 to 3 hours.
This can be served over rice or noodles.

title: pahoa ham
directions: Make sauce of lemon juice and maple syrup.
Presoak and baste while cooking over an open fire.

title: bake beans
directions: Brown ground beef; add beans, brown sugar, ketchup, mustard, onion soup mix and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour into baking dish and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine and Cheez Whiz.
Mix all other ingredients together; pour melted margarine and Cheez Whiz into this mixture. Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: meat loaf (economy)
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Pack lightly into buttered small loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for one hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: chicken waldorf salad
directions: Combine
first
ingredients
in
a medium bowl; toss gently.
Combine
sour cream, yogurt and salt in a small bowl, stirring
well.
Add
sour
cream
mixture to chicken mixture, tossing well.
Place 1 cup lettuce on plate and top with 1 cup chicken
mixture.
Yields 5 servings.
(Contains 218 calories, 29% from fat, per serving.)

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Cut hot dogs into small pieces.
Pour into crock-pot.
Mix ingredients well.
Pour over hot dogs.
Cook on high until sauce begins to
boil. Turn to low.
Cook approximately 1 hour.

title: marshmallow ice cream
directions: In a large bowl beat eggs until light.
Add sugar and beat until thick.
Blend in Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Makes 1 gallon of the fluffy soft serve type.

title: sauerkraut and sausage
directions: Peel carrots and potatoes; slice.
Place all ingredients in Dutch oven.
Cook for 20 minutes, or until done.
Drain any extra liquid.
Serve with mustard.

title: chicken-n-biscuits
directions: Season and bake chicken in a 1 1/2-quart flat baking dish. Saute onion, green onions and mushrooms in margarine.
Add soup. Let heat thoroughly.
Add cheese; stir until it melts.
Add bacon. Pour soup mixture over chicken.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Cook hamburger in crock-pot until lightly brown.
Drain grease.
Add spices.
Leave on low heat overnight.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick oleo (melted).
Use a 10 x 3-inch pan.
Press into crust and cool.
Beat powdered sugar, eggs and 1 stick oleo for 15 minutes.
Spread over graham cracker crumbs.
Slice bananas on top of mix.
Spread crushed pineapple (not necessary to drain pineapple) over bananas.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate overnight.
Can be topped with cherries and/or nuts.

title: mary's chili
directions: Brown in large skillet the ground beef, onion and green pepper. Add remaining ingredients, except cheese and corn chips.
Simmer 20 minutes all ingredients, except cheese and corn chips.
Before serving, top with grated cheese and corn chips.

title: best ever chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Work up by hand, do not use a mixer.
Do not grease pan.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: homemade bread
directions: Put yeast in bowl, add water, sugar and salt; mix with mixer. Add flour, one cup at a time, as you mix.
After about 3 cups flour, add Crisco.
Continue mixing, adding enough flour until the dough is able to be put on board and knead for at least 8 minutes. Let raise until double in size.
Then put in pans.
Let raise again.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes about 4 large loaves.
